48 unsigned CodeGenTypes::ClangCallConvToLLVMCallConv(CallingConv CC) {
49  switch (CC) {
50  default: return llvm::CallingConv::C;
51  case CC_X86StdCall: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_StdCall;
52  case CC_X86FastCall: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_FastCall;
53  case CC_X86RegCall: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall;
54  case CC_X86ThisCall: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_ThisCall;
55  case CC_Win64: return llvm::CallingConv::Win64;
56  case CC_X86_64SysV: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_64_SysV;
57  case CC_AAPCS: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS;
58  case CC_AAPCS_VFP: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP;
59  case CC_IntelOclBicc: return llvm::CallingConv::Intel_OCL_BI;
60  // TODO: Add support for __pascal to LLVM.
61  case CC_X86Pascal: return llvm::CallingConv::C;
62  // TODO: Add support for __vectorcall to LLVM.
63  case CC_X86VectorCall: return llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall;
64  case CC_AArch64VectorCall: return llvm::CallingConv::AArch64_VectorCall;
65  case CC_SpirFunction: return llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_FUNC;
66  case CC_OpenCLKernel: return CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getOpenCLKernelCallingConv();
67  case CC_PreserveMost: return llvm::CallingConv::PreserveMost;
68  case CC_PreserveAll: return llvm::CallingConv::PreserveAll;
69  case CC_Swift: return llvm::CallingConv::Swift;
70  case CC_SwiftAsync: return llvm::CallingConv::SwiftTail;
71  }
72 }

74 /// Derives the 'this' type for codegen purposes, i.e. ignoring method CVR
75 /// qualification. Either or both of RD and MD may be null. A null RD indicates
76 /// that there is no meaningful 'this' type, and a null MD can occur when
77 /// calling a method pointer.
78 CanQualType CodeGenTypes::DeriveThisType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
79  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
80  QualType RecTy;
81  if (RD)
82  RecTy = Context.getTagDeclType(RD)->getCanonicalTypeInternal();
83  else
84  RecTy = Context.VoidTy;
85 
86  if (MD)
87  RecTy = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(RecTy, MD->getMethodQualifiers().getAddressSpace());
88  return Context.getPointerType(CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(RecTy));
89 }
90 
91 /// Returns the canonical formal type of the given C++ method.
92 static CanQual<FunctionProtoType> GetFormalType(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
93  return MD->getType()->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified()
94  .getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
95 }
96 
97 /// Returns the "extra-canonicalized" return type, which discards
98 /// qualifiers on the return type. Codegen doesn't care about them,
99 /// and it makes ABI code a little easier to be able to assume that
100 /// all parameter and return types are top-level unqualified.
101 static CanQualType GetReturnType(QualType RetTy) {
102  return RetTy->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified().getUnqualifiedType();
103 }

105 /// Arrange the argument and result information for a value of the given
106 /// unprototyped freestanding function type.
107 const CGFunctionInfo &
108 CodeGenTypes::arrangeFreeFunctionType(CanQual<FunctionNoProtoType> FTNP) {
109  // When translating an unprototyped function type, always use a
110  // variadic type.
111  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(FTNP->getReturnType().getUnqualifiedType(),
112  /*instanceMethod=*/false,
113  /*chainCall=*/false, None,
114  FTNP->getExtInfo(), {}, RequiredArgs(0));
115 }
116 
117 static void addExtParameterInfosForCall(
118  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo> &paramInfos,
119  const FunctionProtoType *proto,
120  unsigned prefixArgs,
121  unsigned totalArgs) {
122  assert(proto->hasExtParameterInfos());
123  assert(paramInfos.size() <= prefixArgs);
124  assert(proto->getNumParams() + prefixArgs <= totalArgs);
125 
126  paramInfos.reserve(totalArgs);
127 
128  // Add default infos for any prefix args that don't already have infos.
129  paramInfos.resize(prefixArgs);
130 
131  // Add infos for the prototype.
132  for (const auto &ParamInfo : proto->getExtParameterInfos()) {
133  paramInfos.push_back(ParamInfo);
134  // pass_object_size params have no parameter info.
135  if (ParamInfo.hasPassObjectSize())
136  paramInfos.emplace_back();
137  }
138 
139  assert(paramInfos.size() <= totalArgs &&
140  "Did we forget to insert pass_object_size args?");
141  // Add default infos for the variadic and/or suffix arguments.
142  paramInfos.resize(totalArgs);
143 }
144 
145 /// Adds the formal parameters in FPT to the given prefix. If any parameter in
146 /// FPT has pass_object_size attrs, then we'll add parameters for those, too.
147 static void appendParameterTypes(const CodeGenTypes &CGT,
148  SmallVectorImpl<CanQualType> &prefix,
149  SmallVectorImpl<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo> &paramInfos,
150  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FPT) {
151  // Fast path: don't touch param info if we don't need to.
152  if (!FPT->hasExtParameterInfos()) {
153  assert(paramInfos.empty() &&
154  "We have paramInfos, but the prototype doesn't?");
155  prefix.append(FPT->param_type_begin(), FPT->param_type_end());
156  return;
157  }
158 
159  unsigned PrefixSize = prefix.size();
160  // In the vast majority of cases, we'll have precisely FPT->getNumParams()
161  // parameters; the only thing that can change this is the presence of
162  // pass_object_size. So, we preallocate for the common case.
163  prefix.reserve(prefix.size() + FPT->getNumParams());
164 
165  auto ExtInfos = FPT->getExtParameterInfos();
166  assert(ExtInfos.size() == FPT->getNumParams());
167  for (unsigned I = 0, E = FPT->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
168  prefix.push_back(FPT->getParamType(I));
169  if (ExtInfos[I].hasPassObjectSize())
170  prefix.push_back(CGT.getContext().getSizeType());
171  }
172 
173  addExtParameterInfosForCall(paramInfos, FPT.getTypePtr(), PrefixSize,
174  prefix.size());
175 }
176 
177 /// Arrange the LLVM function layout for a value of the given function
178 /// type, on top of any implicit parameters already stored.
179 static const CGFunctionInfo &
180 arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool instanceMethod,
181  SmallVectorImpl<CanQualType> &prefix,
182  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FTP) {
183  SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> paramInfos;
184  RequiredArgs Required = RequiredArgs::forPrototypePlus(FTP, prefix.size());
185  // FIXME: Kill copy.
186  appendParameterTypes(CGT, prefix, paramInfos, FTP);
187  CanQualType resultType = FTP->getReturnType().getUnqualifiedType();
188 
189  return CGT.arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(resultType, instanceMethod,
190  /*chainCall=*/false, prefix,
191  FTP->getExtInfo(), paramInfos,
192  Required);
193 }
194 
195 /// Arrange the argument and result information for a value of the
196 /// given freestanding function type.
197 const CGFunctionInfo &
198 CodeGenTypes::arrangeFreeFunctionType(CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FTP) {
199  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
200  return ::arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(*this, /*instanceMethod=*/false, argTypes,
201  FTP);
202 }
203 
204 static CallingConv getCallingConventionForDecl(const ObjCMethodDecl *D,
205  bool IsWindows) {
206  // Set the appropriate calling convention for the Function.
207  if (D->hasAttr<StdCallAttr>())
208  return CC_X86StdCall;
209 
210  if (D->hasAttr<FastCallAttr>())
211  return CC_X86FastCall;
212 
213  if (D->hasAttr<RegCallAttr>())
214  return CC_X86RegCall;
215 
216  if (D->hasAttr<ThisCallAttr>())
217  return CC_X86ThisCall;
218 
219  if (D->hasAttr<VectorCallAttr>())
220  return CC_X86VectorCall;
221 
222  if (D->hasAttr<PascalAttr>())
223  return CC_X86Pascal;
224 
225  if (PcsAttr *PCS = D->getAttr<PcsAttr>())
226  return (PCS->getPCS() == PcsAttr::AAPCS ? CC_AAPCS : CC_AAPCS_VFP);
227 
228  if (D->hasAttr<AArch64VectorPcsAttr>())
229  return CC_AArch64VectorCall;
230 
231  if (D->hasAttr<IntelOclBiccAttr>())
232  return CC_IntelOclBicc;
233 
234  if (D->hasAttr<MSABIAttr>())
235  return IsWindows ? CC_C : CC_Win64;
236 
237  if (D->hasAttr<SysVABIAttr>())
238  return IsWindows ? CC_X86_64SysV : CC_C;
239 
240  if (D->hasAttr<PreserveMostAttr>())
241  return CC_PreserveMost;
242 
243  if (D->hasAttr<PreserveAllAttr>())
244  return CC_PreserveAll;
245 
246  return CC_C;
247 }
248 
249 /// Arrange the argument and result information for a call to an
250 /// unknown C++ non-static member function of the given abstract type.
251 /// (A null RD means we don't have any meaningful "this" argument type,
252 /// so fall back to a generic pointer type).
253 /// The member function must be an ordinary function, i.e. not a
254 /// constructor or destructor.
255 const CGFunctionInfo &
256 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCXXMethodType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
257  const FunctionProtoType *FTP,
258  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
259  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
260 
261  // Add the 'this' pointer.
262  argTypes.push_back(DeriveThisType(RD, MD));
263 
264  return ::arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
265  *this, true, argTypes,
266  FTP->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified().getAs<FunctionProtoType>());
267 }

269 /// Set calling convention for CUDA/HIP kernel.
270 static void setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(CanQualType &FTy, CodeGenModule &CGM,
271  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
272  if (FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
273  const FunctionType *FT = FTy->getAs<FunctionType>();
274  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(FT);
275  FTy = FT->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified();
276  }
277 }
278 
279 /// Arrange the argument and result information for a declaration or
280 /// definition of the given C++ non-static member function. The
281 /// member function must be an ordinary function, i.e. not a
282 /// constructor or destructor.
283 const CGFunctionInfo &
284 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
285  assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && "wrong method for constructors!");
286  assert(!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) && "wrong method for destructors!");
287 
288  CanQualType FT = GetFormalType(MD).getAs<Type>();
289  setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(FT, CGM, MD);
290  auto prototype = FT.getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
291 
292  if (MD->isInstance()) {
293  // The abstract case is perfectly fine.
294  const CXXRecordDecl *ThisType = TheCXXABI.getThisArgumentTypeForMethod(MD);
295  return arrangeCXXMethodType(ThisType, prototype.getTypePtr(), MD);
296  }
297 
298  return arrangeFreeFunctionType(prototype);
299 }
300 
301 bool CodeGenTypes::inheritingCtorHasParams(
302  const InheritedConstructor &Inherited, CXXCtorType Type) {
303  // Parameters are unnecessary if we're constructing a base class subobject
304  // and the inherited constructor lives in a virtual base.
305  return Type == Ctor_Complete ||
306  !Inherited.getShadowDecl()->constructsVirtualBase() ||
307  !Target.getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants();
308 }
309 
310 const CGFunctionInfo &
311 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCXXStructorDeclaration(GlobalDecl GD) {
312  auto *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
313 
314  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
315  SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> paramInfos;
316  argTypes.push_back(DeriveThisType(MD->getParent(), MD));
317 
318  bool PassParams = true;
319 
320  if (auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD)) {
321  // A base class inheriting constructor doesn't get forwarded arguments
322  // needed to construct a virtual base (or base class thereof).
323  if (auto Inherited = CD->getInheritedConstructor())
324  PassParams = inheritingCtorHasParams(Inherited, GD.getCtorType());
325  }
326 
327  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FTP = GetFormalType(MD);
328 
329  // Add the formal parameters.
330  if (PassParams)
331  appendParameterTypes(*this, argTypes, paramInfos, FTP);
332 
333  CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgCounts AddedArgs =
334  TheCXXABI.buildStructorSignature(GD, argTypes);
335  if (!paramInfos.empty()) {
336  // Note: prefix implies after the first param.
337  if (AddedArgs.Prefix)
338  paramInfos.insert(paramInfos.begin() + 1, AddedArgs.Prefix,
339  FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo{});
340  if (AddedArgs.Suffix)
341  paramInfos.append(AddedArgs.Suffix,
342  FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo{});
343  }
344 
345  RequiredArgs required =
346  (PassParams && MD->isVariadic() ? RequiredArgs(argTypes.size())
347  : RequiredArgs::All);
348 
349  FunctionType::ExtInfo extInfo = FTP->getExtInfo();
350  CanQualType resultType = TheCXXABI.HasThisReturn(GD)
351  ? argTypes.front()
352  : TheCXXABI.hasMostDerivedReturn(GD)
353  ? CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy
354  : Context.VoidTy;
355  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(resultType, /*instanceMethod=*/true,
356  /*chainCall=*/false, argTypes, extInfo,
357  paramInfos, required);
358 }
359 
360 static SmallVector<CanQualType, 16>
361 getArgTypesForCall(ASTContext &ctx, const CallArgList &args) {
362  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
363  for (auto &arg : args)
364  argTypes.push_back(ctx.getCanonicalParamType(arg.Ty));
365  return argTypes;
366 }
367 
368 static SmallVector<CanQualType, 16>
369 getArgTypesForDeclaration(ASTContext &ctx, const FunctionArgList &args) {
370  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
371  for (auto &arg : args)
372  argTypes.push_back(ctx.getCanonicalParamType(arg->getType()));
373  return argTypes;
374 }
375 
376 static llvm::SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16>
377 getExtParameterInfosForCall(const FunctionProtoType *proto,
378  unsigned prefixArgs, unsigned totalArgs) {
379  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> result;
380  if (proto->hasExtParameterInfos()) {
381  addExtParameterInfosForCall(result, proto, prefixArgs, totalArgs);
382  }
383  return result;
384 }
385 
386 /// Arrange a call to a C++ method, passing the given arguments.
387 ///
388 /// ExtraPrefixArgs is the number of ABI-specific args passed after the `this`
389 /// parameter.
390 /// ExtraSuffixArgs is the number of ABI-specific args passed at the end of
391 /// args.
392 /// PassProtoArgs indicates whether `args` has args for the parameters in the
393 /// given CXXConstructorDecl.
394 const CGFunctionInfo &
395 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCXXConstructorCall(const CallArgList &args,
396  const CXXConstructorDecl *D,
397  CXXCtorType CtorKind,
398  unsigned ExtraPrefixArgs,
399  unsigned ExtraSuffixArgs,
400  bool PassProtoArgs) {
401  // FIXME: Kill copy.
402  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> ArgTypes;
403  for (const auto &Arg : args)
404  ArgTypes.push_back(Context.getCanonicalParamType(Arg.Ty));
405 
406  // +1 for implicit this, which should always be args[0].
407  unsigned TotalPrefixArgs = 1 + ExtraPrefixArgs;
408 
409  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FPT = GetFormalType(D);
410  RequiredArgs Required = PassProtoArgs
411  ? RequiredArgs::forPrototypePlus(
412  FPT, TotalPrefixArgs + ExtraSuffixArgs)
413  : RequiredArgs::All;
414 
415  GlobalDecl GD(D, CtorKind);
416  CanQualType ResultType = TheCXXABI.HasThisReturn(GD)
417  ? ArgTypes.front()
418  : TheCXXABI.hasMostDerivedReturn(GD)
419  ? CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy
420  : Context.VoidTy;
421 
422  FunctionType::ExtInfo Info = FPT->getExtInfo();
423  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> ParamInfos;
424  // If the prototype args are elided, we should only have ABI-specific args,
425  // which never have param info.
426  if (PassProtoArgs && FPT->hasExtParameterInfos()) {
427  // ABI-specific suffix arguments are treated the same as variadic arguments.
428  addExtParameterInfosForCall(ParamInfos, FPT.getTypePtr(), TotalPrefixArgs,
429  ArgTypes.size());
430  }
431  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(ResultType, /*instanceMethod=*/true,
432  /*chainCall=*/false, ArgTypes, Info,
433  ParamInfos, Required);
434 }
435 
436 /// Arrange the argument and result information for the declaration or
437 /// definition of the given function.
438 const CGFunctionInfo &
439 CodeGenTypes::arrangeFunctionDeclaration(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
440  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
441  if (MD->isInstance())
442  return arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(MD);
443 
444  CanQualType FTy = FD->getType()->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified();
445 
446  assert(isa<FunctionType>(FTy));
447  setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(FTy, CGM, FD);
448 
449  // When declaring a function without a prototype, always use a
450  // non-variadic type.
451  if (CanQual<FunctionNoProtoType> noProto = FTy.getAs<FunctionNoProtoType>()) {
452  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
453  noProto->getReturnType(), /*instanceMethod=*/false,
454  /*chainCall=*/false, None, noProto->getExtInfo(), {},RequiredArgs::All);
455  }
456 
457  return arrangeFreeFunctionType(FTy.castAs<FunctionProtoType>());
458 }

460 /// Arrange the argument and result information for the declaration or
461 /// definition of an Objective-C method.
462 const CGFunctionInfo &
463 CodeGenTypes::arrangeObjCMethodDeclaration(const ObjCMethodDecl *MD) {
464  // It happens that this is the same as a call with no optional
465  // arguments, except also using the formal 'self' type.
466  return arrangeObjCMessageSendSignature(MD, MD->getSelfDecl()->getType());
467 }
468 
469 /// Arrange the argument and result information for the function type
470 /// through which to perform a send to the given Objective-C method,
471 /// using the given receiver type. The receiver type is not always
472 /// the 'self' type of the method or even an Objective-C pointer type.
473 /// This is *not* the right method for actually performing such a
474 /// message send, due to the possibility of optional arguments.
475 const CGFunctionInfo &
476 CodeGenTypes::arrangeObjCMessageSendSignature(const ObjCMethodDecl *MD,
477  QualType receiverType) {
478  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTys;
479  SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 4> extParamInfos(2);
480  argTys.push_back(Context.getCanonicalParamType(receiverType));
481  argTys.push_back(Context.getCanonicalParamType(Context.getObjCSelType()));
482  // FIXME: Kill copy?
483  for (const auto *I : MD->parameters()) {
484  argTys.push_back(Context.getCanonicalParamType(I->getType()));
485  auto extParamInfo = FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo().withIsNoEscape(
486  I->hasAttr<NoEscapeAttr>());
487  extParamInfos.push_back(extParamInfo);
488  }
489 
490  FunctionType::ExtInfo einfo;
491  bool IsWindows = getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows();
492  einfo = einfo.withCallingConv(getCallingConventionForDecl(MD, IsWindows));
493 
494  if (getContext().getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
495  MD->hasAttr<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>())
496  einfo = einfo.withProducesResult(true);
497 
498  RequiredArgs required =
499  (MD->isVariadic() ? RequiredArgs(argTys.size()) : RequiredArgs::All);
500 
501  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
502  GetReturnType(MD->getReturnType()), /*instanceMethod=*/false,
503  /*chainCall=*/false, argTys, einfo, extParamInfos, required);
504 }
505 
506 const CGFunctionInfo &
507 CodeGenTypes::arrangeUnprototypedObjCMessageSend(QualType returnType,
508  const CallArgList &args) {
509  auto argTypes = getArgTypesForCall(Context, args);
510  FunctionType::ExtInfo einfo;
511 
512  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
513  GetReturnType(returnType), /*instanceMethod=*/false,
514  /*chainCall=*/false, argTypes, einfo, {}, RequiredArgs::All);
515 }

517 const CGFunctionInfo &
518 CodeGenTypes::arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GlobalDecl GD) {
519  // FIXME: Do we need to handle ObjCMethodDecl?
520  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
521 
522  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl()) ||
523  isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl()))
524  return arrangeCXXStructorDeclaration(GD);
525 
526  return arrangeFunctionDeclaration(FD);
527 }

529 /// Arrange a thunk that takes 'this' as the first parameter followed by
530 /// varargs. Return a void pointer, regardless of the actual return type.
531 /// The body of the thunk will end in a musttail call to a function of the
532 /// correct type, and the caller will bitcast the function to the correct
533 /// prototype.
534 const CGFunctionInfo &
535 CodeGenTypes::arrangeUnprototypedMustTailThunk(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
536  assert(MD->isVirtual() && "only methods have thunks");
537  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FTP = GetFormalType(MD);
538  CanQualType ArgTys[] = {DeriveThisType(MD->getParent(), MD)};
539  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(Context.VoidTy, /*instanceMethod=*/false,
540  /*chainCall=*/false, ArgTys,
541  FTP->getExtInfo(), {}, RequiredArgs(1));
542 }
543 
544 const CGFunctionInfo &
545 CodeGenTypes::arrangeMSCtorClosure(const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
546  CXXCtorType CT) {
547  assert(CT == Ctor_CopyingClosure || CT == Ctor_DefaultClosure);
548 
549  CanQual<FunctionProtoType> FTP = GetFormalType(CD);
550  SmallVector<CanQualType, 2> ArgTys;
551  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = CD->getParent();
552  ArgTys.push_back(DeriveThisType(RD, CD));
553  if (CT == Ctor_CopyingClosure)
554  ArgTys.push_back(*FTP->param_type_begin());
555  if (RD->getNumVBases() > 0)
556  ArgTys.push_back(Context.IntTy);
557  CallingConv CC = Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(
558  /*IsVariadic=*/false, /*IsCXXMethod=*/true);
559  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(Context.VoidTy, /*instanceMethod=*/true,
560  /*chainCall=*/false, ArgTys,
561  FunctionType::ExtInfo(CC), {},
562  RequiredArgs::All);
563 }

565 /// Arrange a call as unto a free function, except possibly with an
566 /// additional number of formal parameters considered required.
567 static const CGFunctionInfo &
568 arrangeFreeFunctionLikeCall(CodeGenTypes &CGT,
569  CodeGenModule &CGM,
570  const CallArgList &args,
571  const FunctionType *fnType,
572  unsigned numExtraRequiredArgs,
573  bool chainCall) {
574  assert(args.size() >= numExtraRequiredArgs);
575 
576  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> paramInfos;
577 
578  // In most cases, there are no optional arguments.
579  RequiredArgs required = RequiredArgs::All;
580 
581  // If we have a variadic prototype, the required arguments are the
582  // extra prefix plus the arguments in the prototype.
583  if (const FunctionProtoType *proto = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(fnType)) {
584  if (proto->isVariadic())
585  required = RequiredArgs::forPrototypePlus(proto, numExtraRequiredArgs);
586 
587  if (proto->hasExtParameterInfos())
588  addExtParameterInfosForCall(paramInfos, proto, numExtraRequiredArgs,
589  args.size());
590 
591  // If we don't have a prototype at all, but we're supposed to
592  // explicitly use the variadic convention for unprototyped calls,
593  // treat all of the arguments as required but preserve the nominal
594  // possibility of variadics.
595  } else if (CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo()
596  .isNoProtoCallVariadic(args,
597  cast<FunctionNoProtoType>(fnType))) {
598  required = RequiredArgs(args.size());
599  }
600 
601  // FIXME: Kill copy.
602  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
603  for (const auto &arg : args)
604  argTypes.push_back(CGT.getContext().getCanonicalParamType(arg.Ty));
605  return CGT.arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(GetReturnType(fnType->getReturnType()),
606  /*instanceMethod=*/false, chainCall,
607  argTypes, fnType->getExtInfo(), paramInfos,
608  required);
609 }
610 
611 /// Figure out the rules for calling a function with the given formal
612 /// type using the given arguments. The arguments are necessary
613 /// because the function might be unprototyped, in which case it's
614 /// target-dependent in crazy ways.
615 const CGFunctionInfo &
616 CodeGenTypes::arrangeFreeFunctionCall(const CallArgList &args,
617  const FunctionType *fnType,
618  bool chainCall) {
619  return arrangeFreeFunctionLikeCall(*this, CGM, args, fnType,
620  chainCall ? 1 : 0, chainCall);
621 }
622 
623 /// A block function is essentially a free function with an
624 /// extra implicit argument.
625 const CGFunctionInfo &
626 CodeGenTypes::arrangeBlockFunctionCall(const CallArgList &args,
627  const FunctionType *fnType) {
628  return arrangeFreeFunctionLikeCall(*this, CGM, args, fnType, 1,
629  /*chainCall=*/false);
630 }
631 
632 const CGFunctionInfo &
633 CodeGenTypes::arrangeBlockFunctionDeclaration(const FunctionProtoType *proto,
634  const FunctionArgList &params) {
635  auto paramInfos = getExtParameterInfosForCall(proto, 1, params.size());
636  auto argTypes = getArgTypesForDeclaration(Context, params);
637 
638  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(GetReturnType(proto->getReturnType()),
639  /*instanceMethod*/ false, /*chainCall*/ false,
640  argTypes, proto->getExtInfo(), paramInfos,
641  RequiredArgs::forPrototypePlus(proto, 1));
642 }

644 const CGFunctionInfo &
645 CodeGenTypes::arrangeBuiltinFunctionCall(QualType resultType,
646  const CallArgList &args) {
647  // FIXME: Kill copy.
648  SmallVector<CanQualType, 16> argTypes;
649  for (const auto &Arg : args)
650  argTypes.push_back(Context.getCanonicalParamType(Arg.Ty));
651  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
652  GetReturnType(resultType), /*instanceMethod=*/false,
653  /*chainCall=*/false, argTypes, FunctionType::ExtInfo(),
654  /*paramInfos=*/ {}, RequiredArgs::All);
655 }

662  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(

669  ArrayRef<CanQualType> argTypes) {

671  resultType, /*instanceMethod=*/false, /*chainCall=*/false,
672  argTypes, FunctionType::ExtInfo(), {}, RequiredArgs::All);

675 /// Arrange a call to a C++ method, passing the given arguments.
676 ///
677 /// numPrefixArgs is the number of ABI-specific prefix arguments we have. It
678 /// does not count `this`.
679 const CGFunctionInfo &
680 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCXXMethodCall(const CallArgList &args,
681  const FunctionProtoType *proto,
682  RequiredArgs required,
683  unsigned numPrefixArgs) {
684  assert(numPrefixArgs + 1 <= args.size() &&
685  "Emitting a call with less args than the required prefix?");
686  // Add one to account for `this`. It's a bit awkward here, but we don't count
687  // `this` in similar places elsewhere.
688  auto paramInfos =
689  getExtParameterInfosForCall(proto, numPrefixArgs + 1, args.size());
690 
691  // FIXME: Kill copy.
692  auto argTypes = getArgTypesForCall(Context, args);
693 
694  FunctionType::ExtInfo info = proto->getExtInfo();
695  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
696  GetReturnType(proto->getReturnType()), /*instanceMethod=*/true,
697  /*chainCall=*/false, argTypes, info, paramInfos, required);
698 }

700 const CGFunctionInfo &CodeGenTypes::arrangeNullaryFunction() {
701  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(
702  getContext().VoidTy, /*instanceMethod=*/false, /*chainCall=*/false,
703  None, FunctionType::ExtInfo(), {}, RequiredArgs::All);
704 }
705 
706 const CGFunctionInfo &
707 CodeGenTypes::arrangeCall(const CGFunctionInfo &signature,
708  const CallArgList &args) {
709  assert(signature.arg_size() <= args.size());
710  if (signature.arg_size() == args.size())
711  return signature;
712 
713  SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16> paramInfos;
714  auto sigParamInfos = signature.getExtParameterInfos();
715  if (!sigParamInfos.empty()) {
716  paramInfos.append(sigParamInfos.begin(), sigParamInfos.end());
717  paramInfos.resize(args.size());
718  }
719 
720  auto argTypes = getArgTypesForCall(Context, args);
721 
722  assert(signature.getRequiredArgs().allowsOptionalArgs());
723  return arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(signature.getReturnType(),
724  signature.isInstanceMethod(),
725  signature.isChainCall(),
726  argTypes,
727  signature.getExtInfo(),
728  paramInfos,
729  signature.getRequiredArgs());
730 }

732 namespace clang {
733 namespace CodeGen {
734 void computeSPIRKernelABIInfo(CodeGenModule &CGM, CGFunctionInfo &FI);
735 }
736 }
737 
738 /// Arrange the argument and result information for an abstract value
739 /// of a given function type. This is the method which all of the
740 /// above functions ultimately defer to.
741 const CGFunctionInfo &
742 CodeGenTypes::arrangeLLVMFunctionInfo(CanQualType resultType,
743  bool instanceMethod,
744  bool chainCall,
745  ArrayRef<CanQualType> argTypes,
746  FunctionType::ExtInfo info,
747  ArrayRef<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo> paramInfos,
748  RequiredArgs required) {
749  assert(llvm::all_of(argTypes,
750  [](CanQualType T) { return T.isCanonicalAsParam(); }));
751 
752  // Lookup or create unique function info.
753  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
754  CGFunctionInfo::Profile(ID, instanceMethod, chainCall, info, paramInfos,
755  required, resultType, argTypes);
756 
757  void *insertPos = nullptr;
758  CGFunctionInfo *FI = FunctionInfos.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
759  if (FI)
760  return *FI;
761 
762  unsigned CC = ClangCallConvToLLVMCallConv(info.getCC());
763  // This is required so SYCL kernels are successfully processed by tools from CUDA. Kernels
764  // with a `spir_kernel` calling convention are ignored otherwise.
765  if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL &&
766  (CGM.getTriple().isNVPTX() || CGM.getTriple().isAMDGCN()) &&
767  getContext().getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
768  CC = llvm::CallingConv::C;
769  }
770 
771  // Construct the function info. We co-allocate the ArgInfos.
772  FI = CGFunctionInfo::create(CC, instanceMethod, chainCall, info,
773  paramInfos, resultType, argTypes, required);
774  FunctionInfos.InsertNode(FI, insertPos);
775 
776  bool inserted = FunctionsBeingProcessed.insert(FI).second;
777  (void)inserted;
778  assert(inserted && "Recursively being processed?");
779 
780  // Compute ABI information.
781  if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL) {
782  // Force target independent argument handling for the host visible
783  // kernel functions.
784  computeSPIRKernelABIInfo(CGM, *FI);
785  } else if (info.getCC() == CC_Swift || info.getCC() == CC_SwiftAsync) {
786  swiftcall::computeABIInfo(CGM, *FI);
787  } else {
788  getABIInfo().computeInfo(*FI);
789  }
790 
791  // Loop over all of the computed argument and return value info. If any of
792  // them are direct or extend without a specified coerce type, specify the
793  // default now.
794  ABIArgInfo &retInfo = FI->getReturnInfo();
795  if (retInfo.canHaveCoerceToType() && retInfo.getCoerceToType() == nullptr)
796  retInfo.setCoerceToType(ConvertType(FI->getReturnType()));
797 
798  for (auto &I : FI->arguments())
799  if (I.info.canHaveCoerceToType() && I.info.getCoerceToType() == nullptr)
800  I.info.setCoerceToType(ConvertType(I.type));
801 
802  bool erased = FunctionsBeingProcessed.erase(FI); (void)erased;
803  assert(erased && "Not in set?");
804 
805  return *FI;
806 }
807 
808 CGFunctionInfo *CGFunctionInfo::create(unsigned llvmCC,
809  bool instanceMethod,
810  bool chainCall,
811  const FunctionType::ExtInfo &info,
812  ArrayRef<ExtParameterInfo> paramInfos,
813  CanQualType resultType,
814  ArrayRef<CanQualType> argTypes,
815  RequiredArgs required) {
816  assert(paramInfos.empty() || paramInfos.size() == argTypes.size());
817  assert(!required.allowsOptionalArgs() ||
818  required.getNumRequiredArgs() <= argTypes.size());
819 
820  void *buffer =
821  operator new(totalSizeToAlloc<ArgInfo, ExtParameterInfo>(
822  argTypes.size() + 1, paramInfos.size()));
823 
824  CGFunctionInfo *FI = new(buffer) CGFunctionInfo();
825  FI->CallingConvention = llvmCC;
826  FI->EffectiveCallingConvention = llvmCC;
827  FI->ASTCallingConvention = info.getCC();
828  FI->InstanceMethod = instanceMethod;
829  FI->ChainCall = chainCall;
830  FI->CmseNSCall = info.getCmseNSCall();
831  FI->NoReturn = info.getNoReturn();
832  FI->ReturnsRetained = info.getProducesResult();
833  FI->NoCallerSavedRegs = info.getNoCallerSavedRegs();
834  FI->NoCfCheck = info.getNoCfCheck();
835  FI->Required = required;
836  FI->HasRegParm = info.getHasRegParm();
837  FI->RegParm = info.getRegParm();
838  FI->ArgStruct = nullptr;
839  FI->ArgStructAlign = 0;
840  FI->NumArgs = argTypes.size();
841  FI->HasExtParameterInfos = !paramInfos.empty();
842  FI->getArgsBuffer()[0].type = resultType;
843  for (unsigned i = 0, e = argTypes.size(); i != e; ++i)
844  FI->getArgsBuffer()[i + 1].type = argTypes[i];
845  for (unsigned i = 0, e = paramInfos.size(); i != e; ++i)
846  FI->getExtParameterInfosBuffer()[i] = paramInfos[i];
847  return FI;
848 }

850 /***/
851 
852 namespace {
853 // ABIArgInfo::Expand implementation.
854 
855 // Specifies the way QualType passed as ABIArgInfo::Expand is expanded.
856 struct TypeExpansion {
857  enum TypeExpansionKind {
858  // Elements of constant arrays are expanded recursively.
859  TEK_ConstantArray,
860  // Record fields are expanded recursively (but if record is a union, only
861  // the field with the largest size is expanded).
862  TEK_Record,
863  // For complex types, real and imaginary parts are expanded recursively.
864  TEK_Complex,
865  // All other types are not expandable.
866  TEK_None
867  };
868 
869  const TypeExpansionKind Kind;
870 
871  TypeExpansion(TypeExpansionKind K) : Kind(K) {}
872  virtual ~TypeExpansion() {}
873 };
874 
875 struct ConstantArrayExpansion : TypeExpansion {
876  QualType EltTy;
877  uint64_t NumElts;
878 
879  ConstantArrayExpansion(QualType EltTy, uint64_t NumElts)
880  : TypeExpansion(TEK_ConstantArray), EltTy(EltTy), NumElts(NumElts) {}
881  static bool classof(const TypeExpansion *TE) {
882  return TE->Kind == TEK_ConstantArray;
883  }
884 };
885 
886 struct RecordExpansion : TypeExpansion {
887  SmallVector<const CXXBaseSpecifier *, 1> Bases;
888 
889  SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 1> Fields;
890 
891  RecordExpansion(SmallVector<const CXXBaseSpecifier *, 1> &&Bases,
892  SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 1> &&Fields)
893  : TypeExpansion(TEK_Record), Bases(std::move(Bases)),
894  Fields(std::move(Fields)) {}
895  static bool classof(const TypeExpansion *TE) {
896  return TE->Kind == TEK_Record;
897  }
898 };
899 
900 struct ComplexExpansion : TypeExpansion {
901  QualType EltTy;
902 
903  ComplexExpansion(QualType EltTy) : TypeExpansion(TEK_Complex), EltTy(EltTy) {}
904  static bool classof(const TypeExpansion *TE) {
905  return TE->Kind == TEK_Complex;
906  }
907 };
908 
909 struct NoExpansion : TypeExpansion {
910  NoExpansion() : TypeExpansion(TEK_None) {}
911  static bool classof(const TypeExpansion *TE) {
912  return TE->Kind == TEK_None;
913  }
914 };
915 } // namespace
916 
917 static std::unique_ptr<TypeExpansion>
918 getTypeExpansion(QualType Ty, const ASTContext &Context) {
919  if (const ConstantArrayType *AT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(Ty)) {
920  return std::make_unique<ConstantArrayExpansion>(
921  AT->getElementType(), AT->getSize().getZExtValue());
922  }
923  if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
924  SmallVector<const CXXBaseSpecifier *, 1> Bases;
925  SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 1> Fields;
926  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
927  assert(!RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember() &&
928  "Cannot expand structure with flexible array.");
929  if (RD->isUnion()) {
930  // Unions can be here only in degenerative cases - all the fields are same
931  // after flattening. Thus we have to use the "largest" field.
932  const FieldDecl *LargestFD = nullptr;
933  CharUnits UnionSize = CharUnits::Zero();
934 
935  for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
936  if (FD->isZeroLengthBitField(Context))
937  continue;
938  assert(!FD->isBitField() &&
939  "Cannot expand structure with bit-field members.");
940  CharUnits FieldSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(FD->getType());
941  if (UnionSize < FieldSize) {
942  UnionSize = FieldSize;
943  LargestFD = FD;
944  }
945  }
946  if (LargestFD)
947  Fields.push_back(LargestFD);
948  } else {
949  if (const auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
950  assert(!CXXRD->isDynamicClass() &&
951  "cannot expand vtable pointers in dynamic classes");
952  llvm::append_range(Bases, llvm::make_pointer_range(CXXRD->bases()));
953  }
954 
955  for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
956  if (FD->isZeroLengthBitField(Context))
957  continue;
958  assert(!FD->isBitField() &&
959  "Cannot expand structure with bit-field members.");
960  Fields.push_back(FD);
961  }
962  }
963  return std::make_unique<RecordExpansion>(std::move(Bases),
964  std::move(Fields));
965  }
966  if (const ComplexType *CT = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
967  return std::make_unique<ComplexExpansion>(CT->getElementType());
968  }
969  return std::make_unique<NoExpansion>();
970 }
971 
972 static int getExpansionSize(QualType Ty, const ASTContext &Context) {
973  auto Exp = getTypeExpansion(Ty, Context);
974  if (auto CAExp = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
975  return CAExp->NumElts * getExpansionSize(CAExp->EltTy, Context);
976  }
977  if (auto RExp = dyn_cast<RecordExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
978  int Res = 0;
979  for (auto BS : RExp->Bases)
980  Res += getExpansionSize(BS->getType(), Context);
981  for (auto FD : RExp->Fields)
982  Res += getExpansionSize(FD->getType(), Context);
983  return Res;
984  }
985  if (isa<ComplexExpansion>(Exp.get()))
986  return 2;
987  assert(isa<NoExpansion>(Exp.get()));
988  return 1;
989 }
990 
991 void
992 CodeGenTypes::getExpandedTypes(QualType Ty,
993  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Type *>::iterator &TI) {
994  auto Exp = getTypeExpansion(Ty, Context);
995  if (auto CAExp = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
996  for (int i = 0, n = CAExp->NumElts; i < n; i++) {
997  getExpandedTypes(CAExp->EltTy, TI);
998  }
999  } else if (auto RExp = dyn_cast<RecordExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1000  for (auto BS : RExp->Bases)
1001  getExpandedTypes(BS->getType(), TI);
1002  for (auto FD : RExp->Fields)
1003  getExpandedTypes(FD->getType(), TI);
1004  } else if (auto CExp = dyn_cast<ComplexExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1005  llvm::Type *EltTy = ConvertType(CExp->EltTy);
1006  *TI++ = EltTy;
1007  *TI++ = EltTy;
1008  } else {
1009  assert(isa<NoExpansion>(Exp.get()));
1010  *TI++ = ConvertType(Ty);
1011  }
1012 }
1013 
1014 static void forConstantArrayExpansion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1015  ConstantArrayExpansion *CAE,
1016  Address BaseAddr,
1017  llvm::function_ref<void(Address)> Fn) {
1018  CharUnits EltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CAE->EltTy);
1019  CharUnits EltAlign =
1020  BaseAddr.getAlignment().alignmentOfArrayElement(EltSize);
1021  llvm::Type *EltTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CAE->EltTy);
1022 
1023  for (int i = 0, n = CAE->NumElts; i < n; i++) {
1024  llvm::Value *EltAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(
1025  BaseAddr.getElementType(), BaseAddr.getPointer(), 0, i);
1026  Fn(Address(EltAddr, EltTy, EltAlign));
1027  }
1028 }
1029 
1030 void CodeGenFunction::ExpandTypeFromArgs(QualType Ty, LValue LV,
1031  llvm::Function::arg_iterator &AI) {
1032  assert(LV.isSimple() &&
1033  "Unexpected non-simple lvalue during struct expansion.");
1034 
1035  auto Exp = getTypeExpansion(Ty, getContext());
1036  if (auto CAExp = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1037  forConstantArrayExpansion(
1038  *this, CAExp, LV.getAddress(*this), [&](Address EltAddr) {
1039  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(EltAddr, CAExp->EltTy);
1040  ExpandTypeFromArgs(CAExp->EltTy, LV, AI);
1041  });
1042  } else if (auto RExp = dyn_cast<RecordExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1043  Address This = LV.getAddress(*this);
1044  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier *BS : RExp->Bases) {
1045  // Perform a single step derived-to-base conversion.
1046  Address Base =
1047  GetAddressOfBaseClass(This, Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), &BS, &BS + 1,
1048  /*NullCheckValue=*/false, SourceLocation());
1049  LValue SubLV = MakeAddrLValue(Base, BS->getType());
1050 
1051  // Recurse onto bases.
1052  ExpandTypeFromArgs(BS->getType(), SubLV, AI);
1053  }
1054  for (auto FD : RExp->Fields) {
1055  // FIXME: What are the right qualifiers here?
1056  LValue SubLV = EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LV, FD);
1057  ExpandTypeFromArgs(FD->getType(), SubLV, AI);
1058  }
1059  } else if (isa<ComplexExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1060  auto realValue = &*AI++;
1061  auto imagValue = &*AI++;
1062  EmitStoreOfComplex(ComplexPairTy(realValue, imagValue), LV, /*init*/ true);
1063  } else {
1064  // Call EmitStoreOfScalar except when the lvalue is a bitfield to emit a
1065  // primitive store.
1066  assert(isa<NoExpansion>(Exp.get()));
1067  llvm::Value *Arg = &*AI++;
1068  if (LV.isBitField()) {
1069  EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(Arg), LV);
1070  } else {
1071  // TODO: currently there are some places are inconsistent in what LLVM
1072  // pointer type they use (see D118744). Once clang uses opaque pointers
1073  // all LLVM pointer types will be the same and we can remove this check.
1074  if (Arg->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
1075  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
1076  Arg = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg, Addr.getElementType());
1077  }
1078  EmitStoreOfScalar(Arg, LV);
1079  }
1080  }
1081 }
1082 
1083 void CodeGenFunction::ExpandTypeToArgs(
1084  QualType Ty, CallArg Arg, llvm::FunctionType *IRFuncTy,
1085  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Value *> &IRCallArgs, unsigned &IRCallArgPos) {
1086  auto Exp = getTypeExpansion(Ty, getContext());
1087  if (auto CAExp = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1088  Address Addr = Arg.hasLValue() ? Arg.getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
1089  : Arg.getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
1090  forConstantArrayExpansion(
1091  *this, CAExp, Addr, [&](Address EltAddr) {
1092  CallArg EltArg = CallArg(
1093  convertTempToRValue(EltAddr, CAExp->EltTy, SourceLocation()),
1094  CAExp->EltTy);
1095  ExpandTypeToArgs(CAExp->EltTy, EltArg, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs,
1096  IRCallArgPos);
1097  });
1098  } else if (auto RExp = dyn_cast<RecordExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1099  Address This = Arg.hasLValue() ? Arg.getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
1100  : Arg.getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
1101  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier *BS : RExp->Bases) {
1102  // Perform a single step derived-to-base conversion.
1103  Address Base =
1104  GetAddressOfBaseClass(This, Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), &BS, &BS + 1,
1105  /*NullCheckValue=*/false, SourceLocation());
1106  CallArg BaseArg = CallArg(RValue::getAggregate(Base), BS->getType());
1107 
1108  // Recurse onto bases.
1109  ExpandTypeToArgs(BS->getType(), BaseArg, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs,
1110  IRCallArgPos);
1111  }
1112 
1113  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(This, Ty);
1114  for (auto FD : RExp->Fields) {
1115  CallArg FldArg =
1116  CallArg(EmitRValueForField(LV, FD, SourceLocation()), FD->getType());
1117  ExpandTypeToArgs(FD->getType(), FldArg, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs,
1118  IRCallArgPos);
1119  }
1120  } else if (isa<ComplexExpansion>(Exp.get())) {
1121  ComplexPairTy CV = Arg.getKnownRValue().getComplexVal();
1122  IRCallArgs[IRCallArgPos++] = CV.first;
1123  IRCallArgs[IRCallArgPos++] = CV.second;
1124  } else {
1125  assert(isa<NoExpansion>(Exp.get()));
1126  auto RV = Arg.getKnownRValue();
1127  assert(RV.isScalar() &&
1128  "Unexpected non-scalar rvalue during struct expansion.");
1129 
1130  // Insert a bitcast as needed.
1131  llvm::Value *V = RV.getScalarVal();
1132  if (IRCallArgPos < IRFuncTy->getNumParams() &&
1133  V->getType() != IRFuncTy->getParamType(IRCallArgPos))
1134  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IRFuncTy->getParamType(IRCallArgPos));
1135 
1136  IRCallArgs[IRCallArgPos++] = V;
1137  }
1138 }
1139 
1140 /// Create a temporary allocation for the purposes of coercion.
1141 static Address CreateTempAllocaForCoercion(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Type *Ty,
1142  CharUnits MinAlign,
1143  const Twine &Name = "tmp") {
1144  // Don't use an alignment that's worse than what LLVM would prefer.
1145  auto PrefAlign = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(Ty);
1146  CharUnits Align = std::max(MinAlign, CharUnits::fromQuantity(PrefAlign));
1147 
1148  return CGF.CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Align, Name + ".coerce");
1149 }
1150 
1151 /// EnterStructPointerForCoercedAccess - Given a struct pointer that we are
1152 /// accessing some number of bytes out of it, try to gep into the struct to get
1153 /// at its inner goodness. Dive as deep as possible without entering an element
1154 /// with an in-memory size smaller than DstSize.
1155 static Address
1156 EnterStructPointerForCoercedAccess(Address SrcPtr,
1157  llvm::StructType *SrcSTy,
1158  uint64_t DstSize, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1159  // We can't dive into a zero-element struct.
1160  if (SrcSTy->getNumElements() == 0) return SrcPtr;
1161 
1162  llvm::Type *FirstElt = SrcSTy->getElementType(0);
1163 
1164  // If the first elt is at least as large as what we're looking for, or if the
1165  // first element is the same size as the whole struct, we can enter it. The
1166  // comparison must be made on the store size and not the alloca size. Using
1167  // the alloca size may overstate the size of the load.
1168  uint64_t FirstEltSize =
1169  CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(FirstElt);
1170  if (FirstEltSize < DstSize &&
1171  FirstEltSize < CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(SrcSTy))
1172  return SrcPtr;
1173 
1174  // GEP into the first element.
1175  SrcPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(SrcPtr, 0, "coerce.dive");
1176 
1177  // If the first element is a struct, recurse.
1178  llvm::Type *SrcTy = SrcPtr.getElementType();
1179  if (llvm::StructType *SrcSTy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(SrcTy))
1180  return EnterStructPointerForCoercedAccess(SrcPtr, SrcSTy, DstSize, CGF);
1181 
1182  return SrcPtr;
1183 }
1184 
1185 /// CoerceIntOrPtrToIntOrPtr - Convert a value Val to the specific Ty where both
1186 /// are either integers or pointers. This does a truncation of the value if it
1187 /// is too large or a zero extension if it is too small.
1188 ///
1189 /// This behaves as if the value were coerced through memory, so on big-endian
1190 /// targets the high bits are preserved in a truncation, while little-endian
1191 /// targets preserve the low bits.
1192 static llvm::Value *CoerceIntOrPtrToIntOrPtr(llvm::Value *Val,
1193  llvm::Type *Ty,
1194  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1195  if (Val->getType() == Ty)
1196  return Val;
1197 
1198  if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(Val->getType())) {
1199  // If this is Pointer->Pointer avoid conversion to and from int.
1200  if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(Ty))
1201  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, Ty, "coerce.val");
1202 
1203  // Convert the pointer to an integer so we can play with its width.
1204  Val = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Val, CGF.IntPtrTy, "coerce.val.pi");
1205  }
1206 
1207  llvm::Type *DestIntTy = Ty;
1208  if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(DestIntTy))
1209  DestIntTy = CGF.IntPtrTy;
1210 
1211  if (Val->getType() != DestIntTy) {
1212  const llvm::DataLayout &DL = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout();
1213  if (DL.isBigEndian()) {
1214  // Preserve the high bits on big-endian targets.
1215  // That is what memory coercion does.
1216  uint64_t SrcSize = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Val->getType());
1217  uint64_t DstSize = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(DestIntTy);
1218 
1219  if (SrcSize > DstSize) {
1220  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateLShr(Val, SrcSize - DstSize, "coerce.highbits");
1221  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateTrunc(Val, DestIntTy, "coerce.val.ii");
1222  } else {
1223  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateZExt(Val, DestIntTy, "coerce.val.ii");
1224  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateShl(Val, DstSize - SrcSize, "coerce.highbits");
1225  }
1226  } else {
1227  // Little-endian targets preserve the low bits. No shifts required.
1228  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Val, DestIntTy, false, "coerce.val.ii");
1229  }
1230  }
1231 
1232  if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(Ty))
1233  Val = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, Ty, "coerce.val.ip");
1234  return Val;
1235 }
1236 
1237 
1238 
1239 /// CreateCoercedLoad - Create a load from \arg SrcPtr interpreted as
1240 /// a pointer to an object of type \arg Ty, known to be aligned to
1241 /// \arg SrcAlign bytes.
1242 ///
1243 /// This safely handles the case when the src type is smaller than the
1244 /// destination type; in this situation the values of bits which not
1245 /// present in the src are undefined.
1246 static llvm::Value *CreateCoercedLoad(Address Src, llvm::Type *Ty,
1247  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1248  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src.getElementType();
1249 
1250  // If SrcTy and Ty are the same, just do a load.
1251  if (SrcTy == Ty)
1252  return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Src);
1253 
1254  llvm::TypeSize DstSize = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Ty);
1255 
1256  if (llvm::StructType *SrcSTy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(SrcTy)) {
1257  Src = EnterStructPointerForCoercedAccess(Src, SrcSTy,
1258  DstSize.getFixedSize(), CGF);
1259  SrcTy = Src.getElementType();
1260  }
1261 
1262  llvm::TypeSize SrcSize = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
1263 
1264  // If the source and destination are integer or pointer types, just do an
1265  // extension or truncation to the desired type.
1266  if ((isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ty) || isa<llvm::PointerType>(Ty)) &&
1267  (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy) || isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy))) {
1268  llvm::Value *Load = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Src);
1269  return CoerceIntOrPtrToIntOrPtr(Load, Ty, CGF);
1270  }
1271 
1272  // If load is legal, just bitcast the src pointer.
1273  if (!SrcSize.isScalable() && !DstSize.isScalable() &&
1274  SrcSize.getFixedSize() >= DstSize.getFixedSize()) {
1275  // Generally SrcSize is never greater than DstSize, since this means we are
1276  // losing bits. However, this can happen in cases where the structure has
1277  // additional padding, for example due to a user specified alignment.
1278  //
1279  // FIXME: Assert that we aren't truncating non-padding bits when have access
1280  // to that information.
1281  Src = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Src, Ty);
1282  return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Src);
1283  }
1284 
1285  // If coercing a fixed vector to a scalable vector for ABI compatibility, and
1286  // the types match, use the llvm.experimental.vector.insert intrinsic to
1287  // perform the conversion.
1288  if (auto *ScalableDst = dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Ty)) {
1289  if (auto *FixedSrc = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy)) {
1290  // If we are casting a fixed i8 vector to a scalable 16 x i1 predicate
1291  // vector, use a vector insert and bitcast the result.
1292  bool NeedsBitcast = false;
1293  auto PredType =
1294  llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(), 16);
1295  llvm::Type *OrigType = Ty;
1296  if (ScalableDst == PredType &&
1297  FixedSrc->getElementType() == CGF.Builder.getInt8Ty()) {
1298  ScalableDst = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(CGF.Builder.getInt8Ty(), 2);
1299  NeedsBitcast = true;
1300  }
1301  if (ScalableDst->getElementType() == FixedSrc->getElementType()) {
1302  auto *Load = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Src);
1303  auto *UndefVec = llvm::UndefValue::get(ScalableDst);
1304  auto *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty);
1305  llvm::Value *Result = CGF.Builder.CreateInsertVector(
1306  ScalableDst, UndefVec, Load, Zero, "castScalableSve");
1307  if (NeedsBitcast)
1308  Result = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Result, OrigType);
1309  return Result;
1310  }
1311  }
1312  }
1313 
1314  // Otherwise do coercion through memory. This is stupid, but simple.
1315  Address Tmp =
1316  CreateTempAllocaForCoercion(CGF, Ty, Src.getAlignment(), Src.getName());
1317  CGF.Builder.CreateMemCpy(
1318  Tmp.getPointer(), Tmp.getAlignment().getAsAlign(), Src.getPointer(),
1319  Src.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
1320  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, SrcSize.getKnownMinSize()));
1321  return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Tmp);
1322 }
1323 
1324 // Function to store a first-class aggregate into memory. We prefer to
1325 // store the elements rather than the aggregate to be more friendly to
1326 // fast-isel.
1327 // FIXME: Do we need to recurse here?
1328 void CodeGenFunction::EmitAggregateStore(llvm::Value *Val, Address Dest,
1329  bool DestIsVolatile) {
1330  // Prefer scalar stores to first-class aggregate stores.
1331  if (llvm::StructType *STy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(Val->getType())) {
1332  for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
1333  Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Dest, i);
1334  llvm::Value *Elt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Val, i);
1335  Builder.CreateStore(Elt, EltPtr, DestIsVolatile);
1336  }
1337  } else {
1338  Builder.CreateStore(Val, Dest, DestIsVolatile);
1339  }
1340 }
1341 
1342 /// CreateCoercedStore - Create a store to \arg DstPtr from \arg Src,
1343 /// where the source and destination may have different types. The
1344 /// destination is known to be aligned to \arg DstAlign bytes.
1345 ///
1346 /// This safely handles the case when the src type is larger than the
1347 /// destination type; the upper bits of the src will be lost.
1348 static void CreateCoercedStore(llvm::Value *Src,
1349  Address Dst,
1350  bool DstIsVolatile,
1351  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1352  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1353  llvm::Type *DstTy = Dst.getElementType();
1354  if (SrcTy == DstTy) {
1355  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Src, Dst, DstIsVolatile);
1356  return;
1357  }
1358 
1359  llvm::TypeSize SrcSize = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
1360 
1361  if (llvm::StructType *DstSTy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(DstTy)) {
1362  Dst = EnterStructPointerForCoercedAccess(Dst, DstSTy,
1363  SrcSize.getFixedSize(), CGF);
1364  DstTy = Dst.getElementType();
1365  }
1366 
1367  llvm::PointerType *SrcPtrTy = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy);
1368  llvm::PointerType *DstPtrTy = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(DstTy);
1369  if (SrcPtrTy && DstPtrTy &&
1370  SrcPtrTy->getAddressSpace() != DstPtrTy->getAddressSpace()) {
1371  Src = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Src, DstTy);
1372  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Src, Dst, DstIsVolatile);
1373  return;
1374  }
1375 
1376  // If the source and destination are integer or pointer types, just do an
1377  // extension or truncation to the desired type.
1378  if ((isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcTy) || isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) &&
1379  (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstTy) || isa<llvm::PointerType>(DstTy))) {
1380  Src = CoerceIntOrPtrToIntOrPtr(Src, DstTy, CGF);
1381  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Src, Dst, DstIsVolatile);
1382  return;
1383  }
1384 
1385  llvm::TypeSize DstSize = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(DstTy);
1386 
1387  // If store is legal, just bitcast the src pointer.
1388  if (isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy) ||
1389  isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(DstTy) ||
1390  SrcSize.getFixedSize() <= DstSize.getFixedSize()) {
1391  Dst = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Dst, SrcTy);
1392  CGF.EmitAggregateStore(Src, Dst, DstIsVolatile);
1393  } else {
1394  // Otherwise do coercion through memory. This is stupid, but
1395  // simple.
1396 
1397  // Generally SrcSize is never greater than DstSize, since this means we are
1398  // losing bits. However, this can happen in cases where the structure has
1399  // additional padding, for example due to a user specified alignment.
1400  //
1401  // FIXME: Assert that we aren't truncating non-padding bits when have access
1402  // to that information.
1403  Address Tmp = CreateTempAllocaForCoercion(CGF, SrcTy, Dst.getAlignment());
1404  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Src, Tmp);
1405  CGF.Builder.CreateMemCpy(
1406  Dst.getPointer(), Dst.getAlignment().getAsAlign(), Tmp.getPointer(),
1407  Tmp.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
1408  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, DstSize.getFixedSize()));
1409  }
1410 }
1411 
1412 static Address emitAddressAtOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
1413  const ABIArgInfo &info) {
1414  if (unsigned offset = info.getDirectOffset()) {
1415  addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, CGF.Int8Ty);
1416  addr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(addr,
1417  CharUnits::fromQuantity(offset));
1418  addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, info.getCoerceToType());
1419  }
1420  return addr;
1421 }
1422 
1423 namespace {
1424 
1425 /// Encapsulates information about the way function arguments from
1426 /// CGFunctionInfo should be passed to actual LLVM IR function.
1427 class ClangToLLVMArgMapping {
1428  static const unsigned InvalidIndex = ~0U;
1429  unsigned InallocaArgNo;
1430  unsigned SRetArgNo;
1431  unsigned TotalIRArgs;
1432 
1433  /// Arguments of LLVM IR function corresponding to single Clang argument.
1434  struct IRArgs {
1435  unsigned PaddingArgIndex;
1436  // Argument is expanded to IR arguments at positions
1437  // [FirstArgIndex, FirstArgIndex + NumberOfArgs).
1438  unsigned FirstArgIndex;
1439  unsigned NumberOfArgs;
1440 
1441  IRArgs()
1442  : PaddingArgIndex(InvalidIndex), FirstArgIndex(InvalidIndex),
1443  NumberOfArgs(0) {}
1444  };
1445 
1446  SmallVector<IRArgs, 8> ArgInfo;
1447 
1448 public:
1449  ClangToLLVMArgMapping(const ASTContext &Context, const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
1450  bool OnlyRequiredArgs = false)
1451  : InallocaArgNo(InvalidIndex), SRetArgNo(InvalidIndex), TotalIRArgs(0),
1452  ArgInfo(OnlyRequiredArgs ? FI.getNumRequiredArgs() : FI.arg_size()) {
1453  construct(Context, FI, OnlyRequiredArgs);
1454  }
1455 
1456  bool hasInallocaArg() const { return InallocaArgNo != InvalidIndex; }
1457  unsigned getInallocaArgNo() const {
1458  assert(hasInallocaArg());
1459  return InallocaArgNo;
1460  }
1461 
1462  bool hasSRetArg() const { return SRetArgNo != InvalidIndex; }
1463  unsigned getSRetArgNo() const {
1464  assert(hasSRetArg());
1465  return SRetArgNo;
1466  }
1467 
1468  unsigned totalIRArgs() const { return TotalIRArgs; }
1469 
1470  bool hasPaddingArg(unsigned ArgNo) const {
1471  assert(ArgNo < ArgInfo.size());
1472  return ArgInfo[ArgNo].PaddingArgIndex != InvalidIndex;
1473  }
1474  unsigned getPaddingArgNo(unsigned ArgNo) const {
1475  assert(hasPaddingArg(ArgNo));
1476  return ArgInfo[ArgNo].PaddingArgIndex;
1477  }
1478 
1479  /// Returns index of first IR argument corresponding to ArgNo, and their
1480  /// quantity.
1481  std::pair<unsigned, unsigned> getIRArgs(unsigned ArgNo) const {
1482  assert(ArgNo < ArgInfo.size());
1483  return std::make_pair(ArgInfo[ArgNo].FirstArgIndex,
1484  ArgInfo[ArgNo].NumberOfArgs);
1485  }
1486 
1487 private:
1488  void construct(const ASTContext &Context, const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
1489  bool OnlyRequiredArgs);
1490 };
1491 
1492 void ClangToLLVMArgMapping::construct(const ASTContext &Context,
1493  const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
1494  bool OnlyRequiredArgs) {
1495  unsigned IRArgNo = 0;
1496  bool SwapThisWithSRet = false;
1497  const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
1498 
1499  if (RetAI.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Indirect) {
1500  SwapThisWithSRet = RetAI.isSRetAfterThis();
1501  SRetArgNo = SwapThisWithSRet ? 1 : IRArgNo++;
1502  }
1503 
1504  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
1505  unsigned NumArgs = OnlyRequiredArgs ? FI.getNumRequiredArgs() : FI.arg_size();
1506  for (CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator I = FI.arg_begin(); ArgNo < NumArgs;
1507  ++I, ++ArgNo) {
1508  assert(I != FI.arg_end());
1509  QualType ArgType = I->type;
1510  const ABIArgInfo &AI = I->info;
1511  // Collect data about IR arguments corresponding to Clang argument ArgNo.
1512  auto &IRArgs = ArgInfo[ArgNo];
1513 
1514  if (AI.getPaddingType())
1515  IRArgs.PaddingArgIndex = IRArgNo++;
1516 
1517  switch (AI.getKind()) {
1518  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
1519  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
1520  // FIXME: handle sseregparm someday...
1521  llvm::StructType *STy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(AI.getCoerceToType());
1522  if (AI.isDirect() && AI.getCanBeFlattened() && STy) {
1523  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = STy->getNumElements();
1524  } else {
1525  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = 1;
1526  }
1527  break;
1528  }
1529  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
1530  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
1531  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = 1;
1532  break;
1533  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
1534  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
1535  // ignore and inalloca doesn't have matching LLVM parameters.
1536  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = 0;
1537  break;
1538  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
1539  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = AI.getCoerceAndExpandTypeSequence().size();
1540  break;
1541  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
1542  IRArgs.NumberOfArgs = getExpansionSize(ArgType, Context);
1543  break;
1544  }
1545 
1546  if (IRArgs.NumberOfArgs > 0) {
1547  IRArgs.FirstArgIndex = IRArgNo;
1548  IRArgNo += IRArgs.NumberOfArgs;
1549  }
1550 
1551  // Skip over the sret parameter when it comes second. We already handled it
1552  // above.
1553  if (IRArgNo == 1 && SwapThisWithSRet)
1554  IRArgNo++;
1555  }
1556  assert(ArgNo == ArgInfo.size());
1557 
1558  if (FI.usesInAlloca())
1559  InallocaArgNo = IRArgNo++;
1560 
1561  TotalIRArgs = IRArgNo;
1562 }
1563 } // namespace
1564 
1565 /***/
1566 
1567 bool CodeGenModule::ReturnTypeUsesSRet(const CGFunctionInfo &FI) {
1568  const auto &RI = FI.getReturnInfo();
1569  return RI.isIndirect() || (RI.isInAlloca() && RI.getInAllocaSRet());
1570 }
1571 
1572 bool CodeGenModule::ReturnSlotInterferesWithArgs(const CGFunctionInfo &FI) {
1573  return ReturnTypeUsesSRet(FI) &&
1574  getTargetCodeGenInfo().doesReturnSlotInterfereWithArgs();
1575 }
1576 
1577 bool CodeGenModule::ReturnTypeUsesFPRet(QualType ResultType) {
1578  if (const BuiltinType *BT = ResultType->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
1579  switch (BT->getKind()) {
1580  default:
1581  return false;
1582  case BuiltinType::Float:
1583  return getTarget().useObjCFPRetForRealType(FloatModeKind::Float);
1584  case BuiltinType::Double:
1585  return getTarget().useObjCFPRetForRealType(FloatModeKind::Double);
1586  case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
1587  return getTarget().useObjCFPRetForRealType(FloatModeKind::LongDouble);
1588  }
1589  }
1590 
1591  return false;
1592 }
1593 
1594 bool CodeGenModule::ReturnTypeUsesFP2Ret(QualType ResultType) {
1595  if (const ComplexType *CT = ResultType->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
1596  if (const BuiltinType *BT = CT->getElementType()->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
1597  if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongDouble)
1598  return getTarget().useObjCFP2RetForComplexLongDouble();
1599  }
1600  }
1601 
1602  return false;
1603 }
1604 
1605 llvm::FunctionType *CodeGenTypes::GetFunctionType(GlobalDecl GD) {
1606  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
1607  return GetFunctionType(FI);
1608 }
1609 
1610 llvm::FunctionType *
1611 CodeGenTypes::GetFunctionType(const CGFunctionInfo &FI) {
1612 
1613  bool Inserted = FunctionsBeingProcessed.insert(&FI).second;
1614  (void)Inserted;
1615  assert(Inserted && "Recursively being processed?");
1616 
1617  llvm::Type *resultType = nullptr;
1618  const ABIArgInfo &retAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
1619  switch (retAI.getKind()) {
1620  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
1621  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
1622  llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
1623 
1624  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
1625  case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
1626  resultType = retAI.getCoerceToType();
1627  break;
1628 
1629  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
1630  if (retAI.getInAllocaSRet()) {
1631  // sret things on win32 aren't void, they return the sret pointer.
1632  QualType ret = FI.getReturnType();
1633  llvm::Type *ty = ConvertType(ret);
1634  unsigned addressSpace = Context.getTargetAddressSpace(ret);
1635  resultType = llvm::PointerType::get(ty, addressSpace);
1636  } else {
1637  resultType = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(getLLVMContext());
1638  }
1639  break;
1640 
1641  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
1642  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
1643  resultType = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(getLLVMContext());
1644  break;
1645 
1646  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
1647  resultType = retAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType();
1648  break;
1649  }
1650 
1651  ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(getContext(), FI, true);
1652  SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> ArgTypes(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
1653 
1654  // Add type for sret argument.
1655  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
1656  QualType Ret = FI.getReturnType();
1657  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertType(Ret);
1658  unsigned AddressSpace = Context.getTargetAddressSpace(Ret);
1659  ArgTypes[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] =
1660  llvm::PointerType::get(Ty, AddressSpace);
1661  }
1662 
1663  // Add type for inalloca argument.
1664  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
1665  auto ArgStruct = FI.getArgStruct();
1666  assert(ArgStruct);
1667  ArgTypes[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] = ArgStruct->getPointerTo();
1668  }
1669 
1670  // Add in all of the required arguments.
1671  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
1672  CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator it = FI.arg_begin(),
1673  ie = it + FI.getNumRequiredArgs();
1674  for (; it != ie; ++it, ++ArgNo) {
1675  const ABIArgInfo &ArgInfo = it->info;
1676 
1677  // Insert a padding type to ensure proper alignment.
1678  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo))
1679  ArgTypes[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
1680  ArgInfo.getPaddingType();
1681 
1682  unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
1683  std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
1684 
1685  switch (ArgInfo.getKind()) {
1686  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
1687  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
1688  assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
1689  break;
1690 
1691  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
1692  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
1693  // indirect arguments are always on the stack, which is alloca addr space.
1694  llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertTypeForMem(it->type);
1695  ArgTypes[FirstIRArg] = LTy->getPointerTo(
1696  CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace());
1697  break;
1698  }
1699  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
1700  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
1701  llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertTypeForMem(it->type);
1702  ArgTypes[FirstIRArg] = LTy->getPointerTo(ArgInfo.getIndirectAddrSpace());
1703  break;
1704  }
1705  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
1706  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
1707  // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
1708  // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
1709  llvm::Type *argType = ArgInfo.getCoerceToType();
1710  llvm::StructType *st = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(argType);
1711  if (st && ArgInfo.isDirect() && ArgInfo.getCanBeFlattened()) {
1712  assert(NumIRArgs == st->getNumElements());
1713  for (unsigned i = 0, e = st->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
1714  ArgTypes[FirstIRArg + i] = st->getElementType(i);
1715  } else {
1716  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
1717  ArgTypes[FirstIRArg] = argType;
1718  }
1719  break;
1720  }
1721 
1722  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
1723  auto ArgTypesIter = ArgTypes.begin() + FirstIRArg;
1724  for (auto EltTy : ArgInfo.getCoerceAndExpandTypeSequence()) {
1725  *ArgTypesIter++ = EltTy;
1726  }
1727  assert(ArgTypesIter == ArgTypes.begin() + FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
1728  break;
1729  }
1730 
1731  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
1732  auto ArgTypesIter = ArgTypes.begin() + FirstIRArg;
1733  getExpandedTypes(it->type, ArgTypesIter);
1734  assert(ArgTypesIter == ArgTypes.begin() + FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
1735  break;
1736  }
1737  }
1738 
1739  bool Erased = FunctionsBeingProcessed.erase(&FI); (void)Erased;
1740  assert(Erased && "Not in set?");
1741 
1742  return llvm::FunctionType::get(resultType, ArgTypes, FI.isVariadic());
1743 }
1744 
1745 llvm::Type *CodeGenTypes::GetFunctionTypeForVTable(GlobalDecl GD) {
1746  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1747  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = MD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1748 
1749  if (!isFuncTypeConvertible(FPT))
1750  return llvm::StructType::get(getLLVMContext());
1751 
1752  return GetFunctionType(GD);
1753 }
1754 
1755 static void AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(ASTContext &Ctx,
1756  llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs,
1757  const FunctionProtoType *FPT) {
1758  if (!FPT)
1759  return;
1760 
1761  if (!isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(FPT->getExceptionSpecType()) &&
1762  FPT->isNothrow())
1763  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1764 }
1765 
1766 static void AddAttributesFromAssumes(llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs,
1767  const Decl *Callee) {
1768  if (!Callee)
1769  return;
1770 
1771  SmallVector<StringRef, 4> Attrs;
1772 
1773  for (const AssumptionAttr *AA : Callee->specific_attrs<AssumptionAttr>())
1774  AA->getAssumption().split(Attrs, ",");
1775 
1776  if (!Attrs.empty())
1777  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::AssumptionAttrKey,
1778  llvm::join(Attrs.begin(), Attrs.end(), ","));
1779 }
1780 
1781 bool CodeGenModule::MayDropFunctionReturn(const ASTContext &Context,
1782  QualType ReturnType) {
1783  // We can't just discard the return value for a record type with a
1784  // complex destructor or a non-trivially copyable type.
1785  if (const RecordType *RT =
1786  ReturnType.getCanonicalType()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1787  if (const auto *ClassDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
1788  return ClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor();
1789  }
1790  return ReturnType.isTriviallyCopyableType(Context);
1791 }
1792 
1793 void CodeGenModule::getDefaultFunctionAttributes(StringRef Name,
1794  bool HasOptnone,
1795  bool AttrOnCallSite,
1796  llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs) {
1797  // OptimizeNoneAttr takes precedence over -Os or -Oz. No warning needed.
1798  if (!HasOptnone) {
1799  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize)
1800  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
1801  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize == 2)
1802  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
1803  }
1804 
1805  if (CodeGenOpts.DisableRedZone)
1806  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoRedZone);
1807  if (CodeGenOpts.IndirectTlsSegRefs)
1808  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("indirect-tls-seg-refs");
1809  if (CodeGenOpts.NoImplicitFloat)
1810  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoImplicitFloat);
1811 
1812  if (AttrOnCallSite) {
1813  // Attributes that should go on the call site only.
1814  if (!CodeGenOpts.SimplifyLibCalls || LangOpts.isNoBuiltinFunc(Name))
1815  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
1816  if (!CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName.empty())
1817  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("trap-func-name", CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName);
1818  } else {
1819  StringRef FpKind;
1820  switch (CodeGenOpts.getFramePointer()) {
1821  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::None:
1822  FpKind = "none";
1823  break;
1824  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf:
1825  FpKind = "non-leaf";
1826  break;
1827  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::All:
1828  FpKind = "all";
1829  break;
1830  }
1831  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("frame-pointer", FpKind);
1832 
1833  if (CodeGenOpts.LessPreciseFPMAD)
1834  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("less-precise-fpmad", "true");
1835 
1836  if (CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
1837  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NullPointerIsValid);
1838 
1839  if (CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode != llvm::DenormalMode::getIEEE())
1840  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("denormal-fp-math",
1841  CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode.str());
1842  if (CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode != CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode) {
1843  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(
1844  "denormal-fp-math-f32",
1845  CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode.str());
1846  }
1847 
1848  if (LangOpts.getFPExceptionMode() == LangOptions::FPE_Ignore)
1849  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-trapping-math", "true");
1850 
1851  // TODO: Are these all needed?
1852  // unsafe/inf/nan/nsz are handled by instruction-level FastMathFlags.
1853  if (LangOpts.NoHonorInfs)
1854  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-infs-fp-math", "true");
1855  if (LangOpts.NoHonorNaNs)
1856  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-nans-fp-math", "true");
1857  if (LangOpts.ApproxFunc)
1858  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("approx-func-fp-math", "true");
1859  if (LangOpts.UnsafeFPMath)
1860  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("unsafe-fp-math", "true");
1861  if (CodeGenOpts.SoftFloat)
1862  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("use-soft-float", "true");
1863  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stack-protector-buffer-size",
1864  llvm::utostr(CodeGenOpts.SSPBufferSize));
1865  if (LangOpts.NoSignedZero)
1866  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-signed-zeros-fp-math", "true");
1867 
1868  // TODO: Reciprocal estimate codegen options should apply to instructions?
1869  const std::vector<std::string> &Recips = CodeGenOpts.Reciprocals;
1870  if (!Recips.empty())
1871  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("reciprocal-estimates",
1872  llvm::join(Recips, ","));
1873 
1874  if (!CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth.empty() &&
1875  CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth != "none")
1876  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("prefer-vector-width",
1877  CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth);
1878 
1879  if (CodeGenOpts.StackRealignment)
1880  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stackrealign");
1881  if (CodeGenOpts.Backchain)
1882  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("backchain");
1883  if (CodeGenOpts.EnableSegmentedStacks)
1884  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("split-stack");
1885 
1886  if (CodeGenOpts.SpeculativeLoadHardening)
1887  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
1888 
1889  // Add zero-call-used-regs attribute.
1890  switch (CodeGenOpts.getZeroCallUsedRegs()) {
1891  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::Skip:
1892  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute("zero-call-used-regs");
1893  break;
1894  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::UsedGPRArg:
1895  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "used-gpr-arg");
1896  break;
1897  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::UsedGPR:
1898  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "used-gpr");
1899  break;
1900  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::UsedArg:
1901  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "used-arg");
1902  break;
1903  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::Used:
1904  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "used");
1905  break;
1906  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::AllGPRArg:
1907  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "all-gpr-arg");
1908  break;
1909  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::AllGPR:
1910  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "all-gpr");
1911  break;
1912  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::AllArg:
1913  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "all-arg");
1914  break;
1915  case llvm::ZeroCallUsedRegs::ZeroCallUsedRegsKind::All:
1916  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("zero-call-used-regs", "all");
1917  break;
1918  }
1919  }
1920 
1921  if (getLangOpts().assumeFunctionsAreConvergent()) {
1922  // Conservatively, mark all functions and calls in CUDA and OpenCL as
1923  // convergent (meaning, they may call an intrinsically convergent op, such
1924  // as __syncthreads() / barrier(), and so can't have certain optimizations
1925  // applied around them). LLVM will remove this attribute where it safely
1926  // can.
1927  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
1928  }
1929 
1930  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1931  // Exceptions aren't supported in CUDA device code.
1932  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1933  }
1934 
1935  for (StringRef Attr : CodeGenOpts.DefaultFunctionAttrs) {
1936  StringRef Var, Value;
1937  std::tie(Var, Value) = Attr.split('=');
1938  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(Var, Value);
1939  }
1940 }
1941 
1942 void CodeGenModule::addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes(llvm::Function &F) {
1943  llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs(F.getContext());
1944  getDefaultFunctionAttributes(F.getName(), F.hasOptNone(),
1945  /* AttrOnCallSite = */ false, FuncAttrs);
1946  // TODO: call GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes?
1947  F.addFnAttrs(FuncAttrs);
1948 }
1949 
1950 void CodeGenModule::addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes(
1951  llvm::AttrBuilder &attrs) {
1952  getDefaultFunctionAttributes(/*function name*/ "", /*optnone*/ false,
1953  /*for call*/ false, attrs);
1954  GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GlobalDecl(), attrs);
1955 }
1956 
1957 static void addNoBuiltinAttributes(llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs,
1958  const LangOptions &LangOpts,
1959  const NoBuiltinAttr *NBA = nullptr) {
1960  auto AddNoBuiltinAttr = [&FuncAttrs](StringRef BuiltinName) {
1961  SmallString<32> AttributeName;
1962  AttributeName += "no-builtin-";
1963  AttributeName += BuiltinName;
1964  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(AttributeName);
1965  };
1966 
1967  // First, handle the language options passed through -fno-builtin.
1968  if (LangOpts.NoBuiltin) {
1969  // -fno-builtin disables them all.
1970  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-builtins");
1971  return;
1972  }
1973 
1974  // Then, add attributes for builtins specified through -fno-builtin-<name>.
1975  llvm::for_each(LangOpts.NoBuiltinFuncs, AddNoBuiltinAttr);
1976 
1977  // Now, let's check the __attribute__((no_builtin("...")) attribute added to
1978  // the source.
1979  if (!NBA)
1980  return;
1981 
1982  // If there is a wildcard in the builtin names specified through the
1983  // attribute, disable them all.
1984  if (llvm::is_contained(NBA->builtinNames(), "*")) {
1985  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-builtins");
1986  return;
1987  }
1988 
1989  // And last, add the rest of the builtin names.
1990  llvm::for_each(NBA->builtinNames(), AddNoBuiltinAttr);
1991 }
1992 
1993 static bool DetermineNoUndef(QualType QTy, CodeGenTypes &Types,
1994  const llvm::DataLayout &DL, const ABIArgInfo &AI,
1995  bool CheckCoerce = true) {
1996  llvm::Type *Ty = Types.ConvertTypeForMem(QTy);
1997  if (AI.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Indirect)
1998  return true;
1999  if (AI.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Extend)
2000  return true;
2001  if (!DL.typeSizeEqualsStoreSize(Ty))
2002  // TODO: This will result in a modest amount of values not marked noundef
2003  // when they could be. We care about values that *invisibly* contain undef
2004  // bits from the perspective of LLVM IR.
2005  return false;
2006  if (CheckCoerce && AI.canHaveCoerceToType()) {
2007  llvm::Type *CoerceTy = AI.getCoerceToType();
2008  if (llvm::TypeSize::isKnownGT(DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CoerceTy),
2009  DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Ty)))
2010  // If we're coercing to a type with a greater size than the canonical one,
2011  // we're introducing new undef bits.
2012  // Coercing to a type of smaller or equal size is ok, as we know that
2013  // there's no internal padding (typeSizeEqualsStoreSize).
2014  return false;
2015  }
2016  if (QTy->isBitIntType())
2017  return true;
2018  if (QTy->isReferenceType())
2019  return true;
2020  if (QTy->isNullPtrType())
2021  return false;
2022  if (QTy->isMemberPointerType())
2023  // TODO: Some member pointers are `noundef`, but it depends on the ABI. For
2024  // now, never mark them.
2025  return false;
2026  if (QTy->isScalarType()) {
2027  if (const ComplexType *Complex = dyn_cast<ComplexType>(QTy))
2028  return DetermineNoUndef(Complex->getElementType(), Types, DL, AI, false);
2029  return true;
2030  }
2031  if (const VectorType *Vector = dyn_cast<VectorType>(QTy))
2032  return DetermineNoUndef(Vector->getElementType(), Types, DL, AI, false);
2033  if (const MatrixType *Matrix = dyn_cast<MatrixType>(QTy))
2034  return DetermineNoUndef(Matrix->getElementType(), Types, DL, AI, false);
2035  if (const ArrayType *Array = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(QTy))
2036  return DetermineNoUndef(Array->getElementType(), Types, DL, AI, false);
2037 
2038  // TODO: Some structs may be `noundef`, in specific situations.
2039  return false;
2040 }
2041 
2042 /// Construct the IR attribute list of a function or call.
2043 ///
2044 /// When adding an attribute, please consider where it should be handled:
2045 ///
2046 /// - getDefaultFunctionAttributes is for attributes that are essentially
2047 /// part of the global target configuration (but perhaps can be
2048 /// overridden on a per-function basis). Adding attributes there
2049 /// will cause them to also be set in frontends that build on Clang's
2050 /// target-configuration logic, as well as for code defined in library
2051 /// modules such as CUDA's libdevice.
2052 ///
2053 /// - ConstructAttributeList builds on top of getDefaultFunctionAttributes
2054 /// and adds declaration-specific, convention-specific, and
2055 /// frontend-specific logic. The last is of particular importance:
2056 /// attributes that restrict how the frontend generates code must be
2057 /// added here rather than getDefaultFunctionAttributes.
2058 ///
2059 void CodeGenModule::ConstructAttributeList(StringRef Name,
2060  const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
2061  CGCalleeInfo CalleeInfo,
2062  llvm::AttributeList &AttrList,
2063  unsigned &CallingConv,
2064  bool AttrOnCallSite, bool IsThunk) {
2065  llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs(getLLVMContext());
2066  llvm::AttrBuilder RetAttrs(getLLVMContext());
2067 
2068  // Collect function IR attributes from the CC lowering.
2069  // We'll collect the paramete and result attributes later.
2070  CallingConv = FI.getEffectiveCallingConvention();
2071  if (FI.isNoReturn())
2072  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
2073  if (FI.isCmseNSCall())
2074  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("cmse_nonsecure_call");
2075 
2076  // Collect function IR attributes from the callee prototype if we have one.
