2077  AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(getContext(), FuncAttrs,
2078  CalleeInfo.getCalleeFunctionProtoType());
2079 
2080  const Decl *TargetDecl = CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
2081 
2082  // Attach assumption attributes to the declaration. If this is a call
2083  // site, attach assumptions from the caller to the call as well.
2084  AddAttributesFromAssumes(FuncAttrs, TargetDecl);
2085 
2086  bool HasOptnone = false;
2087  // The NoBuiltinAttr attached to the target FunctionDecl.
2088  const NoBuiltinAttr *NBA = nullptr;
2089 
2090  // Collect function IR attributes based on declaration-specific
2091  // information.
2092  // FIXME: handle sseregparm someday...
2093  if (TargetDecl) {
2094  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsTwiceAttr>())
2095  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReturnsTwice);
2096  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoThrowAttr>())
2097  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2098  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoReturnAttr>())
2099  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
2100  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ColdAttr>())
2101  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Cold);
2102  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<HotAttr>())
2103  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Hot);
2104  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoDuplicateAttr>())
2105  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoDuplicate);
2106  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConvergentAttr>())
2107  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
2108 
2109  if (const FunctionDecl *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
2110  AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(
2111  getContext(), FuncAttrs, Fn->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>());
2112  if (AttrOnCallSite && Fn->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
2113  // A sane operator new returns a non-aliasing pointer.
2114  auto Kind = Fn->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator();
2115  if (getCodeGenOpts().AssumeSaneOperatorNew &&
2116  (Kind == OO_New || Kind == OO_Array_New))
2117  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2118  }
2119  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn);
2120  const bool IsVirtualCall = MD && MD->isVirtual();
2121  // Don't use [[noreturn]], _Noreturn or [[no_builtin]] for a call to a
2122  // virtual function. These attributes are not inherited by overloads.
2123  if (!(AttrOnCallSite && IsVirtualCall)) {
2124  if (Fn->isNoReturn())
2125  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
2126  NBA = Fn->getAttr<NoBuiltinAttr>();
2127  }
2128  // Only place nomerge attribute on call sites, never functions. This
2129  // allows it to work on indirect virtual function calls.
2130  if (AttrOnCallSite && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoMergeAttr>())
2131  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoMerge);
2132  }
2133 
2134  // 'const', 'pure' and 'noalias' attributed functions are also nounwind.
2135  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConstAttr>()) {
2136  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2137  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2138  // gcc specifies that 'const' functions have greater restrictions than
2139  // 'pure' functions, so they also cannot have infinite loops.
2140  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::WillReturn);
2141  } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<PureAttr>()) {
2142  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly);
2143  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2144  // gcc specifies that 'pure' functions cannot have infinite loops.
2145  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::WillReturn);
2146  } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoAliasAttr>()) {
2147  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ArgMemOnly);
2148  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2149  }
2150  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<RestrictAttr>())
2151  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2152  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>() &&
2153  !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2154  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2155  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegistersAttr>())
2156  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no_caller_saved_registers");
2157  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCfCheckAttr>())
2158  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCfCheck);
2159  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<LeafAttr>())
2160  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCallback);
2161 
2162  HasOptnone = TargetDecl->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>();
2163  if (auto *AllocSize = TargetDecl->getAttr<AllocSizeAttr>()) {
2164  Optional<unsigned> NumElemsParam;
2165  if (AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().isValid())
2166  NumElemsParam = AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().getLLVMIndex();
2167  FuncAttrs.addAllocSizeAttr(AllocSize->getElemSizeParam().getLLVMIndex(),
2168  NumElemsParam);
2169  }
2170 
2171  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
2172  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion <= 120) {
2173  // OpenCL v1.2 Work groups are always uniform
2174  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size", "true");
2175  } else {
2176  // OpenCL v2.0 Work groups may be whether uniform or not.
2177  // '-cl-uniform-work-group-size' compile option gets a hint
2178  // to the compiler that the global work-size be a multiple of
2179  // the work-group size specified to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel
2180  // (i.e. work groups are uniform).
2181  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size",
2182  llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.UniformWGSize));
2183  }
2184  }
2185  }
2186 
2187  // Attach "no-builtins" attributes to:
2188  // * call sites: both `nobuiltin` and "no-builtins" or "no-builtin-<name>".
2189  // * definitions: "no-builtins" or "no-builtin-<name>" only.
2190  // The attributes can come from:
2191  // * LangOpts: -ffreestanding, -fno-builtin, -fno-builtin-<name>
2192  // * FunctionDecl attributes: __attribute__((no_builtin(...)))
2193  addNoBuiltinAttributes(FuncAttrs, getLangOpts(), NBA);
2194 
2195  // Collect function IR attributes based on global settiings.
2196  getDefaultFunctionAttributes(Name, HasOptnone, AttrOnCallSite, FuncAttrs);
2197 
2198  // Override some default IR attributes based on declaration-specific
2199  // information.
2200  if (TargetDecl) {
2201  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
2202  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
2203  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<SpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
2204  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
2205  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSplitStackAttr>())
2206  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute("split-stack");
2207  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ZeroCallUsedRegsAttr>()) {
2208  // A function "__attribute__((...))" overrides the command-line flag.
2209  auto Kind =
2210  TargetDecl->getAttr<ZeroCallUsedRegsAttr>()->getZeroCallUsedRegs();
2211  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute("zero-call-used-regs");
2212  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(
2213  "zero-call-used-regs",
2214  ZeroCallUsedRegsAttr::ConvertZeroCallUsedRegsKindToStr(Kind));
2215  }
2216 
2217  // Add NonLazyBind attribute to function declarations when -fno-plt
2218  // is used.
2219  // FIXME: what if we just haven't processed the function definition
2220  // yet, or if it's an external definition like C99 inline?
2221  if (CodeGenOpts.NoPLT) {
2222  if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
2223  if (!Fn->isDefined() && !AttrOnCallSite) {
2224  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind);
2225  }
2226  }
2227  }
2228  }
2229 
2230  // Add "sample-profile-suffix-elision-policy" attribute for internal linkage
2231  // functions with -funique-internal-linkage-names.
2232  if (TargetDecl && CodeGenOpts.UniqueInternalLinkageNames) {
2233  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
2234  if (this->getFunctionLinkage(CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl()) ==
2235  llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage)
2236  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("sample-profile-suffix-elision-policy",
2237  "selected");
2238  }
2239  }
2240 
2241  // Collect non-call-site function IR attributes from declaration-specific
2242  // information.
2243  if (!AttrOnCallSite) {
2244  if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<CmseNSEntryAttr>())
2245  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("cmse_nonsecure_entry");
2246 
2247  // Whether tail calls are enabled.
2248  auto shouldDisableTailCalls = [&] {
2249  // Should this be honored in getDefaultFunctionAttributes?
2250  if (CodeGenOpts.DisableTailCalls)
2251  return true;
2252 
2253  if (!TargetDecl)
2254  return false;
2255 
2256  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<DisableTailCallsAttr>() ||
2257  TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86InterruptAttr>())
2258  return true;
2259 
2260  if (CodeGenOpts.NoEscapingBlockTailCalls) {
2261  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(TargetDecl))
2262  if (!BD->doesNotEscape())
2263  return true;
2264  }
2265 
2266  return false;
2267  };
2268  if (shouldDisableTailCalls())
2269  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("disable-tail-calls", "true");
2270 
2271  // CPU/feature overrides. addDefaultFunctionDefinitionAttributes
2272  // handles these separately to set them based on the global defaults.
2273  GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl(), FuncAttrs);
2274  }
2275 
2276  // Collect attributes from arguments and return values.
2277  ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(getContext(), FI);
2278 
2279  QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
2280  const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
2281  const llvm::DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
2282 
2283  // C++ explicitly makes returning undefined values UB. C's rule only applies
2284  // to used values, so we never mark them noundef for now.
2285  bool HasStrictReturn = getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
2286  if (TargetDecl && HasStrictReturn) {
2287  if (const FunctionDecl *FDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))
2288  HasStrictReturn &= !FDecl->isExternC();
2289  else if (const VarDecl *VDecl = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(TargetDecl))
2290  // Function pointer
2291  HasStrictReturn &= !VDecl->isExternC();
2292  }
2293 
2294  // We don't want to be too aggressive with the return checking, unless
2295  // it's explicit in the code opts or we're using an appropriate sanitizer.
2296  // Try to respect what the programmer intended.
2297  HasStrictReturn &= getCodeGenOpts().StrictReturn ||
2298  !MayDropFunctionReturn(getContext(), RetTy) ||
2299  getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) ||
2300  getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Return);
2301 
2302  // Determine if the return type could be partially undef
2303  if (CodeGenOpts.EnableNoundefAttrs && HasStrictReturn) {
2304  if (!RetTy->isVoidType() && RetAI.getKind() != ABIArgInfo::Indirect &&
2305  DetermineNoUndef(RetTy, getTypes(), DL, RetAI))
2306  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUndef);
2307  }
2308 
2309  switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
2310  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2311  if (RetAI.isSignExt())
2312  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2313  else
2314  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2315  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2316  case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2317  if (RetAI.getInReg())
2318  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2319  break;
2320  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2321  break;
2322 
2323  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2324  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2325  // inalloca and sret disable readnone and readonly
2326  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2327  .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2328  break;
2329  }
2330 
2331  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2332  break;
2333 
2334  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2335  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
2336  llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
2337  }
2338 
2339  if (!IsThunk) {
2340  // FIXME: fix this properly, https://reviews.llvm.org/D100388
2341  if (const auto *RefTy = RetTy->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2342  QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2343  if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2344  RetAttrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2345  getMinimumObjectSize(PTy).getQuantity());
2346  if (getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(PTy) == 0 &&
2347  !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2348  RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2349  if (PTy->isObjectType()) {
2350  llvm::Align Alignment =
2351  getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(RetTy).getAsAlign();
2352  RetAttrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2353  }
2354  }
2355  }
2356 
2357  bool hasUsedSRet = false;
2358  SmallVector<llvm::AttributeSet, 4> ArgAttrs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2359 
2360  // Attach attributes to sret.
2361  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2362  llvm::AttrBuilder SRETAttrs(getLLVMContext());
2363  SRETAttrs.addStructRetAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(RetTy));
2364  hasUsedSRet = true;
2365  if (RetAI.getInReg())
2366  SRETAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2367  SRETAttrs.addAlignmentAttr(RetAI.getIndirectAlign().getQuantity());
2368  ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] =
2369  llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), SRETAttrs);
2370  }
2371 
2372  // Attach attributes to inalloca argument.
2373  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2374  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(getLLVMContext());
2375  Attrs.addInAllocaAttr(FI.getArgStruct());
2376  ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] =
2377  llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2378  }
2379 
2380  // Apply `nonnull`, `dereferencable(N)` and `align N` to the `this` argument,
2381  // unless this is a thunk function.
2382  // FIXME: fix this properly, https://reviews.llvm.org/D100388
2383  if (FI.isInstanceMethod() && !IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg() &&
2384  !FI.arg_begin()->type->isVoidPointerType() && !IsThunk) {
2385  auto IRArgs = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(0);
2386 
2387  assert(IRArgs.second == 1 && "Expected only a single `this` pointer.");
2388 
2389  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(getLLVMContext());
2390 
2391  QualType ThisTy =
2392  FI.arg_begin()->type.castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2393 
2394  if (!CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid &&
2395  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(FI.arg_begin()->type) == 0) {
2396  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2397  Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(getMinimumObjectSize(ThisTy).getQuantity());
2398  } else {
2399  // FIXME dereferenceable should be correct here, regardless of
2400  // NullPointerIsValid. However, dereferenceable currently does not always
2401  // respect NullPointerIsValid and may imply nonnull and break the program.
2402  // See https://reviews.llvm.org/D66618 for discussions.
2403  Attrs.addDereferenceableOrNullAttr(
2404  getMinimumObjectSize(
2405  FI.arg_begin()->type.castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType())
2406  .getQuantity());
2407  }
2408 
2409  llvm::Align Alignment =
2410  getNaturalTypeAlignment(ThisTy, /*BaseInfo=*/nullptr,
2411  /*TBAAInfo=*/nullptr, /*forPointeeType=*/true)
2412  .getAsAlign();
2413  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2414 
2415  ArgAttrs[IRArgs.first] = llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2416  }
2417 
2418  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2419  for (CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator I = FI.arg_begin(),
2420  E = FI.arg_end();
2421  I != E; ++I, ++ArgNo) {
2422  QualType ParamType = I->type;
2423  const ABIArgInfo &AI = I->info;
2424  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(getLLVMContext());
2425 
2426  // Add attribute for padding argument, if necessary.
2427  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo)) {
2428  if (AI.getPaddingInReg()) {
2429  ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
2430  llvm::AttributeSet::get(
2431  getLLVMContext(),
2432  llvm::AttrBuilder(getLLVMContext()).addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg));
2433  }
2434  }
2435 
2436  // Decide whether the argument we're handling could be partially undef
2437  if (CodeGenOpts.EnableNoundefAttrs &&
2438  DetermineNoUndef(ParamType, getTypes(), DL, AI)) {
2439  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUndef);
2440  }
2441 
2442  // 'restrict' -> 'noalias' is done in EmitFunctionProlog when we
2443  // have the corresponding parameter variable. It doesn't make
2444  // sense to do it here because parameters are so messed up.
2445  switch (AI.getKind()) {
2446  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2447  if (AI.isSignExt())
2448  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2449  else
2450  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2451  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2452  case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2453  if (ArgNo == 0 && FI.isChainCall())
2454  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Nest);
2455  else if (AI.getInReg())
2456  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2457  Attrs.addStackAlignmentAttr(llvm::MaybeAlign(AI.getDirectAlign()));
2458  break;
2459 
2460  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2461  if (AI.getInReg())
2462  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2463 
2464  if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2465  Attrs.addByValAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2466 
2467  auto *Decl = ParamType->getAsRecordDecl();
2468  if (CodeGenOpts.PassByValueIsNoAlias && Decl &&
2469  Decl->getArgPassingRestrictions() == RecordDecl::APK_CanPassInRegs)
2470  // When calling the function, the pointer passed in will be the only
2471  // reference to the underlying object. Mark it accordingly.
2472  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2473 
2474  // TODO: We could add the byref attribute if not byval, but it would
2475  // require updating many testcases.
2476 
2477  CharUnits Align = AI.getIndirectAlign();
2478 
2479  // In a byval argument, it is important that the required
2480  // alignment of the type is honored, as LLVM might be creating a
2481  // *new* stack object, and needs to know what alignment to give
2482  // it. (Sometimes it can deduce a sensible alignment on its own,
2483  // but not if clang decides it must emit a packed struct, or the
2484  // user specifies increased alignment requirements.)
2485  //
2486  // This is different from indirect *not* byval, where the object
2487  // exists already, and the align attribute is purely
2488  // informative.
2489  assert(!Align.isZero());
2490 
2491  // For now, only add this when we have a byval argument.
2492  // TODO: be less lazy about updating test cases.
2493  if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2494  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Align.getQuantity());
2495 
2496  // byval disables readnone and readonly.
2497  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2498  .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2499 
2500  break;
2501  }
2502  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
2503  CharUnits Align = AI.getIndirectAlign();
2504  Attrs.addByRefAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2505  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Align.getQuantity());
2506  break;
2507  }
2508  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2509  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2510  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2511  break;
2512 
2513  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2514  // inalloca disables readnone and readonly.
2515  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2516  .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2517  continue;
2518  }
2519 
2520  if (const auto *RefTy = ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2521  QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2522  if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2523  Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2524  getMinimumObjectSize(PTy).getQuantity());
2525  if (getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(PTy) == 0 &&
2526  !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2527  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2528  if (PTy->isObjectType()) {
2529  llvm::Align Alignment =
2530  getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(ParamType).getAsAlign();
2531  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2532  }
2533  }
2534 
2535  // From OpenCL spec v3.0.10 section 6.3.5 Alignment of Types:
2536  // > For arguments to a __kernel function declared to be a pointer to a
2537  // > data type, the OpenCL compiler can assume that the pointee is always
2538  // > appropriately aligned as required by the data type.
2539  if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>() &&
2540  ParamType->isPointerType()) {
2541  QualType PTy = ParamType->getPointeeType();
2542  if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType()) {
2543  llvm::Align Alignment =
2544  getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(ParamType).getAsAlign();
2545  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Alignment);
2546  }
2547  }
2548 
2549  switch (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()) {
2550  case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2551  break;
2552 
2553  case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult: {
2554  // Add 'sret' if we haven't already used it for something, but
2555  // only if the result is void.
2556  if (!hasUsedSRet && RetTy->isVoidType()) {
2557  Attrs.addStructRetAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2558  hasUsedSRet = true;
2559  }
2560 
2561  // Add 'noalias' in either case.
2562  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2563 
2564  // Add 'dereferenceable' and 'alignment'.
2565  auto PTy = ParamType->getPointeeType();
2566  if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType()) {
2567  auto info = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(PTy);
2568  Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(info.Width.getQuantity());
2569  Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(info.Align.getAsAlign());
2570  }
2571  break;
2572  }
2573 
2574  case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2575  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftError);
2576  break;
2577 
2578  case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2579  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftSelf);
2580  break;
2581 
2582  case ParameterABI::SwiftAsyncContext:
2583  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftAsync);
2584  break;
2585  }
2586 
2587  if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).isNoEscape())
2588  Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCapture);
2589 
2590  if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) {
2591  unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2592  std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2593  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumIRArgs; i++)
2594  ArgAttrs[FirstIRArg + i] = ArgAttrs[FirstIRArg + i].addAttributes(
2595  getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs));
2596  }
2597  }
2598  assert(ArgNo == FI.arg_size());
2599 
2600  AttrList = llvm::AttributeList::get(
2601  getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), FuncAttrs),
2602  llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), RetAttrs), ArgAttrs);
2603 }
2604 
2605 /// An argument came in as a promoted argument; demote it back to its
2606 /// declared type.
2607 static llvm::Value *emitArgumentDemotion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2608  const VarDecl *var,
2609  llvm::Value *value) {
2610  llvm::Type *varType = CGF.ConvertType(var->getType());
2611 
2612  // This can happen with promotions that actually don't change the
2613  // underlying type, like the enum promotions.
2614  if (value->getType() == varType) return value;
2615 
2616  assert((varType->isIntegerTy() || varType->isFloatingPointTy())
2617  && "unexpected promotion type");
2618 
2619  if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(varType))
2620  return CGF.Builder.CreateTrunc(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2621 
2622  return CGF.Builder.CreateFPCast(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2623 }
2624 
2625 /// Returns the attribute (either parameter attribute, or function
2626 /// attribute), which declares argument ArgNo to be non-null.
2627 static const NonNullAttr *getNonNullAttr(const Decl *FD, const ParmVarDecl *PVD,
2628  QualType ArgType, unsigned ArgNo) {
2629  // FIXME: __attribute__((nonnull)) can also be applied to:
2630  // - references to pointers, where the pointee is known to be
2631  // nonnull (apparently a Clang extension)
2632  // - transparent unions containing pointers
2633  // In the former case, LLVM IR cannot represent the constraint. In
2634  // the latter case, we have no guarantee that the transparent union
2635  // is in fact passed as a pointer.
2636  if (!ArgType->isAnyPointerType() && !ArgType->isBlockPointerType())
2637  return nullptr;
2638  // First, check attribute on parameter itself.
2639  if (PVD) {
2640  if (auto ParmNNAttr = PVD->getAttr<NonNullAttr>())
2641  return ParmNNAttr;
2642  }
2643  // Check function attributes.
2644  if (!FD)
2645  return nullptr;
2646  for (const auto *NNAttr : FD->specific_attrs<NonNullAttr>()) {
2647  if (NNAttr->isNonNull(ArgNo))
2648  return NNAttr;
2649  }
2650  return nullptr;
2651 }
2652 
2653 namespace {
2654  struct CopyBackSwiftError final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
2655  Address Temp;
2656  Address Arg;
2657  CopyBackSwiftError(Address temp, Address arg) : Temp(temp), Arg(arg) {}
2658  void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
2659  llvm::Value *errorValue = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Temp);
2660  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, Arg);
2661  }
2662  };
2663 }
2664 
2665 void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionProlog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
2666  llvm::Function *Fn,
2667  const FunctionArgList &Args) {
2668  if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
2669  // Naked functions don't have prologues.
2670  return;
2671 
2672  // If this is an implicit-return-zero function, go ahead and
2673  // initialize the return value. TODO: it might be nice to have
2674  // a more general mechanism for this that didn't require synthesized
2675  // return statements.
2676  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
2677  if (FD->hasImplicitReturnZero()) {
2678  QualType RetTy = FD->getReturnType().getUnqualifiedType();
2679  llvm::Type* LLVMTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(RetTy);
2680  llvm::Constant* Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LLVMTy);
2681  Builder.CreateStore(Zero, ReturnValue);
2682  }
2683  }
2684 
2685  // FIXME: We no longer need the types from FunctionArgList; lift up and
2686  // simplify.
2687 
2688  ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), FI);
2689  assert(Fn->arg_size() == IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2690 
2691  // If we're using inalloca, all the memory arguments are GEPs off of the last
2692  // parameter, which is a pointer to the complete memory area.
2693  Address ArgStruct = Address::invalid();
2694  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2695  ArgStruct = Address(Fn->getArg(IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()),
2696  FI.getArgStruct(), FI.getArgStructAlignment());
2697 
2698  assert(ArgStruct.getType() == FI.getArgStruct()->getPointerTo());
2699  }
2700 
2701  // Name the struct return parameter.
2702  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2703  auto AI = Fn->getArg(IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo());
2704  AI->setName("agg.result");
2705  AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2706  }
2707 
2708  // Track if we received the parameter as a pointer (indirect, byval, or
2709  // inalloca). If already have a pointer, EmitParmDecl doesn't need to copy it
2710  // into a local alloca for us.
2711  SmallVector<ParamValue, 16> ArgVals;
2712  ArgVals.reserve(Args.size());
2713 
2714  // Create a pointer value for every parameter declaration. This usually
2715  // entails copying one or more LLVM IR arguments into an alloca. Don't push
2716  // any cleanups or do anything that might unwind. We do that separately, so
2717  // we can push the cleanups in the correct order for the ABI.
2718  assert(FI.arg_size() == Args.size() &&
2719  "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
2720  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2721  CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = FI.arg_begin();
2722  for (FunctionArgList::const_iterator i = Args.begin(), e = Args.end();
2723  i != e; ++i, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
2724  const VarDecl *Arg = *i;
2725  const ABIArgInfo &ArgI = info_it->info;
2726 
2727  bool isPromoted =
2728  isa<ParmVarDecl>(Arg) && cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)->isKNRPromoted();
2729  // We are converting from ABIArgInfo type to VarDecl type directly, unless
2730  // the parameter is promoted. In this case we convert to
2731  // CGFunctionInfo::ArgInfo type with subsequent argument demotion.
2732  QualType Ty = isPromoted ? info_it->type : Arg->getType();
2733  assert(hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty) ==
2734  hasScalarEvaluationKind(Arg->getType()));
2735 
2736  unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2737  std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2738 
2739  if (Arg->hasAttr<SYCLAccessorReadonlyAttr>())
2740  Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg)->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly);
2741 
2742  if (const auto *AddIRAttr =
2743  Arg->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameterAttr>()) {
2744  SmallVector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, 4> NameValuePairs =
2745  AddIRAttr->getFilteredAttributeNameValuePairs(CGM.getContext());
2746 
2747  llvm::AttrBuilder KernelParamAttrBuilder(Fn->getContext());
2748  for (const auto &NameValuePair : NameValuePairs)
2749  KernelParamAttrBuilder.addAttribute(NameValuePair.first,
2750  NameValuePair.second);
2751  Fn->addParamAttrs(ArgNo, KernelParamAttrBuilder);
2752  }
2753 
2754  switch (ArgI.getKind()) {
2755  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
2756  assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
2757  auto FieldIndex = ArgI.getInAllocaFieldIndex();
2758  Address V =
2759  Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgStruct, FieldIndex, Arg->getName());
2760  if (ArgI.getInAllocaIndirect())
2761  V = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(V), ConvertTypeForMem(Ty),
2762  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty));
2763  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2764  break;
2765  }
2766 
2767  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
2768  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
2769  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2770  Address ParamAddr = Address(Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg), ConvertTypeForMem(Ty),
2771  ArgI.getIndirectAlign());
2772 
2773  if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2774  // Aggregates and complex variables are accessed by reference. All we
2775  // need to do is realign the value, if requested. Also, if the address
2776  // may be aliased, copy it to ensure that the parameter variable is
2777  // mutable and has a unique adress, as C requires.
2778  Address V = ParamAddr;
2779  if (ArgI.getIndirectRealign() || ArgI.isIndirectAliased()) {
2780  Address AlignedTemp = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "coerce");
2781 
2782  // Copy from the incoming argument pointer to the temporary with the
2783  // appropriate alignment.
2784  //
2785  // FIXME: We should have a common utility for generating an aggregate
2786  // copy.
2787  CharUnits Size = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
2788  Builder.CreateMemCpy(
2789  AlignedTemp.getPointer(), AlignedTemp.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
2790  ParamAddr.getPointer(), ParamAddr.getAlignment().getAsAlign(),
2791  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, Size.getQuantity()));
2792  V = AlignedTemp;
2793  }
2794  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2795  } else {
2796  // Load scalar value from indirect argument.
2797  llvm::Value *V =
2798  EmitLoadOfScalar(ParamAddr, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
2799 
2800  if (isPromoted)
2801  V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2802  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2803  }
2804  break;
2805  }
2806 
2807  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2808  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
2809  auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
2810  llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertType(Arg->getType());
2811 
2812  // Prepare parameter attributes. So far, only attributes for pointer
2813  // parameters are prepared. See
2814  // http://llvm.org/docs/LangRef.html#paramattrs.
2815  if (ArgI.getDirectOffset() == 0 && LTy->isPointerTy() &&
2816  ArgI.getCoerceToType()->isPointerTy()) {
2817  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2818 
2819  if (const ParmVarDecl *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)) {
2820  // Set `nonnull` attribute if any.
2821  if (getNonNullAttr(CurCodeDecl, PVD, PVD->getType(),
2822  PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex()) &&
2823  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2824  AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2825 
2826  QualType OTy = PVD->getOriginalType();
2827  if (const auto *ArrTy =
2828  getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(OTy)) {
2829  // A C99 array parameter declaration with the static keyword also
2830  // indicates dereferenceability, and if the size is constant we can
2831  // use the dereferenceable attribute (which requires the size in
2832  // bytes).
2833  if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == ArrayType::Static) {
2834  QualType ETy = ArrTy->getElementType();
2835  llvm::Align Alignment =
2836  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ETy).getAsAlign();
2837  AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder(getLLVMContext()).addAlignmentAttr(Alignment));
2838  uint64_t ArrSize = ArrTy->getSize().getZExtValue();
2839  if (!ETy->isIncompleteType() && ETy->isConstantSizeType() &&
2840  ArrSize) {
2841  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(getLLVMContext());
2842  Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2843  getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ETy).getQuantity() *
2844  ArrSize);
2845  AI->addAttrs(Attrs);
2846  } else if (getContext().getTargetInfo().getNullPointerValue(
2847  ETy.getAddressSpace()) == 0 &&
2848  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid) {
2849  AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2850  }
2851  }
2852  } else if (const auto *ArrTy =
2853  getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(OTy)) {
2854  // For C99 VLAs with the static keyword, we don't know the size so
2855  // we can't use the dereferenceable attribute, but in addrspace(0)
2856  // we know that it must be nonnull.
2857  if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == VariableArrayType::Static) {
2858  QualType ETy = ArrTy->getElementType();
2859  llvm::Align Alignment =
2860  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ETy).getAsAlign();
2861  AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder(getLLVMContext()).addAlignmentAttr(Alignment));
2862  if (!getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(ETy) &&
2863  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2864  AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2865  }
2866  }
2867 
2868  // Set `align` attribute if any.
2869  const auto *AVAttr = PVD->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2870  if (!AVAttr)
2871  if (const auto *TOTy = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(OTy))
2872  AVAttr = TOTy->getDecl()->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2873  if (AVAttr && !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
2874  // If alignment-assumption sanitizer is enabled, we do *not* add
2875  // alignment attribute here, but emit normal alignment assumption,
2876  // so the UBSAN check could function.
2877  llvm::ConstantInt *AlignmentCI =
2878  cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(EmitScalarExpr(AVAttr->getAlignment()));
2879  uint64_t AlignmentInt =
2880  AlignmentCI->getLimitedValue(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment);
2881  if (AI->getParamAlign().valueOrOne() < AlignmentInt) {
2882  AI->removeAttr(llvm::Attribute::AttrKind::Alignment);
2883  AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder(getLLVMContext()).addAlignmentAttr(
2884  llvm::Align(AlignmentInt)));
2885  }
2886  }
2887  }
2888 
2889  // Set 'noalias' if an argument type has the `restrict` qualifier.
2890  if (Arg->getType().isRestrictQualified() ||
2891  (CurCodeDecl &&
2892  CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<SYCLIntelKernelArgsRestrictAttr>() &&
2893  Arg->getType()->isPointerType()) ||
2894  (Arg->hasAttr<RestrictAttr>() && Arg->getType()->isPointerType()))
2895  AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2896  }
2897 
2898  // Prepare the argument value. If we have the trivial case, handle it
2899  // with no muss and fuss.
2900  if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType()) &&
2901  ArgI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(Ty) &&
2902  ArgI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
2903  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2904 
2905  // LLVM expects swifterror parameters to be used in very restricted
2906  // ways. Copy the value into a less-restricted temporary.
2907  llvm::Value *V = AI;
2908  if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
2909  == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
2910  QualType pointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
2911  assert(pointeeTy->isPointerType());
2912  Address temp =
2913  CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
2914  Address arg(V, ConvertTypeForMem(pointeeTy),
2915  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
2916  llvm::Value *incomingErrorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(arg);
2917  Builder.CreateStore(incomingErrorValue, temp);
2918  V = temp.getPointer();
2919 
2920  // Push a cleanup to copy the value back at the end of the function.
2921  // The convention does not guarantee that the value will be written
2922  // back if the function exits with an unwind exception.
2923  EHStack.pushCleanup<CopyBackSwiftError>(NormalCleanup, temp, arg);
2924  }
2925 
2926  // Ensure the argument is the correct type.
2927  if (V->getType() != ArgI.getCoerceToType())
2928  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2929 
2930  if (isPromoted)
2931  V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2932 
2933  // Because of merging of function types from multiple decls it is
2934  // possible for the type of an argument to not match the corresponding
2935  // type in the function type. Since we are codegening the callee
2936  // in here, add a cast to the argument type.
2937  llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertType(Arg->getType());
2938  if (V->getType() != LTy)
2939  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, LTy);
2940 
2941  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2942  break;
2943  }
2944 
2945  // VLST arguments are coerced to VLATs at the function boundary for
2946  // ABI consistency. If this is a VLST that was coerced to
2947  // a VLAT at the function boundary and the types match up, use
2948  // llvm.experimental.vector.extract to convert back to the original
2949  // VLST.
2950  if (auto *VecTyTo = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ConvertType(Ty))) {
2951  llvm::Value *Coerced = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
2952  if (auto *VecTyFrom =
2953  dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(Coerced->getType())) {
2954  // If we are casting a scalable 16 x i1 predicate vector to a fixed i8
2955  // vector, bitcast the source and use a vector extract.
2956  auto PredType =
2957  llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), 16);
2958  if (VecTyFrom == PredType &&
2959  VecTyTo->getElementType() == Builder.getInt8Ty()) {
2960  VecTyFrom = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), 2);
2961  Coerced = Builder.CreateBitCast(Coerced, VecTyFrom);
2962  }
2963  if (VecTyFrom->getElementType() == VecTyTo->getElementType()) {
2964  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int64Ty);
2965 
2966  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2967  Coerced->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce");
2968  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(Builder.CreateExtractVector(
2969  VecTyTo, Coerced, Zero, "castFixedSve")));
2970  break;
2971  }
2972  }
2973  }
2974 
2975  Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg),
2976  Arg->getName());
2977 
2978  // Pointer to store into.
2979  Address Ptr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Alloca, ArgI);
2980 
2981  // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
2982  // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
2983  llvm::StructType *STy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2984  if (ArgI.isDirect() && ArgI.getCanBeFlattened() && STy &&
2985  STy->getNumElements() > 1) {
2986  uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
2987  llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr.getElementType();
2988  uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(DstTy);
2989 
2990  Address AddrToStoreInto = Address::invalid();
2991  if (SrcSize <= DstSize) {
2992  AddrToStoreInto = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Ptr, STy);
2993  } else {
2994  AddrToStoreInto =
2995  CreateTempAlloca(STy, Alloca.getAlignment(), "coerce");
2996  }
2997 
2998  assert(STy->getNumElements() == NumIRArgs);
2999  for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
3000  auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg + i);
3001  AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce" + Twine(i));
3002  Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(AddrToStoreInto, i);
3003  Builder.CreateStore(AI, EltPtr);
3004  }
3005 
3006  if (SrcSize > DstSize) {
3007  Builder.CreateMemCpy(Ptr, AddrToStoreInto, DstSize);
3008  }
3009 
3010  } else {
3011  // Simple case, just do a coerced store of the argument into the alloca.
3012  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
3013  auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg);
3014  AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce");
3015  CreateCoercedStore(AI, Ptr, /*DstIsVolatile=*/false, *this);
3016  }
3017 
3018  // Match to what EmitParmDecl is expecting for this type.
3019  if (CodeGenFunction::hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
3020  llvm::Value *V =
3021  EmitLoadOfScalar(Alloca, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
3022  if (isPromoted)
3023  V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
3024  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
3025  } else {
3026  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
3027  }
3028  break;
3029  }
3030 
3031  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
3032  // Reconstruct into a temporary.
3033  Address alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
3034  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(alloca));
3035 
3036  auto coercionType = ArgI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
3037  alloca = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(alloca, coercionType);
3038 
3039  unsigned argIndex = FirstIRArg;
3040  for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
3041  llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
3042  if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType))
3043  continue;
3044 
3045  auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(alloca, i);
3046  auto elt = Fn->getArg(argIndex++);
3047  Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
3048  }
3049  assert(argIndex == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
3050  break;
3051  }
3052 
3053  case ABIArgInfo::Expand: {
3054  // If this structure was expanded into multiple arguments then
3055  // we need to create a temporary and reconstruct it from the
3056  // arguments.
3057  Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
3058  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Alloca, Ty);
3059  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
3060 
3061  auto FnArgIter = Fn->arg_begin() + FirstIRArg;
3062  ExpandTypeFromArgs(Ty, LV, FnArgIter);
3063  assert(FnArgIter == Fn->arg_begin() + FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
3064  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumIRArgs; i != e; ++i) {
3065  auto AI = Fn->getArg(FirstIRArg + i);
3066  AI->setName(Arg->getName() + "." + Twine(i));
3067  }
3068  break;
3069  }
3070 
3071  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
3072  assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
3073  // Initialize the local variable appropriately.
3074  if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
3075  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(CreateMemTemp(Ty)));
3076  } else {
3077  llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Arg->getType()));
3078  ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(U));
3079  }
3080  break;
3081  }
3082  }
3083 
3084  if (getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()) {
3085  for (int I = Args.size() - 1; I >= 0; --I)
3086  EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
3087  } else {
3088  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I != E; ++I)
3089  EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
3090  }
3091 }

3093 static void eraseUnusedBitCasts(llvm::Instruction *insn) {
3094  while (insn->use_empty()) {
3095  llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(insn);
3096  if (!bitcast) return;
3097 
3098  // This is "safe" because we would have used a ConstantExpr otherwise.
3099  insn = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
3100  bitcast->eraseFromParent();
3101  }
3102 }
3103 
3104 /// Try to emit a fused autorelease of a return result.
3105 static llvm::Value *tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3106  llvm::Value *result) {
3107  // We must be immediately followed the cast.
3108  llvm::BasicBlock *BB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3109  if (BB->empty()) return nullptr;
3110  if (&BB->back() != result) return nullptr;
3111 
3112  llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
3113 
3114  // result is in a BasicBlock and is therefore an Instruction.
3115  llvm::Instruction *generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(result);
3116 
3117  SmallVector<llvm::Instruction *, 4> InstsToKill;
3118 
3119  // Look for:
3120  // %generator = bitcast %type1* %generator2 to %type2*
3121  while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(generator)) {
3122  // We would have emitted this as a constant if the operand weren't
3123  // an Instruction.
3124  generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
3125 
3126  // Require the generator to be immediately followed by the cast.
3127  if (generator->getNextNode() != bitcast)
3128  return nullptr;
3129 
3130  InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
3131  }
3132 
3133  // Look for:
3134  // %generator = call i8* @objc_retain(i8* %originalResult)
3135  // or
3136  // %generator = call i8* @objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue(i8* %originalResult)
3137  llvm::CallInst *call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(generator);
3138  if (!call) return nullptr;
3139 
3140  bool doRetainAutorelease;
3141 
3142  if (call->getCalledOperand() == CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain) {
3143  doRetainAutorelease = true;
3144  } else if (call->getCalledOperand() ==
3145  CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue) {
3146  doRetainAutorelease = false;
3147 
3148  // If we emitted an assembly marker for this call (and the
3149  // ARCEntrypoints field should have been set if so), go looking
3150  // for that call. If we can't find it, we can't do this
3151  // optimization. But it should always be the immediately previous
3152  // instruction, unless we needed bitcasts around the call.
3153  if (CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker) {
3154  llvm::Instruction *prev = call->getPrevNode();
3155  assert(prev);
3156  if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(prev)) {
3157  prev = prev->getPrevNode();
3158  assert(prev);
3159  }
3160  assert(isa<llvm::CallInst>(prev));
3161  assert(cast<llvm::CallInst>(prev)->getCalledOperand() ==
3162  CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker);
3163  InstsToKill.push_back(prev);
3164  }
3165  } else {
3166  return nullptr;
3167  }
3168 
3169  result = call->getArgOperand(0);
3170  InstsToKill.push_back(call);
3171 
3172  // Keep killing bitcasts, for sanity. Note that we no longer care
3173  // about precise ordering as long as there's exactly one use.
3174  while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(result)) {
3175  if (!bitcast->hasOneUse()) break;
3176  InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
3177  result = bitcast->getOperand(0);
3178  }
3179 
3180  // Delete all the unnecessary instructions, from latest to earliest.
3181  for (auto *I : InstsToKill)
3182  I->eraseFromParent();
3183 
3184  // Do the fused retain/autorelease if we were asked to.
3185  if (doRetainAutorelease)
3186  result = CGF.EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
3187 
3188  // Cast back to the result type.
3189  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, resultType);
3190 }
3191 
3192 /// If this is a +1 of the value of an immutable 'self', remove it.
3193 static llvm::Value *tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3194  llvm::Value *result) {
3195  // This is only applicable to a method with an immutable 'self'.
3196  const ObjCMethodDecl *method =
3197  dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
3198  if (!method) return nullptr;
3199  const VarDecl *self = method->getSelfDecl();
3200  if (!self->getType().isConstQualified()) return nullptr;
3201 
3202  // Look for a retain call.
3203  llvm::CallInst *retainCall =
3204  dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(result->stripPointerCasts());
3205  if (!retainCall || retainCall->getCalledOperand() !=
3206  CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain)
3207  return nullptr;
3208 
3209  // Look for an ordinary load of 'self'.
3210  llvm::Value *retainedValue = retainCall->getArgOperand(0);
3211  llvm::LoadInst *load =
3212  dyn_cast<llvm::LoadInst>(retainedValue->stripPointerCasts());
3213  if (!load || load->isAtomic() || load->isVolatile() ||
3214  load->getPointerOperand() != CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(self).getPointer())
3215  return nullptr;
3216 
3217  // Okay! Burn it all down. This relies for correctness on the
3218  // assumption that the retain is emitted as part of the return and
3219  // that thereafter everything is used "linearly".
3220  llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
3221  eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(result));
3222  assert(retainCall->use_empty());
3223  retainCall->eraseFromParent();
3224  eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(retainedValue));
3225 
3226  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(load, resultType);
3227 }
3228 
3229 /// Emit an ARC autorelease of the result of a function.
3230 ///
3231 /// \return the value to actually return from the function
3232 static llvm::Value *emitAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3233  llvm::Value *result) {
3234  // If we're returning 'self', kill the initial retain. This is a
3235  // heuristic attempt to "encourage correctness" in the really unfortunate
3236  // case where we have a return of self during a dealloc and we desperately
3237  // need to avoid the possible autorelease.
3238  if (llvm::Value *self = tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CGF, result))
3239  return self;
3240 
3241  // At -O0, try to emit a fused retain/autorelease.
3242  if (CGF.shouldUseFusedARCCalls())
3243  if (llvm::Value *fused = tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CGF, result))
3244  return fused;
3245 
3246  return CGF.EmitARCAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
3247 }
3248 
3249 /// Heuristically search for a dominating store to the return-value slot.
3250 static llvm::StoreInst *findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
3251  // Check if a User is a store which pointerOperand is the ReturnValue.
3252  // We are looking for stores to the ReturnValue, not for stores of the
3253  // ReturnValue to some other location.
3254  auto GetStoreIfValid = [&CGF](llvm::User *U) -> llvm::StoreInst * {
3255  auto *SI = dyn_cast<llvm::StoreInst>(U);
3256  if (!SI || SI->getPointerOperand() != CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer())
3257  return nullptr;
3258  // These aren't actually possible for non-coerced returns, and we
3259  // only care about non-coerced returns on this code path.
3260  assert(!SI->isAtomic() && !SI->isVolatile());
3261  return SI;
3262  };
3263  // If there are multiple uses of the return-value slot, just check
3264  // for something immediately preceding the IP. Sometimes this can
3265  // happen with how we generate implicit-returns; it can also happen
3266  // with noreturn cleanups.
3267  if (!CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->hasOneUse()) {
3268  llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3269  if (IP->empty()) return nullptr;
3270  llvm::Instruction *I = &IP->back();
3271 
3272  // Skip lifetime markers
3273  for (llvm::BasicBlock::reverse_iterator II = IP->rbegin(),
3274  IE = IP->rend();
3275  II != IE; ++II) {
3276  if (llvm::IntrinsicInst *Intrinsic =
3277  dyn_cast<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(&*II)) {
3278  if (Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID() == llvm::Intrinsic::lifetime_end) {
3279  const llvm::Value *CastAddr = Intrinsic->getArgOperand(1);
3280  ++II;
3281  if (II == IE)
3282  break;
3283  if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(&*II) && (CastAddr == &*II))
3284  continue;
3285  }
3286  }
3287  I = &*II;
3288  break;
3289  }
3290 
3291  return GetStoreIfValid(I);
3292  }
3293 
3294  llvm::StoreInst *store =
3295  GetStoreIfValid(CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->user_back());
3296  if (!store) return nullptr;
3297 
3298  // Now do a first-and-dirty dominance check: just walk up the
3299  // single-predecessors chain from the current insertion point.
3300  llvm::BasicBlock *StoreBB = store->getParent();
3301  llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3302  while (IP != StoreBB) {
3303  if (!(IP = IP->getSinglePredecessor()))
3304  return nullptr;
3305  }
3306 
3307  // Okay, the store's basic block dominates the insertion point; we
3308  // can do our thing.
3309  return store;
3310 }
3311 
3312 // Helper functions for EmitCMSEClearRecord
3313 
3314 // Set the bits corresponding to a field having width `BitWidth` and located at
3315 // offset `BitOffset` (from the least significant bit) within a storage unit of
3316 // `Bits.size()` bytes. Each element of `Bits` corresponds to one target byte.
3317 // Use little-endian layout, i.e.`Bits[0]` is the LSB.
3318 static void setBitRange(SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits, int BitOffset,
3319  int BitWidth, int CharWidth) {
3320  assert(CharWidth <= 64);
3321  assert(static_cast<unsigned>(BitWidth) <= Bits.size() * CharWidth);
3322 
3323  int Pos = 0;
3324  if (BitOffset >= CharWidth) {
3325  Pos += BitOffset / CharWidth;
3326  BitOffset = BitOffset % CharWidth;
3327  }
3328 
3329  const uint64_t Used = (uint64_t(1) << CharWidth) - 1;
3330  if (BitOffset + BitWidth >= CharWidth) {
3331  Bits[Pos++] |= (Used << BitOffset) & Used;
3332  BitWidth -= CharWidth - BitOffset;
3333  BitOffset = 0;
3334  }
3335 
3336  while (BitWidth >= CharWidth) {
3337  Bits[Pos++] = Used;
3338  BitWidth -= CharWidth;
3339  }
3340 
3341  if (BitWidth > 0)
3342  Bits[Pos++] |= (Used >> (CharWidth - BitWidth)) << BitOffset;
3343 }
3344 
3345 // Set the bits corresponding to a field having width `BitWidth` and located at
3346 // offset `BitOffset` (from the least significant bit) within a storage unit of
3347 // `StorageSize` bytes, located at `StorageOffset` in `Bits`. Each element of
3348 // `Bits` corresponds to one target byte. Use target endian layout.
3349 static void setBitRange(SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits, int StorageOffset,
3350  int StorageSize, int BitOffset, int BitWidth,
3351  int CharWidth, bool BigEndian) {
3352 
3353  SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> TmpBits(StorageSize);
3354  setBitRange(TmpBits, BitOffset, BitWidth, CharWidth);
3355 
3356  if (BigEndian)
3357  std::reverse(TmpBits.begin(), TmpBits.end());
3358 
3359  for (uint64_t V : TmpBits)
3360  Bits[StorageOffset++] |= V;
3361 }
3362 
3363 static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &, QualType, int,
3364  SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &);
3365 
3366 // Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3367 // the actual members of the record type `RTy`. Note that this function does
3368 // not handle base classes, virtual tables, etc, since they cannot happen in
3369 // CMSE function arguments or return. The bit mask corresponds to the target
3370 // memory layout, i.e. it's endian dependent.
3371 static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, const RecordType *RTy, int Offset,
3372  SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3373  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3374  int CharWidth = Context.getCharWidth();
3375  const RecordDecl *RD = RTy->getDecl()->getDefinition();
3376  const ASTRecordLayout &ASTLayout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3377  const CGRecordLayout &Layout = CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD);
3378 
3379  int Idx = 0;
3380  for (auto I = RD->field_begin(), E = RD->field_end(); I != E; ++I, ++Idx) {
3381  const FieldDecl *F = *I;
3382 
3383  if (F->isUnnamedBitfield() || F->isZeroLengthBitField(Context) ||
3384  F->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType())
3385  continue;
3386 
3387  if (F->isBitField()) {
3388  const CGBitFieldInfo &BFI = Layout.getBitFieldInfo(F);
3389  setBitRange(Bits, Offset + BFI.StorageOffset.getQuantity(),
3390  BFI.StorageSize / CharWidth, BFI.Offset,
3391  BFI.Size, CharWidth,
3392  CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian());
3393  continue;
3394  }
3395 
3396  setUsedBits(CGM, F->getType(),
3397  Offset + ASTLayout.getFieldOffset(Idx) / CharWidth, Bits);
3398  }
3399 }
3400 
3401 // Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3402 // the elements of an array type `ATy`.
3403 static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, const ConstantArrayType *ATy,
3404  int Offset, SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3405  const ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3406 
3407  QualType ETy = Context.getBaseElementType(ATy);
3408  int Size = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(ETy).getQuantity();
3409  SmallVector<uint64_t, 4> TmpBits(Size);
3410  setUsedBits(CGM, ETy, 0, TmpBits);
3411 
3412  for (int I = 0, N = Context.getConstantArrayElementCount(ATy); I < N; ++I) {
3413  auto Src = TmpBits.begin();
3414  auto Dst = Bits.begin() + Offset + I * Size;
3415  for (int J = 0; J < Size; ++J)
3416  *Dst++ |= *Src++;
3417  }
3418 }
3419 
3420 // Set the bits in `Bits`, which correspond to the value representations of
3421 // the type `QTy`.
3422 static void setUsedBits(CodeGenModule &CGM, QualType QTy, int Offset,
3423  SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits) {
3424  if (const auto *RTy = QTy->getAs<RecordType>())
3425  return setUsedBits(CGM, RTy, Offset, Bits);
3426 
3427  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3428  if (const auto *ATy = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(QTy))
3429  return setUsedBits(CGM, ATy, Offset, Bits);
3430 
3431  int Size = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(QTy).getQuantity();
3432  if (Size <= 0)
3433  return;
3434 
3435  std::fill_n(Bits.begin() + Offset, Size,
3436  (uint64_t(1) << Context.getCharWidth()) - 1);
3437 }
3438 
3439 static uint64_t buildMultiCharMask(const SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Bits,
3440  int Pos, int Size, int CharWidth,
3441  bool BigEndian) {
3442  assert(Size > 0);
3443  uint64_t Mask = 0;
3444  if (BigEndian) {
3445  for (auto P = Bits.begin() + Pos, E = Bits.begin() + Pos + Size; P != E;
3446  ++P)
3447  Mask = (Mask << CharWidth) | *P;
3448  } else {
3449  auto P = Bits.begin() + Pos + Size, End = Bits.begin() + Pos;
3450  do
3451  Mask = (Mask << CharWidth) | *--P;
3452  while (P != End);
3453  }
3454  return Mask;
3455 }
3456 
3457 // Emit code to clear the bits in a record, which aren't a part of any user
3458 // declared member, when the record is a function return.
3459 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCMSEClearRecord(llvm::Value *Src,
3460  llvm::IntegerType *ITy,
3461  QualType QTy) {
3462  assert(Src->getType() == ITy);
3463  assert(ITy->getScalarSizeInBits() <= 64);
3464 
3465  const llvm::DataLayout &DataLayout = CGM.getDataLayout();
3466  int Size = DataLayout.getTypeStoreSize(ITy);
3467  SmallVector<uint64_t, 4> Bits(Size);
3468  setUsedBits(CGM, QTy->castAs<RecordType>(), 0, Bits);
3469 
3470  int CharWidth = CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
3471  uint64_t Mask =
3472  buildMultiCharMask(Bits, 0, Size, CharWidth, DataLayout.isBigEndian());
3473 
3474  return Builder.CreateAnd(Src, Mask, "cmse.clear");
3475 }
3476 
3477 // Emit code to clear the bits in a record, which aren't a part of any user
3478 // declared member, when the record is a function argument.
3479 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCMSEClearRecord(llvm::Value *Src,
3480  llvm::ArrayType *ATy,
3481  QualType QTy) {
3482  const llvm::DataLayout &DataLayout = CGM.getDataLayout();
3483  int Size = DataLayout.getTypeStoreSize(ATy);
3484  SmallVector<uint64_t, 16> Bits(Size);
3485  setUsedBits(CGM, QTy->castAs<RecordType>(), 0, Bits);
3486 
3487  // Clear each element of the LLVM array.
3488  int CharWidth = CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
3489  int CharsPerElt =
3490  ATy->getArrayElementType()->getScalarSizeInBits() / CharWidth;
3491  int MaskIndex = 0;
3492  llvm::Value *R = llvm::UndefValue::get(ATy);
3493  for (int I = 0, N = ATy->getArrayNumElements(); I != N; ++I) {
3494  uint64_t Mask = buildMultiCharMask(Bits, MaskIndex, CharsPerElt, CharWidth,
3495  DataLayout.isBigEndian());
3496  MaskIndex += CharsPerElt;
3497  llvm::Value *T0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I);
3498  llvm::Value *T1 = Builder.CreateAnd(T0, Mask, "cmse.clear");
3499  R = Builder.CreateInsertValue(R, T1, I);
3500  }
3501 
3502  return R;
3503 }
3504 
3505 void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionEpilog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
3506  bool EmitRetDbgLoc,
3507  SourceLocation EndLoc) {
3508  if (FI.isNoReturn()) {
3509  // Noreturn functions don't return.
3510  EmitUnreachable(EndLoc);
3511  return;
3512  }
3513 
3514  if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>()) {
3515  // Naked functions don't have epilogues.
3516  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3517  return;
3518  }
3519 
3520  // Functions with no result always return void.
3521  if (!ReturnValue.isValid()) {
3522  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3523  return;
3524  }
3525 
3526  llvm::DebugLoc RetDbgLoc;
3527  llvm::Value *RV = nullptr;
3528  QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
3529  const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
3530 
3531  switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
3532  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
3533  // Aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination. Sometimes we
3534  // need to return the sret value in a register, though.
3535  assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(RetTy));
3536  if (RetAI.getInAllocaSRet()) {
3537  llvm::Function::arg_iterator EI = CurFn->arg_end();
3538  --EI;
3539  llvm::Value *ArgStruct = &*EI;
3540  llvm::Value *SRet = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
3541  FI.getArgStruct(), ArgStruct, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
3542  llvm::Type *Ty =
3543  cast<llvm::GetElementPtrInst>(SRet)->getResultElementType();
3544  RV = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Ty, SRet, getPointerAlign(), "sret");
3545  }
3546  break;
3547 
3548  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
3549  auto AI = CurFn->arg_begin();
3550  if (RetAI.isSRetAfterThis())
3551  ++AI;
3552  switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
3553  case TEK_Complex: {
3554  ComplexPairTy RT =
3555  EmitLoadOfComplex(MakeAddrLValue(ReturnValue, RetTy), EndLoc);
3556  EmitStoreOfComplex(RT, MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(&*AI, RetTy),
3557  /*isInit*/ true);
3558  break;
3559  }
3560  case TEK_Aggregate:
3561  // Do nothing; aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination.
3562  break;
3563  case TEK_Scalar: {
3564  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
3565  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
3566  CharUnits Alignment =
3567  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(RetTy, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
3568  Address ArgAddr(&*AI, ConvertType(RetTy), Alignment);
3569  LValue ArgVal =
3570  LValue::MakeAddr(ArgAddr, RetTy, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
3571  EmitStoreOfScalar(
3572  Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue), ArgVal, /*isInit*/ true);
3573  break;
3574  }
3575  }
3576  break;
3577  }
3578 
3579  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
3580  case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
3581  if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(RetTy) &&
3582  RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
3583  // The internal return value temp always will have pointer-to-return-type
3584  // type, just do a load.
3585 
3586  // If there is a dominating store to ReturnValue, we can elide
3587  // the load, zap the store, and usually zap the alloca.
3588  if (llvm::StoreInst *SI =
3589  findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(*this)) {
3590  // Reuse the debug location from the store unless there is
3591  // cleanup code to be emitted between the store and return
3592  // instruction.
3593  if (EmitRetDbgLoc && !AutoreleaseResult)
3594  RetDbgLoc = SI->getDebugLoc();
3595  // Get the stored value and nuke the now-dead store.
3596  RV = SI->getValueOperand();
3597  SI->eraseFromParent();
3598 
3599  // Otherwise, we have to do a simple load.
3600  } else {
3601  RV = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue);
3602  }
3603  } else {
3604  // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
3605  Address V = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, ReturnValue, RetAI);
3606 
3607  RV = CreateCoercedLoad(V, RetAI.getCoerceToType(), *this);
3608  }
3609 
3610  // In ARC, end functions that return a retainable type with a call
3611  // to objc_autoreleaseReturnValue.
3612  if (AutoreleaseResult) {
3613 #ifndef NDEBUG
3614  // Type::isObjCRetainabletype has to be called on a QualType that hasn't
3615  // been stripped of the typedefs, so we cannot use RetTy here. Get the
3616  // original return type of FunctionDecl, CurCodeDecl, and BlockDecl from
3617  // CurCodeDecl or BlockInfo.
3618  QualType RT;
3619 
3620  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3621  RT = FD->getReturnType();
3622  else if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3623  RT = MD->getReturnType();
3624  else if (isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3625  RT = BlockInfo->BlockExpression->getFunctionType()->getReturnType();
3626  else
3627  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected function/method type");
3628 
3629  assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
3630  !FI.isReturnsRetained() &&
3631  RT->isObjCRetainableType());
3632 #endif
3633  RV = emitAutoreleaseOfResult(*this, RV);
3634  }
3635 
3636  break;
3637 
3638  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
3639  break;
3640 
3641  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
3642  auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
3643 
3644  // Load all of the coerced elements out into results.
3645  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 4> results;
3646  Address addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(ReturnValue, coercionType);
3647  for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
3648  auto coercedEltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
3649  if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(coercedEltType))
3650  continue;
3651 
3652  auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
3653  auto elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
3654  results.push_back(elt);
3655  }
3656 
3657  // If we have one result, it's the single direct result type.
3658  if (results.size() == 1) {
3659  RV = results[0];
3660 
3661  // Otherwise, we need to make a first-class aggregate.
3662  } else {
3663  // Construct a return type that lacks padding elements.
3664  llvm::Type *returnType = RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType();
3665 
3666  RV = llvm::UndefValue::get(returnType);
3667  for (unsigned i = 0, e = results.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3668  RV = Builder.CreateInsertValue(RV, results[i], i);
3669  }
3670  }
3671  break;
3672  }
3673  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
3674  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
3675  llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
3676  }
3677 
3678  llvm::Instruction *Ret;
3679  if (RV) {
3680  if (CurFuncDecl && CurFuncDecl->hasAttr<CmseNSEntryAttr>()) {
3681  // For certain return types, clear padding bits, as they may reveal
3682  // sensitive information.
3683  // Small struct/union types are passed as integers.
3684  auto *ITy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(RV->getType());
3685  if (ITy != nullptr && isa<RecordType>(RetTy.getCanonicalType()))
3686  RV = EmitCMSEClearRecord(RV, ITy, RetTy);
3687  }
3688  EmitReturnValueCheck(RV);
3689  Ret = Builder.CreateRet(RV);
3690  } else {
3691  Ret = Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3692  }
3693 
3694  if (RetDbgLoc)
3695  Ret->setDebugLoc(std::move(RetDbgLoc));
3696 }
3697 
3698 void CodeGenFunction::EmitReturnValueCheck(llvm::Value *RV) {
3699  // A current decl may not be available when emitting vtable thunks.
3700  if (!CurCodeDecl)
3701  return;
3702 
3703  // If the return block isn't reachable, neither is this check, so don't emit
3704  // it.
3705  if (ReturnBlock.isValid() && ReturnBlock.getBlock()->use_empty())
3706  return;
3707 
3708  ReturnsNonNullAttr *RetNNAttr = nullptr;
3709  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute))
3710  RetNNAttr = CurCodeDecl->getAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>();
3711 
3712  if (!RetNNAttr && !requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3713  return;
3714 
3715  // Prefer the returns_nonnull attribute if it's present.
3716  SourceLocation AttrLoc;
3717  SanitizerMask CheckKind;
3718  SanitizerHandler Handler;
3719  if (RetNNAttr) {
3720  assert(!requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck() &&
3721  "Cannot check nullability and the nonnull attribute");
3722  AttrLoc = RetNNAttr->getLocation();
3723  CheckKind = SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute;
3724  Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullReturn;
3725  } else {
3726  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3727  if (auto *TSI = DD->getTypeSourceInfo())
3728  if (auto FTL = TSI->getTypeLoc().getAsAdjusted<FunctionTypeLoc>())
3729  AttrLoc = FTL.getReturnLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
3730  CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityReturn;
3731  Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityReturn;
3732  }
3733 
3734  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3735 
3736  // Make sure the "return" source location is valid. If we're checking a
3737  // nullability annotation, make sure the preconditions for the check are met.
3738  llvm::BasicBlock *Check = createBasicBlock("nullcheck");
3739  llvm::BasicBlock *NoCheck = createBasicBlock("no.nullcheck");
3740  llvm::Value *SLocPtr = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnLocation, "return.sloc.load");
3741  llvm::Value *CanNullCheck = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(SLocPtr);
3742  if (requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3743  CanNullCheck =
3744  Builder.CreateAnd(CanNullCheck, RetValNullabilityPrecondition);
3745  Builder.CreateCondBr(CanNullCheck, Check, NoCheck);
3746  EmitBlock(Check);
3747 
3748  // Now do the null check.
3749  llvm::Value *Cond = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(RV);
3750  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc)};
3751  llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = {SLocPtr};
3752  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, DynamicData);
3753 
3754  EmitBlock(NoCheck);
3755 
3756 #ifndef NDEBUG
3757  // The return location should not be used after the check has been emitted.
3758  ReturnLocation = Address::invalid();
3759 #endif
3760 }
3761 
3762 static bool isInAllocaArgument(CGCXXABI &ABI, QualType type) {
3763  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3764  return RD && ABI.getRecordArgABI(RD) == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory;
3765 }

3767 static AggValueSlot createPlaceholderSlot(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3768  QualType Ty) {
3769  // FIXME: Generate IR in one pass, rather than going back and fixing up these
3770  // placeholders.
3771  llvm::Type *IRTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
3772  llvm::Type *IRPtrTy = IRTy->getPointerTo();
3773  llvm::Value *Placeholder = llvm::UndefValue::get(IRPtrTy->getPointerTo());
3774 
3775  // FIXME: When we generate this IR in one pass, we shouldn't need
3776  // this win32-specific alignment hack.
3777  CharUnits Align = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
3778  Placeholder = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(IRPtrTy, Placeholder, Align);
3779 
3780  return AggValueSlot::forAddr(Address(Placeholder, IRTy, Align),
3781  Ty.getQualifiers(),
3782  AggValueSlot::IsNotDestructed,
3783  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
3784  AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
3785  AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
3786 }
