3788 void CodeGenFunction::EmitDelegateCallArg(CallArgList &args,
3789  const VarDecl *param,
3790  SourceLocation loc) {
3791  // StartFunction converted the ABI-lowered parameter(s) into a
3792  // local alloca. We need to turn that into an r-value suitable
3793  // for EmitCall.
3794  Address local = GetAddrOfLocalVar(param);
3795 
3796  QualType type = param->getType();
3797 
3798  if (isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), type)) {
3799  CGM.ErrorUnsupported(param, "forwarded non-trivially copyable parameter");
3800  }
3801 
3802  // GetAddrOfLocalVar returns a pointer-to-pointer for references,
3803  // but the argument needs to be the original pointer.
3804  if (type->isReferenceType()) {
3805  args.add(RValue::get(Builder.CreateLoad(local)), type);
3806 
3807  // In ARC, move out of consumed arguments so that the release cleanup
3808  // entered by StartFunction doesn't cause an over-release. This isn't
3809  // optimal -O0 code generation, but it should get cleaned up when
3810  // optimization is enabled. This also assumes that delegate calls are
3811  // performed exactly once for a set of arguments, but that should be safe.
3812  } else if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
3813  param->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>() &&
3814  type->isObjCRetainableType()) {
3815  llvm::Value *ptr = Builder.CreateLoad(local);
3816  auto null =
3817  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ptr->getType()));
3818  Builder.CreateStore(null, local);
3819  args.add(RValue::get(ptr), type);
3820 
3821  // For the most part, we just need to load the alloca, except that
3822  // aggregate r-values are actually pointers to temporaries.
3823  } else {
3824  args.add(convertTempToRValue(local, type, loc), type);
3825  }
3826 
3827  // Deactivate the cleanup for the callee-destructed param that was pushed.
3828  if (type->isRecordType() && !CurFuncIsThunk &&
3829  type->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee() &&
3830  param->needsDestruction(getContext())) {
3831  EHScopeStack::stable_iterator cleanup =
3832  CalleeDestructedParamCleanups.lookup(cast<ParmVarDecl>(param));
3833  assert(cleanup.isValid() &&
3834  "cleanup for callee-destructed param not recorded");
3835  // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
3836  llvm::Instruction *isActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3837  args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(cleanup, isActive);
3838  }
3839 }
3840 
3841 static bool isProvablyNull(llvm::Value *addr) {
3842  return isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(addr);
3843 }
3844 
3845 /// Emit the actual writing-back of a writeback.
3846 static void emitWriteback(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3847  const CallArgList::Writeback &writeback) {
3848  const LValue &srcLV = writeback.Source;
3849  Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress(CGF);
3850  assert(!isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer()) &&
3851  "shouldn't have writeback for provably null argument");
3852 
3853  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3854 
3855  // If the argument wasn't provably non-null, we need to null check
3856  // before doing the store.
3857  bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3858  CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3859  if (!provablyNonNull) {
3860  llvm::BasicBlock *writebackBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.writeback");
3861  contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.done");
3862 
3863  llvm::Value *isNull =
3864  CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
3865  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, writebackBB);
3866  CGF.EmitBlock(writebackBB);
3867  }
3868 
3869  // Load the value to writeback.
3870  llvm::Value *value = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(writeback.Temporary);
3871 
3872  // Cast it back, in case we're writing an id to a Foo* or something.
3873  value = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(value, srcAddr.getElementType(),
3874  "icr.writeback-cast");
3875 
3876  // Perform the writeback.
3877 
3878  // If we have a "to use" value, it's something we need to emit a use
3879  // of. This has to be carefully threaded in: if it's done after the
3880  // release it's potentially undefined behavior (and the optimizer
3881  // will ignore it), and if it happens before the retain then the
3882  // optimizer could move the release there.
3883  if (writeback.ToUse) {
3884  assert(srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong);
3885 
3886  // Retain the new value. No need to block-copy here: the block's
3887  // being passed up the stack.
3888  value = CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(value);
3889 
3890  // Emit the intrinsic use here.
3891  CGF.EmitARCIntrinsicUse(writeback.ToUse);
3892 
3893  // Load the old value (primitively).
3894  llvm::Value *oldValue = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(srcLV, SourceLocation());
3895 
3896  // Put the new value in place (primitively).
3897  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(value, srcLV, /*init*/ false);
3898 
3899  // Release the old value.
3900  CGF.EmitARCRelease(oldValue, srcLV.isARCPreciseLifetime());
3901 
3902  // Otherwise, we can just do a normal lvalue store.
3903  } else {
3904  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), srcLV);
3905  }
3906 
3907  // Jump to the continuation block.
3908  if (!provablyNonNull)
3909  CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
3910 }
3911 
3912 static void emitWritebacks(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3913  const CallArgList &args) {
3914  for (const auto &I : args.writebacks())
3915  emitWriteback(CGF, I);
3916 }
3917 
3918 static void deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3919  const CallArgList &CallArgs) {
3920  ArrayRef<CallArgList::CallArgCleanup> Cleanups =
3921  CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate();
3922  // Iterate in reverse to increase the likelihood of popping the cleanup.
3923  for (const auto &I : llvm::reverse(Cleanups)) {
3924  CGF.DeactivateCleanupBlock(I.Cleanup, I.IsActiveIP);
3925  I.IsActiveIP->eraseFromParent();
3926  }
3927 }
3928 
3929 static const Expr *maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(const Expr *E) {
3930  if (const UnaryOperator *uop = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E->IgnoreParens()))
3931  if (uop->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
3932  return uop->getSubExpr();
3933  return nullptr;
3934 }
3935 
3936 /// Emit an argument that's being passed call-by-writeback. That is,
3937 /// we are passing the address of an __autoreleased temporary; it
3938 /// might be copy-initialized with the current value of the given
3939 /// address, but it will definitely be copied out of after the call.
3940 static void emitWritebackArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, CallArgList &args,
3941  const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE) {
3942  LValue srcLV;
3943 
3944  // Make an optimistic effort to emit the address as an l-value.
3945  // This can fail if the argument expression is more complicated.
3946  if (const Expr *lvExpr = maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(CRE->getSubExpr())) {
3947  srcLV = CGF.EmitLValue(lvExpr);
3948 
3949  // Otherwise, just emit it as a scalar.
3950  } else {
3951  Address srcAddr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CRE->getSubExpr());
3952 
3953  QualType srcAddrType =
3954  CRE->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3955  srcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(srcAddr, srcAddrType);
3956  }
3957  Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress(CGF);
3958 
3959  // The dest and src types don't necessarily match in LLVM terms
3960  // because of the crazy ObjC compatibility rules.
3961 
3962  llvm::PointerType *destType =
3963  cast<llvm::PointerType>(CGF.ConvertType(CRE->getType()));
3964  llvm::Type *destElemType =
3965  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CRE->getType()->getPointeeType());
3966 
3967  // If the address is a constant null, just pass the appropriate null.
3968  if (isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer())) {
3969  args.add(RValue::get(llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType)),
3970  CRE->getType());
3971  return;
3972  }
3973 
3974  // Create the temporary.
3975  Address temp =
3976  CGF.CreateTempAlloca(destElemType, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "icr.temp");
3977  // Loading an l-value can introduce a cleanup if the l-value is __weak,
3978  // and that cleanup will be conditional if we can't prove that the l-value
3979  // isn't null, so we need to register a dominating point so that the cleanups
3980  // system will make valid IR.
3981  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation condEval(CGF);
3982 
3983  // Zero-initialize it if we're not doing a copy-initialization.
3984  bool shouldCopy = CRE->shouldCopy();
3985  if (!shouldCopy) {
3986  llvm::Value *null =
3987  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(destElemType));
3988  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(null, temp);
3989  }
3990 
3991  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3992  llvm::BasicBlock *originBB = nullptr;
3993 
3994  // If the address is *not* known to be non-null, we need to switch.
3995  llvm::Value *finalArgument;
3996 
3997  bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3998  CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3999  if (provablyNonNull) {
4000  finalArgument = temp.getPointer();
4001  } else {
4002  llvm::Value *isNull =
4003  CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
4004 
4005  finalArgument = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(isNull,
4006  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType),
4007  temp.getPointer(), "icr.argument");
4008 
4009  // If we need to copy, then the load has to be conditional, which
4010  // means we need control flow.
4011  if (shouldCopy) {
4012  originBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4013  contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.cont");
4014  llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.copy");
4015  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, copyBB);
4016  CGF.EmitBlock(copyBB);
4017  condEval.begin(CGF);
4018  }
4019  }
4020 
4021  llvm::Value *valueToUse = nullptr;
4022 
4023  // Perform a copy if necessary.
4024  if (shouldCopy) {
4025  RValue srcRV = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(srcLV, SourceLocation());
4026  assert(srcRV.isScalar());
4027 
4028  llvm::Value *src = srcRV.getScalarVal();
4029  src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, destElemType, "icr.cast");
4030 
4031  // Use an ordinary store, not a store-to-lvalue.
4032  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(src, temp);
4033 
4034  // If optimization is enabled, and the value was held in a
4035  // __strong variable, we need to tell the optimizer that this
4036  // value has to stay alive until we're doing the store back.
4037  // This is because the temporary is effectively unretained,
4038  // and so otherwise we can violate the high-level semantics.
4039  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0 &&
4040  srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
4041  valueToUse = src;
4042  }
4043  }
4044 
4045  // Finish the control flow if we needed it.
4046  if (shouldCopy && !provablyNonNull) {
4047  llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4048  CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
4049 
4050  // Make a phi for the value to intrinsically use.
4051  if (valueToUse) {
4052  llvm::PHINode *phiToUse = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(valueToUse->getType(), 2,
4053  "icr.to-use");
4054  phiToUse->addIncoming(valueToUse, copyBB);
4055  phiToUse->addIncoming(llvm::UndefValue::get(valueToUse->getType()),
4056  originBB);
4057  valueToUse = phiToUse;
4058  }
4059 
4060  condEval.end(CGF);
4061  }
4062 
4063  args.addWriteback(srcLV, temp, valueToUse);
4064  args.add(RValue::get(finalArgument), CRE->getType());
4065 }
4066 
4067 void CallArgList::allocateArgumentMemory(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
4068  assert(!StackBase);
4069 
4070  // Save the stack.
4071  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::stacksave);
4072  StackBase = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, {}, "inalloca.save");
4073 }
4074 
4075 void CallArgList::freeArgumentMemory(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
4076  if (StackBase) {
4077  // Restore the stack after the call.
4078  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::stackrestore);
4079  CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, StackBase);
4080  }
4081 }

4083 void CodeGenFunction::EmitNonNullArgCheck(RValue RV, QualType ArgType,
4084  SourceLocation ArgLoc,
4085  AbstractCallee AC,
4086  unsigned ParmNum) {
4087  if (!AC.getDecl() || !(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute) ||
4088  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg)))
4089  return;
4090 
4091  // The param decl may be missing in a variadic function.
4092  auto PVD = ParmNum < AC.getNumParams() ? AC.getParamDecl(ParmNum) : nullptr;
4093  unsigned ArgNo = PVD ? PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex() : ParmNum;
4094 
4095  // Prefer the nonnull attribute if it's present.
4096  const NonNullAttr *NNAttr = nullptr;
4097  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute))
4098  NNAttr = getNonNullAttr(AC.getDecl(), PVD, ArgType, ArgNo);
4099 
4100  bool CanCheckNullability = false;
4101  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg) && !NNAttr && PVD) {
4102  auto Nullability = PVD->getType()->getNullability(getContext());
4103  CanCheckNullability = Nullability &&
4104  *Nullability == NullabilityKind::NonNull &&
4105  PVD->getTypeSourceInfo();
4106  }
4107 
4108  if (!NNAttr && !CanCheckNullability)
4109  return;
4110 
4111  SourceLocation AttrLoc;
4112  SanitizerMask CheckKind;
4113  SanitizerHandler Handler;
4114  if (NNAttr) {
4115  AttrLoc = NNAttr->getLocation();
4116  CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute;
4117  Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullArg;
4118  } else {
4119  AttrLoc = PVD->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
4120  CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg;
4121  Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityArg;
4122  }
4123 
4124  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
4125  llvm::Value *Cond = EmitNonNullRValueCheck(RV, ArgType);
4126  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
4127  EmitCheckSourceLocation(ArgLoc), EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc),
4128  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, ArgNo + 1),
4129  };
4130  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, None);
4131 }
4132 
4133 // Check if the call is going to use the inalloca convention. This needs to
4134 // agree with CGFunctionInfo::usesInAlloca. The CGFunctionInfo is arranged
4135 // later, so we can't check it directly.
4136 static bool hasInAllocaArgs(CodeGenModule &CGM, CallingConv ExplicitCC,
4137  ArrayRef<QualType> ArgTypes) {
4138  // The Swift calling conventions don't go through the target-specific
4139  // argument classification, they never use inalloca.
4140  // TODO: Consider limiting inalloca use to only calling conventions supported
4141  // by MSVC.
4142  if (ExplicitCC == CC_Swift || ExplicitCC == CC_SwiftAsync)
4143  return false;
4144  if (!CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
4145  return false;
4146  return llvm::any_of(ArgTypes, [&](QualType Ty) {
4147  return isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), Ty);
4148  });
4149 }

4151 #ifndef NDEBUG
4152 // Determine whether the given argument is an Objective-C method
4153 // that may have type parameters in its signature.
4154 static bool isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(const ObjCMethodDecl *method) {
4155  const DeclContext *dc = method->getDeclContext();
4156  if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *classDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(dc)) {
4157  return classDecl->getTypeParamListAsWritten();
4158  }
4159 
4160  if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *catDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(dc)) {
4161  return catDecl->getTypeParamList();
4162  }
4163 
4164  return false;
4165 }
4166 #endif
4167 
4168 /// EmitCallArgs - Emit call arguments for a function.
4169 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArgs(
4170  CallArgList &Args, PrototypeWrapper Prototype,
4171  llvm::iterator_range<CallExpr::const_arg_iterator> ArgRange,
4172  AbstractCallee AC, unsigned ParamsToSkip, EvaluationOrder Order) {
4173  SmallVector<QualType, 16> ArgTypes;
4174 
4175  assert((ParamsToSkip == 0 || Prototype.P) &&
4176  "Can't skip parameters if type info is not provided");
4177 
4178  // This variable only captures *explicitly* written conventions, not those
4179  // applied by default via command line flags or target defaults, such as
4180  // thiscall, aapcs, stdcall via -mrtd, etc. Computing that correctly would
4181  // require knowing if this is a C++ instance method or being able to see
4182  // unprototyped FunctionTypes.
4183  CallingConv ExplicitCC = CC_C;
4184 
4185  // First, if a prototype was provided, use those argument types.
4186  bool IsVariadic = false;
4187  if (Prototype.P) {
4188  const auto *MD = Prototype.P.dyn_cast<const ObjCMethodDecl *>();
4189  if (MD) {
4190  IsVariadic = MD->isVariadic();
4191  ExplicitCC = getCallingConventionForDecl(
4192  MD, CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows());
4193  ArgTypes.assign(MD->param_type_begin() + ParamsToSkip,
4194  MD->param_type_end());
4195  } else {
4196  const auto *FPT = Prototype.P.get<const FunctionProtoType *>();
4197  IsVariadic = FPT->isVariadic();
4198  ExplicitCC = FPT->getExtInfo().getCC();
4199  ArgTypes.assign(FPT->param_type_begin() + ParamsToSkip,
4200  FPT->param_type_end());
4201  }
4202 
4203 #ifndef NDEBUG
4204  // Check that the prototyped types match the argument expression types.
4205  bool isGenericMethod = MD && isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(MD);
4206  CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin();
4207  for (QualType Ty : ArgTypes) {
4208  assert(Arg != ArgRange.end() && "Running over edge of argument list!");
4209  assert(
4210  (isGenericMethod || Ty->isVariablyModifiedType() ||
4211  Ty.getNonReferenceType()->isObjCRetainableType() ||
4212  getContext()
4213  .getCanonicalType(Ty.getNonReferenceType())
4214  .getTypePtr() ==
4215  getContext().getCanonicalType((*Arg)->getType()).getTypePtr()) &&
4216  "type mismatch in call argument!");
4217  ++Arg;
4218  }
4219 
4220  // Either we've emitted all the call args, or we have a call to variadic
4221  // function.
4222  assert((Arg == ArgRange.end() || IsVariadic) &&
4223  "Extra arguments in non-variadic function!");
4224 #endif
4225  }
4226 
4227  // If we still have any arguments, emit them using the type of the argument.
4228  for (auto *A : llvm::drop_begin(ArgRange, ArgTypes.size()))
4229  ArgTypes.push_back(IsVariadic ? getVarArgType(A) : A->getType());
4230  assert((int)ArgTypes.size() == (ArgRange.end() - ArgRange.begin()));
4231 
4232  // We must evaluate arguments from right to left in the MS C++ ABI,
4233  // because arguments are destroyed left to right in the callee. As a special
4234  // case, there are certain language constructs that require left-to-right
4235  // evaluation, and in those cases we consider the evaluation order requirement
4236  // to trump the "destruction order is reverse construction order" guarantee.
4237  bool LeftToRight =
4238  CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()
4239  ? Order == EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight
4240  : Order != EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
4241 
4242  auto MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize = [&](unsigned I, const Expr *Arg,
4243  RValue EmittedArg) {
4244  if (!AC.hasFunctionDecl() || I >= AC.getNumParams())
4245  return;
4246  auto *PS = AC.getParamDecl(I)->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
4247  if (PS == nullptr)
4248  return;
4249 
4250  const auto &Context = getContext();
4251  auto SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
4252  auto T = Builder.getIntNTy(Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy));
4253  assert(EmittedArg.getScalarVal() && "We emitted nothing for the arg?");
4254  llvm::Value *V = evaluateOrEmitBuiltinObjectSize(Arg, PS->getType(), T,
4255  EmittedArg.getScalarVal(),
4256  PS->isDynamic());
4257  Args.add(RValue::get(V), SizeTy);
4258  // If we're emitting args in reverse, be sure to do so with
4259  // pass_object_size, as well.
4260  if (!LeftToRight)
4261  std::swap(Args.back(), *(&Args.back() - 1));
4262  };
4263 
4264  // Insert a stack save if we're going to need any inalloca args.
4265  if (hasInAllocaArgs(CGM, ExplicitCC, ArgTypes)) {
4266  assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86 &&
4267  "inalloca only supported on x86");
4268  Args.allocateArgumentMemory(*this);
4269  }
4270 
4271  // Evaluate each argument in the appropriate order.
4272  size_t CallArgsStart = Args.size();
4273  for (unsigned I = 0, E = ArgTypes.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4274  unsigned Idx = LeftToRight ? I : E - I - 1;
4275  CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin() + Idx;
4276  unsigned InitialArgSize = Args.size();
4277  // If *Arg is an ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr, check that either the types of
4278  // the argument and parameter match or the objc method is parameterized.
4279  assert((!isa<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(*Arg) ||
4280  getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType((*Arg)->getType(),
4281  ArgTypes[Idx]) ||
4282  (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl()) &&
4283  isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl())))) &&
4284  "Argument and parameter types don't match");
4285  EmitCallArg(Args, *Arg, ArgTypes[Idx]);
4286  // In particular, we depend on it being the last arg in Args, and the
4287  // objectsize bits depend on there only being one arg if !LeftToRight.
4288  assert(InitialArgSize + 1 == Args.size() &&
4289  "The code below depends on only adding one arg per EmitCallArg");
4290  (void)InitialArgSize;
4291  // Since pointer argument are never emitted as LValue, it is safe to emit
4292  // non-null argument check for r-value only.
4293  if (!Args.back().hasLValue()) {
4294  RValue RVArg = Args.back().getKnownRValue();
4295  EmitNonNullArgCheck(RVArg, ArgTypes[Idx], (*Arg)->getExprLoc(), AC,
4296  ParamsToSkip + Idx);
4297  // @llvm.objectsize should never have side-effects and shouldn't need
4298  // destruction/cleanups, so we can safely "emit" it after its arg,
4299  // regardless of right-to-leftness
4300  MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize(Idx, *Arg, RVArg);
4301  }
4302  }
4303 
4304  if (!LeftToRight) {
4305  // Un-reverse the arguments we just evaluated so they match up with the LLVM
4306  // IR function.
4307  std::reverse(Args.begin() + CallArgsStart, Args.end());
4308  }
4309 }

4313 struct DestroyUnpassedArg final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
4314  DestroyUnpassedArg(Address Addr, QualType Ty)
4315  : Addr(Addr), Ty(Ty) {}
4316 
4317  Address Addr;
4318  QualType Ty;
4319 
4320  void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
4321  QualType::DestructionKind DtorKind = Ty.isDestructedType();
4322  if (DtorKind == QualType::DK_cxx_destructor) {
4323  const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->getDestructor();
4324  assert(!Dtor->isTrivial());
4325  CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(Dtor, Dtor_Complete, /*for vbase*/ false,
4326  /*Delegating=*/false, Addr, Ty);
4327  } else {
4328  CGF.callCStructDestructor(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty));
4329  }
4330  }
4331 };

4337  if ((disabledDebugInfo = isa<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E) && CGF.getDebugInfo()))
4338  CGF.disableDebugInfo();

4348 RValue CallArg::getRValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
4349  if (!HasLV)
4350  return RV;
4351  LValue Copy = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty), Ty);
4352  CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Copy, LV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
4353  LV.isVolatile());
4354  IsUsed = true;
4355  return RValue::getAggregate(Copy.getAddress(CGF));
4356 }

4358 void CallArg::copyInto(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Addr) const {
4359  LValue Dst = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
4360  if (!HasLV && RV.isScalar())
4361  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(RV.getScalarVal(), Dst, /*isInit=*/true);
4362  else if (!HasLV && RV.isComplex())
4363  CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(RV.getComplexVal(), Dst, /*init=*/true);
4364  else {
4365  auto Addr = HasLV ? LV.getAddress(CGF) : RV.getAggregateAddress();
4366  LValue SrcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
4367  // We assume that call args are never copied into subobjects.
4368  CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dst, SrcLV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
4369  HasLV ? LV.isVolatileQualified()
4370  : RV.isVolatileQualified());
4371  }
4372  IsUsed = true;
4373 }
4374 
4375 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArg(CallArgList &args, const Expr *E,
4376  QualType type) {
4377  DisableDebugLocationUpdates Dis(*this, E);
4378  if (const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE
4379  = dyn_cast<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(E)) {
4380  assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
4381  return emitWritebackArg(*this, args, CRE);
4382  }
4383 
4384  assert(type->isReferenceType() == E->isGLValue() &&
4385  "reference binding to unmaterialized r-value!");
4386 
4387  if (E->isGLValue()) {
4388  assert(E->getObjectKind() == OK_Ordinary);
4389  return args.add(EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(E), type);
4390  }
4391 
4392  bool HasAggregateEvalKind = hasAggregateEvaluationKind(type);
4393 
4394  // In the Microsoft C++ ABI, aggregate arguments are destructed by the callee.
4395  // However, we still have to push an EH-only cleanup in case we unwind before
4396  // we make it to the call.
4397  if (type->isRecordType() &&
4398  type->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee()) {
4399  // If we're using inalloca, use the argument memory. Otherwise, use a
4400  // temporary.
4401  AggValueSlot Slot = args.isUsingInAlloca()
4402  ? createPlaceholderSlot(*this, type) : CreateAggTemp(type, "agg.tmp");
4403 
4404  bool DestroyedInCallee = true, NeedsEHCleanup = true;
4405  if (const auto *RD = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4406  DestroyedInCallee = RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor();
4407  else
4408  NeedsEHCleanup = needsEHCleanup(type.isDestructedType());
4409 
4410  if (DestroyedInCallee)
4411  Slot.setExternallyDestructed();
4412 
4413  EmitAggExpr(E, Slot);
4414  RValue RV = Slot.asRValue();
4415  args.add(RV, type);
4416 
4417  if (DestroyedInCallee && NeedsEHCleanup) {
4418  // Create a no-op GEP between the placeholder and the cleanup so we can
4419  // RAUW it successfully. It also serves as a marker of the first
4420  // instruction where the cleanup is active.
4421  pushFullExprCleanup<DestroyUnpassedArg>(EHCleanup, Slot.getAddress(),
4422  type);
4423  // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
4424  llvm::Instruction *IsActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4425  args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(EHStack.stable_begin(), IsActive);
4426  }
4427  return;
4428  }
4429 
4430  if (HasAggregateEvalKind && isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(E) &&
4431  cast<CastExpr>(E)->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue) {
4432  LValue L = EmitLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
4433  assert(L.isSimple());
4434  args.addUncopiedAggregate(L, type);
4435  return;
4436  }
4437 
4438  args.add(EmitAnyExprToTemp(E), type);
4439 }
4440 
4441 QualType CodeGenFunction::getVarArgType(const Expr *Arg) {
4442  // System headers on Windows define NULL to 0 instead of 0LL on Win64. MSVC
4443  // implicitly widens null pointer constants that are arguments to varargs
4444  // functions to pointer-sized ints.
4445  if (!getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows())
4446  return Arg->getType();
4447 
4448  if (Arg->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
4449  getContext().getTypeSize(Arg->getType()) <
4450  getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) &&
4451  Arg->isNullPointerConstant(getContext(),
4452  Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
4453  return getContext().getIntPtrType();
4454  }
4455 
4456  return Arg->getType();
4457 }

4459 // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
4460 // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
4461 void
4462 CodeGenFunction::AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(llvm::Instruction *Inst) {
4463  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0 &&
4464  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ObjCAutoRefCountExceptions)
4465  Inst->setMetadata("clang.arc.no_objc_arc_exceptions",
4466  CGM.getNoObjCARCExceptionsMetadata());
4467 }

4492 
4493 // Calls which may throw must have operand bundles indicating which funclet
4494 // they are nested within.
4495 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1>
4496 CodeGenFunction::getBundlesForFunclet(llvm::Value *Callee) {
4497  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList;
4498  // There is no need for a funclet operand bundle if we aren't inside a
4499  // funclet.
4500  if (!CurrentFuncletPad)
4501  return BundleList;
4502 
4503  // Skip intrinsics which cannot throw.
4504  auto *CalleeFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Callee->stripPointerCasts());
4505  if (CalleeFn && CalleeFn->isIntrinsic() && CalleeFn->doesNotThrow())
4506  return BundleList;
4507 
4508  BundleList.emplace_back("funclet", CurrentFuncletPad);
4509  return BundleList;
4510 }

4512 /// Emits a simple call (never an invoke) to the given runtime function.
4513 llvm::CallInst *CodeGenFunction::EmitRuntimeCall(llvm::FunctionCallee callee,
4514  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> args,
4515  const llvm::Twine &name) {
4516  llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(
4517  callee, args, getBundlesForFunclet(callee.getCallee()), name);
4518  call->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4519  return call;
4520 }

4522 /// Emits a call or invoke to the given noreturn runtime function.
4523 void CodeGenFunction::EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(
4524  llvm::FunctionCallee callee, ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> args) {
4525  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
4526  getBundlesForFunclet(callee.getCallee());
4527 
4528  if (getInvokeDest()) {
4529  llvm::InvokeInst *invoke =
4530  Builder.CreateInvoke(callee,
4531  getUnreachableBlock(),
4532  getInvokeDest(),
4533  args,
4534  BundleList);
4535  invoke->setDoesNotReturn();
4536  invoke->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4537  } else {
4538  llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(callee, args, BundleList);
4539  call->setDoesNotReturn();
4540  call->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4541  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4542  }
4543 }

4552 /// Emits a call or invoke instruction to the given runtime function.

4561 
4562 /// Emits a call or invoke instruction to the given function, depending
4563 /// on the current state of the EH stack.
4564 llvm::CallBase *CodeGenFunction::EmitCallOrInvoke(llvm::FunctionCallee Callee,
4565  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args,
4566  const Twine &Name) {
4567  llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = getInvokeDest();
4568  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
4569  getBundlesForFunclet(Callee.getCallee());
4570 
4571  llvm::CallBase *Inst;
4572  if (!InvokeDest)
4573  Inst = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args, BundleList, Name);
4574  else {
4575  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
4576  Inst = Builder.CreateInvoke(Callee, ContBB, InvokeDest, Args, BundleList,
4577  Name);
4578  EmitBlock(ContBB);
4579  }
4580 
4581  // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
4582  // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
4583  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
4584  AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(Inst);
4585 
4586  return Inst;
4587 }
4588 
4589 void CodeGenFunction::deferPlaceholderReplacement(llvm::Instruction *Old,
4590  llvm::Value *New) {
4591  DeferredReplacements.push_back(
4592  std::make_pair(llvm::WeakTrackingVH(Old), New));
4593 }

4595 namespace {
4596 
4597 /// Specify given \p NewAlign as the alignment of return value attribute. If
4598 /// such attribute already exists, re-set it to the maximal one of two options.
4599 LLVM_NODISCARD llvm::AttributeList
4600 maybeRaiseRetAlignmentAttribute(llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx,
4601  const llvm::AttributeList &Attrs,
4602  llvm::Align NewAlign) {
4603  llvm::Align CurAlign = Attrs.getRetAlignment().valueOrOne();
4604  if (CurAlign >= NewAlign)
4605  return Attrs;
4606  llvm::Attribute AlignAttr = llvm::Attribute::getWithAlignment(Ctx, NewAlign);
4607  return Attrs.removeRetAttribute(Ctx, llvm::Attribute::AttrKind::Alignment)
4608  .addRetAttribute(Ctx, AlignAttr);
4609 }
4610 
4611 template <typename AlignedAttrTy> class AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter {
4612 protected:
4613  CodeGenFunction &CGF;
4614 
4615  /// We do nothing if this is, or becomes, nullptr.
4616  const AlignedAttrTy *AA = nullptr;
4617 
4618  llvm::Value *Alignment = nullptr; // May or may not be a constant.
4619  llvm::ConstantInt *OffsetCI = nullptr; // Constant, hopefully zero.
4620 
4621  AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl)
4622  : CGF(CGF_) {
4623  if (!FuncDecl)
4624  return;
4625  AA = FuncDecl->getAttr<AlignedAttrTy>();
4626  }
4627 
4628 public:
4629  /// If we can, materialize the alignment as an attribute on return value.
4630  LLVM_NODISCARD llvm::AttributeList
4631  TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(const llvm::AttributeList &Attrs) {
4632  if (!AA || OffsetCI || CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment))
4633  return Attrs;
4634  const auto *AlignmentCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Alignment);
4635  if (!AlignmentCI)
4636  return Attrs;
4637  // We may legitimately have non-power-of-2 alignment here.
4638  // If so, this is UB land, emit it via `@llvm.assume` instead.
4639  if (!AlignmentCI->getValue().isPowerOf2())
4640  return Attrs;
4641  llvm::AttributeList NewAttrs = maybeRaiseRetAlignmentAttribute(
4642  CGF.getLLVMContext(), Attrs,
4643  llvm::Align(
4644  AlignmentCI->getLimitedValue(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment)));
4645  AA = nullptr; // We're done. Disallow doing anything else.
4646  return NewAttrs;
4647  }
4648 
4649  /// Emit alignment assumption.
4650  /// This is a general fallback that we take if either there is an offset,
4651  /// or the alignment is variable or we are sanitizing for alignment.
4652  void EmitAsAnAssumption(SourceLocation Loc, QualType RetTy, RValue &Ret) {
4653  if (!AA)
4654  return;
4655  CGF.emitAlignmentAssumption(Ret.getScalarVal(), RetTy, Loc,
4656  AA->getLocation(), Alignment, OffsetCI);
4657  AA = nullptr; // We're done. Disallow doing anything else.
4658  }
4659 };
4660 
4661 /// Helper data structure to emit `AssumeAlignedAttr`.
4662 class AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter final
4663  : public AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter<AssumeAlignedAttr> {
4664 public:
4665  AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl)
4666  : AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CGF_, FuncDecl) {
4667  if (!AA)
4668  return;
4669  // It is guaranteed that the alignment/offset are constants.
4670  Alignment = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(AA->getAlignment()));
4671  if (Expr *Offset = AA->getOffset()) {
4672  OffsetCI = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Offset));
4673  if (OffsetCI->isNullValue()) // Canonicalize zero offset to no offset.
4674  OffsetCI = nullptr;
4675  }
4676  }
4677 };
4678 
4679 /// Helper data structure to emit `AllocAlignAttr`.
4680 class AllocAlignAttrEmitter final
4681  : public AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter<AllocAlignAttr> {
4682 public:
4683  AllocAlignAttrEmitter(CodeGenFunction &CGF_, const Decl *FuncDecl,
4684  const CallArgList &CallArgs)
4685  : AbstractAssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(CGF_, FuncDecl) {
4686  if (!AA)
4687  return;
4688  // Alignment may or may not be a constant, and that is okay.
4689  Alignment = CallArgs[AA->getParamIndex().getLLVMIndex()]
4690  .getRValue(CGF)
4691  .getScalarVal();
4692  }
4693 };
4694 
4695 } // namespace
4696 
4697 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(const CGFunctionInfo &CallInfo,
4698  const CGCallee &Callee,
4699  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
4700  const CallArgList &CallArgs,
4701  llvm::CallBase **callOrInvoke, bool IsMustTail,
4702  SourceLocation Loc) {
4703  // FIXME: We no longer need the types from CallArgs; lift up and simplify.
4704 
4705  assert(Callee.isOrdinary() || Callee.isVirtual());
4706 
4707  // Handle struct-return functions by passing a pointer to the
4708  // location that we would like to return into.
4709  QualType RetTy = CallInfo.getReturnType();
4710  const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = CallInfo.getReturnInfo();
4711 
4712  llvm::FunctionType *IRFuncTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(CallInfo);
4713 
4714  const Decl *TargetDecl = Callee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
4715  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
4716  // We can only guarantee that a function is called from the correct
4717  // context/function based on the appropriate target attributes,
4718  // so only check in the case where we have both always_inline and target
4719  // since otherwise we could be making a conditional call after a check for
4720  // the proper cpu features (and it won't cause code generation issues due to
4721  // function based code generation).
4722  if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
4723  TargetDecl->hasAttr<TargetAttr>())
4724  checkTargetFeatures(Loc, FD);
4725 
4726  // Some architectures (such as x86-64) have the ABI changed based on
4727  // attribute-target/features. Give them a chance to diagnose.
4728  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().checkFunctionCallABI(
4729  CGM, Loc, dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl), FD, CallArgs);
4730  }
4731 
4732 #ifndef NDEBUG
4733  if (!(CallInfo.isVariadic() && CallInfo.getArgStruct())) {
4734  // For an inalloca varargs function, we don't expect CallInfo to match the
4735  // function pointer's type, because the inalloca struct a will have extra
4736  // fields in it for the varargs parameters. Code later in this function
4737  // bitcasts the function pointer to the type derived from CallInfo.
4738  //
4739  // In other cases, we assert that the types match up (until pointers stop
4740  // having pointee types).
4741  if (Callee.isVirtual())
4742  assert(IRFuncTy == Callee.getVirtualFunctionType());
4743  else {
4744  llvm::PointerType *PtrTy =
4745  llvm::cast<llvm::PointerType>(Callee.getFunctionPointer()->getType());
4746  assert(PtrTy->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(IRFuncTy));
4747  }
4748  }
4749 #endif
4750 
4751  // 1. Set up the arguments.
4752 
4753  // If we're using inalloca, insert the allocation after the stack save.
4754  // FIXME: Do this earlier rather than hacking it in here!
4755  Address ArgMemory = Address::invalid();
4756  if (llvm::StructType *ArgStruct = CallInfo.getArgStruct()) {
4757  const llvm::DataLayout &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
4758  llvm::Instruction *IP = CallArgs.getStackBase();
4759  llvm::AllocaInst *AI;
4760  if (IP) {
4761  IP = IP->getNextNode();
4762  AI = new llvm::AllocaInst(ArgStruct, DL.getAllocaAddrSpace(),
4763  "argmem", IP);
4764  } else {
4765  AI = CreateTempAlloca(ArgStruct, "argmem");
4766  }
4767  auto Align = CallInfo.getArgStructAlignment();
4768  AI->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
4769  AI->setUsedWithInAlloca(true);
4770  assert(AI->isUsedWithInAlloca() && !AI->isStaticAlloca());
4771  ArgMemory = Address(AI, ArgStruct, Align);
4772  }
4773 
4774  ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), CallInfo);
4775  SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> IRCallArgs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
4776 
4777  // If the call returns a temporary with struct return, create a temporary
4778  // alloca to hold the result, unless one is given to us.
4779  Address SRetPtr = Address::invalid();
4780  Address SRetAlloca = Address::invalid();
4781  llvm::Value *UnusedReturnSizePtr = nullptr;
4782  if (RetAI.isIndirect() || RetAI.isInAlloca() || RetAI.isCoerceAndExpand()) {
4783  if (!ReturnValue.isNull()) {
4784  SRetPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
4785  } else {
4786  SRetPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "tmp", &SRetAlloca);
4787  if (HaveInsertPoint() && ReturnValue.isUnused()) {
4788  llvm::TypeSize size =
4789  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ConvertTypeForMem(RetTy));
4790  UnusedReturnSizePtr = EmitLifetimeStart(size, SRetAlloca.getPointer());
4791  }
4792  }
4793  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
4794  IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] = SRetPtr.getPointer();
4795  } else if (RetAI.isInAlloca()) {
4796  Address Addr =
4797  Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4798  Builder.CreateStore(SRetPtr.getPointer(), Addr);
4799  }
4800  }
4801 
4802  Address swiftErrorTemp = Address::invalid();
4803  Address swiftErrorArg = Address::invalid();
4804 
4805  // When passing arguments using temporary allocas, we need to add the
4806  // appropriate lifetime markers. This vector keeps track of all the lifetime
4807  // markers that need to be ended right after the call.
4808  SmallVector<CallLifetimeEnd, 2> CallLifetimeEndAfterCall;
4809 
4810  // Translate all of the arguments as necessary to match the IR lowering.
4811  assert(CallInfo.arg_size() == CallArgs.size() &&
4812  "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
4813  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
4814  CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = CallInfo.arg_begin();
4815  for (CallArgList::const_iterator I = CallArgs.begin(), E = CallArgs.end();
4816  I != E; ++I, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
4817  const ABIArgInfo &ArgInfo = info_it->info;
4818 
4819  // Insert a padding argument to ensure proper alignment.
4820  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo))
4821  IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
4822  llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgInfo.getPaddingType());
4823 
4824  unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
4825  std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
4826 
4827  switch (ArgInfo.getKind()) {
4828  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
4829  assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
4830  assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86);
4831  if (I->isAggregate()) {
4832  Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
4833  ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4834  : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4835  llvm::Instruction *Placeholder =
4836  cast<llvm::Instruction>(Addr.getPointer());
4837 
4838  if (!ArgInfo.getInAllocaIndirect()) {
4839  // Replace the placeholder with the appropriate argument slot GEP.
4840  CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint IP = Builder.saveIP();
4841  Builder.SetInsertPoint(Placeholder);
4842  Addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory,
4843  ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4844  Builder.restoreIP(IP);
4845  } else {
4846  // For indirect things such as overaligned structs, replace the
4847  // placeholder with a regular aggregate temporary alloca. Store the
4848  // address of this alloca into the struct.
4849  Addr = CreateMemTemp(info_it->type, "inalloca.indirect.tmp");
4850  Address ArgSlot = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
4851  ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4852  Builder.CreateStore(Addr.getPointer(), ArgSlot);
4853  }
4854  deferPlaceholderReplacement(Placeholder, Addr.getPointer());
4855  } else if (ArgInfo.getInAllocaIndirect()) {
4856  // Make a temporary alloca and store the address of it into the argument
4857  // struct.
4858  Address Addr = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4859  I->Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(I->Ty),
4860  "indirect-arg-temp");
4861  I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4862  Address ArgSlot =
4863  Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4864  Builder.CreateStore(Addr.getPointer(), ArgSlot);
4865  } else {
4866  // Store the RValue into the argument struct.
4867  Address Addr =
4868  Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
4869  // There are some cases where a trivial bitcast is not avoidable. The
4870  // definition of a type later in a translation unit may change it's type
4871  // from {}* to (%struct.foo*)*.
4872  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ConvertTypeForMem(I->Ty));
4873  I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4874  }
4875  break;
4876  }
4877 
4878  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
4879  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased: {
4880  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4881  if (!I->isAggregate()) {
4882  // Make a temporary alloca to pass the argument.
4883  Address Addr = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4884  I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "indirect-arg-temp");
4885  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = Addr.getPointer();
4886 
4887  I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
4888  } else {
4889  // We want to avoid creating an unnecessary temporary+copy here;
4890  // however, we need one in three cases:
4891  // 1. If the argument is not byval, and we are required to copy the
4892  // source. (This case doesn't occur on any common architecture.)
4893  // 2. If the argument is byval, RV is not sufficiently aligned, and
4894  // we cannot force it to be sufficiently aligned.
4895  // 3. If the argument is byval, but RV is not located in default
4896  // or alloca address space.
4897  Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
4898  ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4899  : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4900  llvm::Value *V = Addr.getPointer();
4901  CharUnits Align = ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign();
4902  const llvm::DataLayout *TD = &CGM.getDataLayout();
4903 
4904  assert((FirstIRArg >= IRFuncTy->getNumParams() ||
4905  IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
4906  TD->getAllocaAddrSpace()) &&
4907  "indirect argument must be in alloca address space");
4908 
4909  bool NeedCopy = false;
4910 
4911  if (Addr.getAlignment() < Align &&
4912  llvm::getOrEnforceKnownAlignment(V, Align.getAsAlign(), *TD) <
4913  Align.getAsAlign()) {
4914  NeedCopy = true;
4915  } else if (I->hasLValue()) {
4916  auto LV = I->getKnownLValue();
4917  auto AS = LV.getAddressSpace();
4918 
4919  if (!ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() ||
4920  (LV.getAlignment() < getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(I->Ty))) {
4921  NeedCopy = true;
4922  }
4923  if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4924  if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4925  (AS != LangAS::Default &&
4926  AS != CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace()))) {
4927  NeedCopy = true;
4928  }
4929  }
4930  // For OpenCL even if RV is located in default or alloca address space
4931  // we don't want to perform address space cast for it.
4932  else if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4933  Addr.getType()->getAddressSpace() != IRFuncTy->
4934  getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace())) {
4935  NeedCopy = true;
4936  }
4937  }
4938 
4939  if (NeedCopy) {
4940  // Create an aligned temporary, and copy to it.
4941  Address AI = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4942  I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "byval-temp");
4943  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = AI.getPointer();
4944 
4945  // Emit lifetime markers for the temporary alloca.
4946  llvm::TypeSize ByvalTempElementSize =
4947  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getElementType());
4948  llvm::Value *LifetimeSize =
4949  EmitLifetimeStart(ByvalTempElementSize, AI.getPointer());
4950 
4951  // Add cleanup code to emit the end lifetime marker after the call.
4952  if (LifetimeSize) // In case we disabled lifetime markers.
4953  CallLifetimeEndAfterCall.emplace_back(AI, LifetimeSize);
4954 
4955  // Generate the copy.
4956  I->copyInto(*this, AI);
4957  } else {
4958  // Skip the extra memcpy call.
4959  auto *T = llvm::PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(
4960  cast<llvm::PointerType>(V->getType()),
4961  CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace());
4962  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
4963  *this, V, LangAS::Default, CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), T,
4964  true);
4965  }
4966  }
4967  break;
4968  }
4969 
4970  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
4971  assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
4972  break;
4973 
4974  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
4975  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
4976  if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType()) &&
4977  ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(info_it->type) &&
4978  ArgInfo.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
4979  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4980  llvm::Value *V;
4981  if (!I->isAggregate())
4982  V = I->getKnownRValue().getScalarVal();
4983  else
4984  V = Builder.CreateLoad(
4985  I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
4986  : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress());
4987 
4988  // Implement swifterror by copying into a new swifterror argument.
4989  // We'll write back in the normal path out of the call.
4990  if (CallInfo.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
4991  == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
4992  assert(!swiftErrorTemp.isValid() && "multiple swifterror args");
4993 
4994  QualType pointeeTy = I->Ty->getPointeeType();
4995  swiftErrorArg = Address(V, ConvertTypeForMem(pointeeTy),
4996  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
4997 
4998  swiftErrorTemp =
4999  CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
5000  V = swiftErrorTemp.getPointer();
5001  cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(V)->setSwiftError(true);
5002 
5003  llvm::Value *errorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorArg);
5004  Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, swiftErrorTemp);
5005  }
5006 
5007  // We might have to widen integers, but we should never truncate.
5008  if (ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() != V->getType() &&
5009  V->getType()->isIntegerTy())
5010  V = Builder.CreateZExt(V, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
5011 
5012  // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
5013  // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
5014  if (FirstIRArg < IRFuncTy->getNumParams() &&
5015  V->getType() != IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg)) {
5016  if (V->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() !=
5017  IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace())
5018  V = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(V,
5019  IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg));
5020  else
5021  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg));
5022  }
5023  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = V;
5024  break;
5025  }
5026 
5027  // FIXME: Avoid the conversion through memory if possible.
5028  Address Src = Address::invalid();
5029  if (!I->isAggregate()) {
5030  Src = CreateMemTemp(I->Ty, "coerce");
5031  I->copyInto(*this, Src);
5032  } else {
5033  Src = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
5034  : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
5035  }
5036 
5037  // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
5038  Src = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Src, ArgInfo);
5039 
5040  // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
5041  // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
5042  llvm::StructType *STy =
5043  dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
5044  if (STy && ArgInfo.isDirect() && ArgInfo.getCanBeFlattened()) {
5045  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src.getElementType();
5046  uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
5047  uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
5048 
5049  // If the source type is smaller than the destination type of the
5050  // coerce-to logic, copy the source value into a temp alloca the size
5051  // of the destination type to allow loading all of it. The bits past
5052  // the source value are left undef.
5053  if (SrcSize < DstSize) {
5054  Address TempAlloca
5055  = CreateTempAlloca(STy, Src.getAlignment(),
5056  Src.getName() + ".coerce");
5057  Builder.CreateMemCpy(TempAlloca, Src, SrcSize);
5058  Src = TempAlloca;
5059  } else {
5060  Src = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Src, STy);
5061  }
5062 
5063  assert(NumIRArgs == STy->getNumElements());
5064  for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
5065  Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Src, i);
5066  llvm::Value *LI = Builder.CreateLoad(EltPtr);
5067  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg + i] = LI;
5068  }
5069  } else {
5070  // In the simple case, just pass the coerced loaded value.
5071  assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
5072  llvm::Value *Load =
5073  CreateCoercedLoad(Src, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType(), *this);
5074 
5075  if (CallInfo.isCmseNSCall()) {
5076  // For certain parameter types, clear padding bits, as they may reveal
5077  // sensitive information.
5078  // Small struct/union types are passed as integer arrays.
5079  auto *ATy = dyn_cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Load->getType());
5080  if (ATy != nullptr && isa<RecordType>(I->Ty.getCanonicalType()))
5081  Load = EmitCMSEClearRecord(Load, ATy, I->Ty);
5082  }
5083  IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = Load;
5084  }
5085 
5086  break;
5087  }
5088 
5089  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
5090  auto coercionType = ArgInfo.getCoerceAndExpandType();
5091  auto layout = CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(coercionType);
5092 
5093  llvm::Value *tempSize = nullptr;
5094  Address addr = Address::invalid();
5095  Address AllocaAddr = Address::invalid();
5096  if (I->isAggregate()) {
5097  addr = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress(*this)
5098  : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
5099 
5100  } else {
5101  RValue RV = I->getKnownRValue();
5102  assert(RV.isScalar()); // complex should always just be direct
5103 
5104  llvm::Type *scalarType = RV.getScalarVal()->getType();
5105  auto scalarSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(scalarType);
5106  auto scalarAlign = CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(scalarType);
5107 
5108  // Materialize to a temporary.
5109  addr =
5110  CreateTempAlloca(RV.getScalarVal()->getType(),
5111  CharUnits::fromQuantity(std::max(
5112  layout->getAlignment().value(), scalarAlign)),
5113  "tmp",
5114  /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, &AllocaAddr);
5115  tempSize = EmitLifetimeStart(scalarSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
5116 
5117  Builder.CreateStore(RV.getScalarVal(), addr);
5118  }
5119 
5120  addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
5121 
5122  unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
5123  for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
5124  llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
5125  if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
5126  Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
5127  llvm::Value *elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
5128  IRCallArgs[IRArgPos++] = elt;
5129  }
5130  assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
5131 
5132  if (tempSize) {
5133  EmitLifetimeEnd(tempSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
5134  }
5135 
5136  break;
5137  }
5138 
5139  case ABIArgInfo::Expand: {
5140  unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
5141  ExpandTypeToArgs(I->Ty, *I, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs, IRArgPos);
5142  assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
5143  break;
5144  }
5145  }
5146  }
5147 
5148  const CGCallee &ConcreteCallee = Callee.prepareConcreteCallee(*this);
5149  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = ConcreteCallee.getFunctionPointer();
5150 
5151  // If we're using inalloca, set up that argument.
5152  if (ArgMemory.isValid()) {
5153  llvm::Value *Arg = ArgMemory.getPointer();
5154  if (CallInfo.isVariadic()) {
5155  // When passing non-POD arguments by value to variadic functions, we will
5156  // end up with a variadic prototype and an inalloca call site. In such
5157  // cases, we can't do any parameter mismatch checks. Give up and bitcast
5158  // the callee.
5159  unsigned CalleeAS = CalleePtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
5160  CalleePtr =
5161  Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, IRFuncTy->getPointerTo(CalleeAS));
5162  } else {
5163  llvm::Type *LastParamTy =
5164  IRFuncTy->getParamType(IRFuncTy->getNumParams() - 1);
5165  if (Arg->getType() != LastParamTy) {
5166 #ifndef NDEBUG
5167  // Assert that these structs have equivalent element types.
5168  llvm::StructType *FullTy = CallInfo.getArgStruct();
5169  if (!LastParamTy->isOpaquePointerTy()) {
5170  llvm::StructType *DeclaredTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(
5171  LastParamTy->getNonOpaquePointerElementType());
5172  assert(DeclaredTy->getNumElements() == FullTy->getNumElements());
5173  for (auto DI = DeclaredTy->element_begin(),
5174  DE = DeclaredTy->element_end(),
5175  FI = FullTy->element_begin();
5176  DI != DE; ++DI, ++FI)
5177  assert(*DI == *FI);
5178  }
5179 #endif
5180  Arg = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg, LastParamTy);
5181  }
5182  }
5183  assert(IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg());
5184  IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] = Arg;
5185  }
5186 
5187  // 2. Prepare the function pointer.
5188 
5189  // If the callee is a bitcast of a non-variadic function to have a
5190  // variadic function pointer type, check to see if we can remove the
5191  // bitcast. This comes up with unprototyped functions.
5192  //
5193  // This makes the IR nicer, but more importantly it ensures that we
5194  // can inline the function at -O0 if it is marked always_inline.
5195  auto simplifyVariadicCallee = [](llvm::FunctionType *CalleeFT,
5196  llvm::Value *Ptr) -> llvm::Function * {
5197  if (!CalleeFT->isVarArg())
5198  return nullptr;
5199 
5200  // Get underlying value if it's a bitcast
5201  if (llvm::ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Ptr)) {
5202  if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
5203  Ptr = CE->getOperand(0);
5204  }
5205 
5206  llvm::Function *OrigFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Ptr);
5207  if (!OrigFn)
5208  return nullptr;
5209 
5210  llvm::FunctionType *OrigFT = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
5211 
5212  // If the original type is variadic, or if any of the component types
5213  // disagree, we cannot remove the cast.
5214  if (OrigFT->isVarArg() ||
5215  OrigFT->getNumParams() != CalleeFT->getNumParams() ||
5216  OrigFT->getReturnType() != CalleeFT->getReturnType())
5217  return nullptr;
5218 
5219  for (unsigned i = 0, e = OrigFT->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i)
5220  if (OrigFT->getParamType(i) != CalleeFT->getParamType(i))
5221  return nullptr;
5222 
5223  return OrigFn;
5224  };
5225 
5226  if (llvm::Function *OrigFn = simplifyVariadicCallee(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr)) {
5227  CalleePtr = OrigFn;
5228  IRFuncTy = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
5229  }
5230 
5231  // 3. Perform the actual call.
5232 
5233  // Deactivate any cleanups that we're supposed to do immediately before
5234  // the call.
5235  if (!CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate().empty())
5236  deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(*this, CallArgs);
5237 
5238  // Assert that the arguments we computed match up. The IR verifier
5239  // will catch this, but this is a common enough source of problems
5240  // during IRGen changes that it's way better for debugging to catch
5241  // it ourselves here.
5242 #ifndef NDEBUG
5243  assert(IRCallArgs.size() == IRFuncTy->getNumParams() || IRFuncTy->isVarArg());
5244  for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
5245  // Inalloca argument can have different type.
5246  if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg() &&
5247  i == IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo())
5248  continue;
5249  if (i < IRFuncTy->getNumParams())
5250  assert(IRCallArgs[i]->getType() == IRFuncTy->getParamType(i));
5251  }
5252 #endif
5253 
5254  // Update the largest vector width if any arguments have vector types.
5255  for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
5256  if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(IRCallArgs[i]->getType()))
5257  LargestVectorWidth =
5258  std::max((uint64_t)LargestVectorWidth,
5259  VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize());
5260  }
5261 
5262  // Compute the calling convention and attributes.
5263  unsigned CallingConv;
5264  llvm::AttributeList Attrs;
5265  CGM.ConstructAttributeList(CalleePtr->getName(), CallInfo,
5266  Callee.getAbstractInfo(), Attrs, CallingConv,
5267  /*AttrOnCallSite=*/true,
5268  /*IsThunk=*/false);
5269 
5270  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl))
5271  if (FD->hasAttr<StrictFPAttr>())
5272  // All calls within a strictfp function are marked strictfp
5273  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::StrictFP);
5274 
5275  // Add call-site nomerge attribute if exists.
5276  if (InNoMergeAttributedStmt)
5277  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::NoMerge);
5278 
5279  // Add call-site noinline attribute if exists.
5280  if (InNoInlineAttributedStmt)
5281  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
5282 
5283  // Add call-site always_inline attribute if exists.
5284  if (InAlwaysInlineAttributedStmt)
5285  Attrs =
5286  Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
5287 
5288  // Apply some call-site-specific attributes.
5289  // TODO: work this into building the attribute set.
5290 
5291  // Apply always_inline to all calls within flatten functions.
5292  // FIXME: should this really take priority over __try, below?
5293  if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<FlattenAttr>() &&
5294  !InNoInlineAttributedStmt &&
5295  !(TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>())) {
5296  Attrs =
5297  Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
5298  }
5299 
5300  // Disable inlining inside SEH __try blocks.
5301  if (isSEHTryScope()) {
5302  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
5303  }
5304 
5305  // Decide whether to use a call or an invoke.
5306  bool CannotThrow;
5307  if (currentFunctionUsesSEHTry()) {
5308  // SEH cares about asynchronous exceptions, so everything can "throw."
5309  CannotThrow = false;
5310  } else if (isCleanupPadScope() &&
5311  EHPersonality::get(*this).isMSVCXXPersonality()) {
5312  // The MSVC++ personality will implicitly terminate the program if an
5313  // exception is thrown during a cleanup outside of a try/catch.
5314  // We don't need to model anything in IR to get this behavior.
5315  CannotThrow = true;
5316  } else {
5317  // Otherwise, nounwind call sites will never throw.
5318  CannotThrow = Attrs.hasFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
5319 
5320  if (auto *FPtr = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(CalleePtr))
5321  if (FPtr->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind))
5322  CannotThrow = true;
5323  }
5324 
5325  // If we made a temporary, be sure to clean up after ourselves. Note that we
5326  // can't depend on being inside of an ExprWithCleanups, so we need to manually
5327  // pop this cleanup later on. Being eager about this is OK, since this
5328  // temporary is 'invisible' outside of the callee.
5329  if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5330  pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, SRetAlloca,
5331  UnusedReturnSizePtr);
5332 
5333  llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = CannotThrow ? nullptr : getInvokeDest();
5334 
5335  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
5336  getBundlesForFunclet(CalleePtr);
5337 
5338  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl))
5339  if (FD->hasAttr<StrictFPAttr>())
5340  // All calls within a strictfp function are marked strictfp
5341  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::Attribute::StrictFP);
5342 
5343  AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter(*this, TargetDecl);
5344  Attrs = AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter.TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(Attrs);
5345 
5346  AllocAlignAttrEmitter AllocAlignAttrEmitter(*this, TargetDecl, CallArgs);
5347  Attrs = AllocAlignAttrEmitter.TryEmitAsCallSiteAttribute(Attrs);
5348 
5349  // Emit the actual call/invoke instruction.
5350  llvm::CallBase *CI;
5351  if (!InvokeDest) {
5352  CI = Builder.CreateCall(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, IRCallArgs, BundleList);
5353  } else {
5354  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
5355  CI = Builder.CreateInvoke(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, Cont, InvokeDest, IRCallArgs,
5356  BundleList);
5357  EmitBlock(Cont);
5358  }
5359  if (callOrInvoke)
5360  *callOrInvoke = CI;
5361 
5362  // If this is within a function that has the guard(nocf) attribute and is an
5363  // indirect call, add the "guard_nocf" attribute to this call to indicate that
5364  // Control Flow Guard checks should not be added, even if the call is inlined.
5365  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurFuncDecl)) {
5366  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<CFGuardAttr>()) {
5367  if (A->getGuard() == CFGuardAttr::GuardArg::nocf && !CI->getCalledFunction())
5368  Attrs = Attrs.addFnAttribute(getLLVMContext(), "guard_nocf");
5369  }
5370  }
5371 
5372  // Apply the attributes and calling convention.
5373  CI->setAttributes(Attrs);
5374  CI->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(CallingConv));
5375 
5376  // Apply various metadata.
5377 
5378  if (!CI->getType()->isVoidTy())
5379  CI->setName("call");
5380 
5381  // Update largest vector width from the return type.
5382  if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(CI->getType()))
5383  LargestVectorWidth =
5384  std::max((uint64_t)LargestVectorWidth,
5385  VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize());
5386 
5387  // Insert instrumentation or attach profile metadata at indirect call sites.
5388  // For more details, see the comment before the definition of
5389  // IPVK_IndirectCallTarget in InstrProfData.inc.
5390  if (!CI->getCalledFunction())
5391  PGO.valueProfile(Builder, llvm::IPVK_IndirectCallTarget,
5392  CI, CalleePtr);
5393 
5394  // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
5395  // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
5396  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
5397  AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(CI);
5398 
5399  // Set tail call kind if necessary.
5400  if (llvm::CallInst *Call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(CI)) {
5401  if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NotTailCalledAttr>())
5402  Call->setTailCallKind(llvm::CallInst::TCK_NoTail);
5403  else if (IsMustTail)
5404  Call->setTailCallKind(llvm::CallInst::TCK_MustTail);
5405  }
5406 
5407  // Add metadata for calls to MSAllocator functions
5408  if (getDebugInfo() && TargetDecl &&
5409  TargetDecl->hasAttr<MSAllocatorAttr>())
5410  getDebugInfo()->addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(CI, RetTy->getPointeeType(), Loc);
5411 
5412  // Add metadata if calling an __attribute__((error(""))) or warning fn.
5413  if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<ErrorAttr>()) {
5414  llvm::ConstantInt *Line =
5415  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Loc.getRawEncoding());
5416  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata *MD = llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Line);
5417  llvm::MDTuple *MDT = llvm::MDNode::get(getLLVMContext(), {MD});
5418  CI->setMetadata("srcloc", MDT);
5419  }
5420 
5421  // 4. Finish the call.
5422 
5423  // SYCL does not support C++ exceptions or termination in device code, so all
5424  // functions have to return.
5425  bool SyclSkipNoReturn = false;
5426  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice && CI->doesNotReturn()) {
5427  if (auto *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
5428  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5429  CI->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5430  SyclSkipNoReturn = true;
5431  }
5432 
5433  // If the call doesn't return for non-sycl devices, finish the basic block and
5434  // clear the insertion point; this allows the rest of IRGen to discard
5435  // unreachable code.
5436  if (!SyclSkipNoReturn && CI->doesNotReturn()) {
5437  if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5438  PopCleanupBlock();
5439 
5440  // Strip away the noreturn attribute to better diagnose unreachable UB.
5441  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
5442  // Also remove from function since CallBase::hasFnAttr additionally checks
5443  // attributes of the called function.
5444  if (auto *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
5445  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5446  CI->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5447 
5448  // Avoid incompatibility with ASan which relies on the `noreturn`
5449  // attribute to insert handler calls.
5450  if (SanOpts.hasOneOf(SanitizerKind::Address |
5451  SanitizerKind::KernelAddress)) {
5452  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5453  llvm::IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPGuard(Builder);
5454  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CI);
5455  auto *FnType = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
5456  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn =
5457  CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FnType, "__asan_handle_no_return");
5458  EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn);
5459  }
5460  }
5461 
5462  EmitUnreachable(Loc);
5463  Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
5464 
5465  // FIXME: For now, emit a dummy basic block because expr emitters in
5466  // generally are not ready to handle emitting expressions at unreachable
5467  // points.
5468  EnsureInsertPoint();
5469 
5470  // Return a reasonable RValue.
5471  return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
5472  }
5473 
5474  // If this is a musttail call, return immediately. We do not branch to the
5475  // epilogue in this case.
5476  if (IsMustTail) {
5477  for (auto it = EHStack.find(CurrentCleanupScopeDepth); it != EHStack.end();
5478  ++it) {
5479  EHCleanupScope *Cleanup = dyn_cast<EHCleanupScope>(&*it);
5480  if (!(Cleanup && Cleanup->getCleanup()->isRedundantBeforeReturn()))
5481  CGM.ErrorUnsupported(MustTailCall, "tail call skipping over cleanups");
5482  }
5483  if (CI->getType()->isVoidTy())
5484  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
5485  else
5486  Builder.CreateRet(CI);
5487  Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
5488  EnsureInsertPoint();
5489  return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
5490  }
5491 
5492  // Perform the swifterror writeback.
5493  if (swiftErrorTemp.isValid()) {
5494  llvm::Value *errorResult = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorTemp);
5495  Builder.CreateStore(errorResult, swiftErrorArg);
5496  }
5497 
5498  // Emit any call-associated writebacks immediately. Arguably this
5499  // should happen after any return-value munging.
5500  if (CallArgs.hasWritebacks())
5501  emitWritebacks(*this, CallArgs);
5502 
5503  // The stack cleanup for inalloca arguments has to run out of the normal
5504  // lexical order, so deactivate it and run it manually here.
5505  CallArgs.freeArgumentMemory(*this);
5506 
5507  // Extract the return value.
5508  RValue Ret = [&] {
5509  switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
5510  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
5511  auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
5512 
5513  Address addr = SRetPtr;
5514  addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
5515 
5516  assert(CI->getType() == RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType());
5517  bool requiresExtract = isa<llvm::StructType>(CI->getType());
5518 
5519  unsigned unpaddedIndex = 0;
5520  for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
5521  llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
5522  if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
5523  Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
5524  llvm::Value *elt = CI;
5525  if (requiresExtract)
5526  elt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(elt, unpaddedIndex++);
5527  else
5528  assert(unpaddedIndex == 0);
5529  Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
5530  }
5531  // FALLTHROUGH
5532  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5533  }
5534 
5535  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
5536  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
5537  RValue ret = convertTempToRValue(SRetPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
5538  if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
5539  PopCleanupBlock();
5540  return ret;
5541  }
5542 
5543  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
5544  // If we are ignoring an argument that had a result, make sure to
5545  // construct the appropriate return value for our caller.
5546  return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
5547 
5548  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
5549  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
5550  llvm::Type *RetIRTy = ConvertType(RetTy);
5551  if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == RetIRTy && RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
5552  switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
5553  case TEK_Complex: {
5554  llvm::Value *Real = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 0);
5555  llvm::Value *Imag = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 1);
5556  return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(Real, Imag));
5557  }
5558  case TEK_Aggregate: {
5559  Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
5560  bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
5561 
5562  if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
5563  DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "agg.tmp");
5564  DestIsVolatile = false;
5565  }
5566  EmitAggregateStore(CI, DestPtr, DestIsVolatile);
5567  return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
5568  }
5569  case TEK_Scalar: {
5570  // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
5571  // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
5572  llvm::Value *V = CI;
5573  if (V->getType() != RetIRTy)
5574  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, RetIRTy);
5575  return RValue::get(V);
5576  }
5577  }
5578  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5579  }
5580 
5581  Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
5582  bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
5583 
5584  if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
5585  DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "coerce");
5586  DestIsVolatile = false;
5587  }
5588 
5589  // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
5590  Address StorePtr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, DestPtr, RetAI);
5591  CreateCoercedStore(CI, StorePtr, DestIsVolatile, *this);
5592 
5593  return convertTempToRValue(DestPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
5594  }
5595 
5596  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
5597  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
5598  llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
5599  }
5600 
5601  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled ABIArgInfo::Kind");
5602  } ();
5603 
5604  // Emit the assume_aligned check on the return value.
5605  if (Ret.isScalar() && TargetDecl) {
5606  AssumeAlignedAttrEmitter.EmitAsAnAssumption(Loc, RetTy, Ret);
5607  AllocAlignAttrEmitter.EmitAsAnAssumption(Loc, RetTy, Ret);
5608  }
5609 
5610  // Explicitly call CallLifetimeEnd::Emit just to re-use the code even though
5611  // we can't use the full cleanup mechanism.
5612  for (CallLifetimeEnd &LifetimeEnd : CallLifetimeEndAfterCall)
5613  LifetimeEnd.Emit(*this, /*Flags=*/{});
5614 
5615  if (!ReturnValue.isExternallyDestructed() &&
5616  RetTy.isDestructedType() == QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct)
5617  pushDestroy(QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct, Ret.getAggregateAddress(),
5618  RetTy);
5619 
5620  return Ret;
5621 }
5622 
5623 CGCallee CGCallee::prepareConcreteCallee(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
5624  if (isVirtual()) {
5625  const CallExpr *CE = getVirtualCallExpr();
5626  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().getVirtualFunctionPointer(
5627  CGF, getVirtualMethodDecl(), getThisAddress(), getVirtualFunctionType(),
5628  CE ? CE->getBeginLoc() : SourceLocation());
5629  }
5630 
5631  return *this;
5632 }
5633 
5634 /* VarArg handling */
5635 
5636 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitVAArg(VAArgExpr *VE, Address &VAListAddr) {
5637  VAListAddr = VE->isMicrosoftABI()
5638  ? EmitMSVAListRef(VE->getSubExpr())
5639  : EmitVAListRef(VE->getSubExpr());
5640  QualType Ty = VE->getType();
5641  if (VE->isMicrosoftABI())
5642  return CGM.getTypes().getABIInfo().EmitMSVAArg(*this, VAListAddr, Ty);
5643  return CGM.getTypes().getABIInfo().EmitVAArg(*this, VAListAddr, Ty);
5644 }
